formatted_address: 730 N Rush St, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Giordano's

reviews.text:
Started off with the tomato bruschetta and WOW straight fire! Juicy tomatoes, fresh basil, that sweet balsamic drizzle... it was like the Avengers of appetizers, teaming up to knock our tastebuds out.
Then came the main event: our very first Chicago deep dish pizza. Let me tell you Giordano’s did not disappoint. That pizza was next level amazing. The cheese? Gooey perfection. The toppings? Flavor-packed. The crust? Thin, crispy, and holding it all together like a champ. The sauce, cheese, and toppings were blended into this magical, super-fantastic bite after bite experience.
We legit agreed we’d hop in the car from Cleveland just to eat here again it’s that good. 10/10, highly recommend, will absolutely be back! Giordano’s, you officially have us hooked for life!

This is a must eat place for deep dish pizza!! LaLa our waitress was amazing!! She had a great personality along with the great food. The medium deep dish was more than enough for two. Warning!! One slice is like eating two with cheese that stretches for miles.

This is my first time in Chicago, and Giordano's is one of the best rated. Gotta try the best, right?! Well...if you're here on business, don't tell the guy at the bar that you just want a small personal pizza. He'll get you their "small", which is 10 inches, and then tell you that you should have said "individual" if you wanted...you know...the small one. 🤦‍♂️😖 Yes I read the menu...as best I could, anyway—it was on my phone and I didn't realize there were such nuances to it. So how was the food?! Well...pretty tasty, for sure. And if you like cheese, you're gonna love this! I ordered the The Special, which is 10 inches wide (the "small" one, anyway 🙄) and at least 1 inch deep of pure cheese. There's an occasional sausage, pepper or mushroom in there, but make no mistake: you're buying a hell of a lot of cheese. Do I regret going? That wasn't quite what I thought a $30 pizza should be. I think I'll try somewhere a little more "hole in the wall" next time.

We had our first experience trying the iconic Chicago deep dish pizza, and it absolutely lived up to the hype. The generous layers of cheese, rich tomato sauce, and perfectly baked crust were all top-notch. Be prepared for a bit of a wait—both in line and for the pizza itself (about 30–40 minutes)—but it’s totally worth it. The service was excellent, and the staff was friendly and helpful throughout. A must-visit spot when you’re in Chicago!

Great service waitress was excellent. Came in with a party of 6 and ordered a decent amount of food. Everyone’s order came out perfectly- no errors. Pizza was hot. There was a nearby giordanos (different location ) where our food came out cold so we were very happy at this location. Drink refills came quickly. Would definitely be a repeat customer.

formatted_address: 445 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Frontera Grill

reviews.text: Absolutely love this place! The Mexican food is always spot on—fresh, flavorful, and satisfying. The real highlight? The drinks! Juliana and Esmeralda are amazing behind the bar—friendly, attentive, and they know how to mix a killer margarita. Great vibes all around. Highly recommend!

Y’all, the Windy City done blew me into this place and let me tell ya, hurricane winds had to blow me out! Lookin for that authentic taste, blasting all types of flavors in your mouth… well this the place. Our server knew his food and suggested margaritas that best paired with the dish. Bout those margs, go ahead and let the first one hit them lips and tell me you ain’t getting another one, I’ll wait! Make reservations, no dress requirement, clean, and for sure decently priced!

We had the 3 course lunch today and it was excellent! So much food that we walked back to our hotel and I may only have fruit later. Our server was Felipe and he took excellent care to make our first experience here a joy. Highly recommend.

I had a great experience here! Right after our waiter knows I can’t have pork products, he provided me alternative options to chips since it’s fired with pork skin together. This small gesture and his knowledge of the ingredients and food processing amazed me. I would say great food and superb service! Highly recommended!

While I was excited to try their vegetarian menu and go to acclaimed Mexican restaurant, I left disappointed. I thought the starters were good, but the entrees (especially the enchiladas) were completely overwhelmed by the sauce. The mole became one note as you then can’t taste anything else on the plate. That dish, along with the high prices, made for an average dining experience overall. The other dishes were better, but nothing stood out as a showstopper or reason for me to return to try other items on the menu. Service was great and the location is situated in the heart of Chicago… but the food left me wanting more.

formatted_address: 5220 Fashion Outlets Way, Rosemont, IL 60018, USA
name: Fashion Outlets of Chicago

reviews.text: This mall was very easy to access thanks to its attached parking garage with plenty of available parking inside. The mall is full of name brand designer clothing stores along with your "average joe" clothing stores, so theres definitely something for everyone. Several stores also had uniformed police at the entryway for added security, we felt very safe walking the entirety of the mall. There's also a large foodcourt with options from pizza to Chinese, think your typical mall food court. Overall an excellent mall full of stores!

This is a nice place for clothes shopping as well as walking around. The location is incredible right off I-294.

The parking garage has 7 levels. It gets busy on the weekends.

Food court has a decent selection of foods and dessert places.

Such a fun shopping experience! This outlet mall is beautiful—clean, bustling, and easy to navigate with plenty of parking. Super convenient too—right off the highway and even accessible by shuttle from the Rosemont Blue Line station. There’s a great mix of stores, from high-end spots like Gucci to everyday favorites like Bath & Body Works, plus the exciting new Pop Mart! The food court has solid options too, whether you’re craving a classic slice from Sbarro, some ramen, burgers, or even a Chicago-style beef. Honestly, being here felt like a throwback to high school—shopping with my friend, laughing nonstop, and half-joking about recreating that iconic Cruel Intentions escalator scene. A total 90s vibe.

Audited Verified Review (AVR)

The Fashion Outlets of Chicago, located in Rosemont, IL, opened in August 2013. Developed by Macerich, a leading REIT, the 530,000 sq. ft. mall was designed as a premium outlet destination, featuring over 130 stores, including luxury brands like Gucci and Prada. Built near O’Hare International Airport, it targets both local shoppers and travelers. Its modern design, with indoor parking and a focus on high-end retail, marked it as a significant addition to Chicago’s retail landscape, revitalizing the Rosemont area.

NAICS Code
531120 (Lessors of Nonresidential Buildings, except Miniwarehouses), reflecting its primary activity of leasing retail space to tenants etc.

Ownership
Owned by Macerich, a publicly traded REIT headquartered in Santa Monica, CA. Macerich developed and retains ownership, managing the property as part of its portfolio of premium retail centers.

Management
Managed by Macerich, with a dedicated on-site team led by General Manager Hawkins overseeing leasing, operations, and events. The management office handles tenant relations, marketing, and maintenance, ensuring a high-quality shopping experience.

Address
Fashion Outlets of Chicago

Rosemont, IL 60018

Economic Impact
The 530,000 sq. ft. mall generates significant economic activity in Rosemont, attracting millions of visitors annually due to its proximity to O’Hare Airport. With 130+ stores, it drives retail sales, local taxes, and tourism revenue. The outlet’s development created a retail hub, boosting nearby businesses and hotels. While exact figures are proprietary, its economic contributions include job creation and increased municipal revenue, solidifying Rosemont’s commercial appeal.

Employment
The outlet employs ~100–150 directly for management, security, and maintenance. Retail tenants (e.g., Bloomingdale’s Outlet, Nordstrom Rack) employ ~1,000–1,500 workers, based on typical outlet staffing. Seasonal hiring for holidays or events adds jobs. The mall supports ~1,100–1,700 total jobs, a key employer in Rosemont.

Compliance
Adheres to federal, state, and local regulations for commercial real estate, including building codes, ADA accessibility, and workplace safety. Macerich ensures environmental compliance through waste management and energy-efficient systems. Tenant leases enforce labor and ethical standards. No major violations are reported, indicating strong compliance.

Reputation
Highly regarded as a premier outlet mall, praised for its upscale brands, modern design, and accessibility. Reviews on platforms like Yelp highlight its variety and convenience for travelers, though some note high prices. Its 4-star ratings reflect a positive reputation among shoppers and tourists, with minor critiques on parking fees.

Social Responsibility Participation & Involvement Score (SRPIS)

•  Diversity: Macerich promotes diversity corporately, but tenant workforce diversity data is unavailable. (Basic)
•  Governance: Transparent operations with no ethical issues reported. (Strong)
•  Philanthropy: Partners with charities for events (e.g., breast cancer awareness), but ongoing efforts are not well-publicized. (Basic-Moderate)
Data Gathering: Based on Macerich’s sustainability reports, tenant reviews, and public data.

Disclaimer

High end shopping I guess. It's a mall. Go to the top of the parking garage to watch the planes take off from O'Hare. That's the best part of this mall.

formatted_address: 444 Michigan Ave, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: The Purple Pig Restaurant

reviews.text: Very good dinner. Unique dining experience. I would highly recommend for the foodie, but there is also plenty to eat for the less adventurous diners in your party. Beautiful location off Michigan Ave. I recommend reservations. We had a wheelchair in our group, and they were very accommodating.

Highly recommended by the docent of the architectural boat tour. Gourmet food, wonderful shareable, portions and very entertaining service in a lively, cheerful atmosphere! The bone narrow appetizer was the best we’ve ever had. Everything was expertly prepared, well season, but not over seasoned, and beautifully presented.

This restaurant was truly impressive. The 36-Day Aged Pork Chop was a revelation—cooked to perfection, as rich and flavorful as a top-tier steak. The Spanish Octopus was juicy with a slight char on the outside, complemented beautifully by its sauce. The Pork Shank was incredibly tender, falling off the bone effortlessly, while the Seafood Risotto was packed with flavor, with perfectly cooked rice. Overall, I highly recommend this restaurant, especially the aged pork chop, it was an unforgettable culinary experience.

Hands down one of the best dining experiences I’ve ever had. The staff made us feel like VIPs- attentive, friendly, and on point with every detail. Honestly, with how well we were treated, we might have been in a five-star restaurant.

My drink never hit empty, the food came out fast and piping hot, and every single dish was a knockout. We tried the bone marrow (rich and buttery), the pork pâté (perfectly seasoned), and the brown butter short rib ravioli (don’t even get me started, trust me, just order it).

The vibe, the service, the food- chef’s kiss. I’d go back in a heartbeat.

Great experience here. We ordered a bunch of different apps and entrees and shared between 6 of us. The dishes come out as they're ready (apps before entrees tho) and it's a perfect steady flow of food constantly coming to the table. All the flavors were good and seasoned well. Service was attentive and friendly.

formatted_address: 162 E Superior St, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Gino's East

reviews.text:
We went to Gino’s East in Chicago and wow—the deep dish pizza was absolutely worth the 45-minute wait! It was cheesy, flavorful, and just the right kind of indulgent. While we waited, we ordered the hummus plate and honestly, it was surprisingly delicious—fresh, creamy, and beautifully served.

This place totally lived up to the hype. The taste is still on my mind, and I’d 100% come back again.

Pizza was really good, and the salads.were amazing.  Really good flavor and service.  Jason did an great job explaining everything and taking care of us.  Katie was training as a bartender and took good care of us with drinks.  Awesome experience.. delicious pizza.

Food was GREAT. Debate is settled- Chicago style is better than New York style (coming from a person from neither city therefore my opinion is completely unbiased). This restaurant was so cute and oldie looking. The chicken Alfredo was also delicious! I’d only say our waiter kinda seemed to rush us and not really care too much but other than that everything was great. I recommend if you want bomb pizza!

Gino’s was a highly recommended place for Chicago-style pizza by a number of people we met during a recent visit to Chicago.  And they were right.  The atmosphere is sports bar like but not too noisy, and the staff friendly and attentive.  The deep dish pizza is thick and delicious, and filling.  We started wanting a size up but our waiter recommended sizing down based upon other food we wanted.  It was a great recommend and worked out perfectly.  This truly is a nice place for delicious Chicago pies.

Quick wedding anniversary getaway to Chicago! The long wait was worth our while... Outstanding service by Marco and their lady manager! Groovy, family friendly vibes. Food was outstanding. We were happy to bring back leftovers to our room.

formatted_address: 51 W Kinzie St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Siena Tavern

reviews.text: Came for the first time to this place on a dinner date and it was amazing. The second you walk in you’re greeted in a friendly and professional manner. The vibe is good and the music is louder than at a usual restaurant but I liked that part too. My favorite part were the dishes. We got an entree, a plate and dessert. It was an experience of different tastes that all come together so well. Their cocktails were also good and the server that we got gave us good recommendations. Overall 10/10 recommend!

I visited this place after seeing great reviews, and it definitely lived up to the hype! It’s located in the heart of Chicago. We ordered a few pizzas and drinks. A hostess greeted us at the entrance and showed us to our table. The waiter was friendly, and the food was served quickly. The restaurant has a stylish design and a great, spacious atmosphere. The pizza was delicious — we really enjoyed it. Highly recommend! Also, the music and conversations around us didn’t overpower each other, which is a rare and pleasant surprise in most restaurants.

We celebrated our anniversary this past weekend at Siena Tavern and had an outstanding experience. Our server, Bree, was attentive and friendly and made sure we knew about the best menu options and even surprised us with a special anniversary dessert! The atmosphere is cozy and intimate! It was the perfect choice for our special dinner. I had the rigatoni alla vodka and it was divine. We will definitely return soon!

Located close to all the beautiful spots downtown Chicago has to offer, Siena Tavern is a beautiful restaurant.  We sat in a very comfortable booth.  I actually got there 20 mins early and would you believe, I got seated right away.  It was still early before the dinner rush, so I got to enjoy my booth all by myself for just a bit. I was attended to by some very kind servers.  They took my appetizer order and I enjoyed the octopus appetizer before the rest of my group got there. It was just a beautiful tasty appetizer. The food is overall pretty good.  I had the lasagna and others ordered pizzas.  Unfortunately, the restaurant did get really noisy as it was brimming with activity.  Our group was having a hard time trying to have a conversation. But, it was a fun place.

Wow!  What an amazing experience!  I was dining solo, but ALL of the servers were extremely attentive and made it a great end to my “me time” in Chicago. Bri was incredible and her recommendation of the spaghetti dish was spot on!  Definitely a must try and this place is #1 on my list for a repeat visit next time I’m in Chicago.

formatted_address: 9415 W Higgins Rd, Rosemont, IL 60018, USA
name: Giordano's

reviews.text: I had a great experience at Giordano’s! The pizza was delicious—perfectly cheesy and full of flavor. The atmosphere was warm and inviting, making it a great spot to relax and enjoy a meal. Highly recommend for any pizza lover!
First time in Chicago and our first deep dish pizza experience. Hands down the best pizza we’ve ever had. The Greek salad was great as well. Service was superb. Cant wait to come back

Chicago Classic Deep Dish…recommend it!  Such flaky crust and unique layers of toppings. Sauce on top makes each bite get better as I chew. Attentive server, quick seating and boxed up to go once I was done. Thanks guys!  I’ll be back.

Deep dish was amazing! 5 stars
Thin crust was not hitting at all. -5 stars

If you're looking for good cheese pull, lots of robust sauce and tasty crust. Go with the deep dish.  Reminds me of a country biscuit.

If you're looking for cheap, cardboard pizza, go with the tavern style.

I could eat this all the time if only my stomach allowed it.  Delicious!

Last week was my first time eating at Giordano's. I can honestly say that the place does live up to its hype.

I asked this lady at the bar what the best pizza in Chicago would be. She listed off 3 popular Chicago chains, Giordano's being one of them.

Now being from Detroit, I know what good pizza is so I consider my standards to be somewhat high. And while Giordano's pizza wasn't the best I've ever had, it was pretty darn good. I got the deep dish meat pizza and it had terrific flavor. I didn't really care for the crust but it was still very good quality.

As far as the price, you are really getting what you pay for here, meaning the place is not cheap. But it is very good

Overall, Giordano's is a staple in the Chicago area. It's well worth the visit as the pizza is pricey, but filling and flavorful.

formatted_address: 539 N State St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Weber Grill Restaurant

reviews.text: I didn't know Weber Grill restaurants were a thing. It is on the corner of Ohio and state by the Embassy Suites hotel. I ordered the smoked turkey club with slaw on the side. The sandwich was one of the better turkey clubs I have had. The slaw was fresh made but average in taste.  Our waiter was very good and attentive with us and his other customers. I would definitely go back if in the area again.

Last Saturday I went to lunch with my brother at the Weber Grill Restaurant. They seated us right away at a table. The server was so polite and kept checking up on us. She made the dining experience wonderful. We ordered appetizers and they were really good! I ordered the Filet Mignon with garlic mashed potatoes, and OMG, I was in heaven. The steak was so delicious. We also had cocktails, and they were perfectly made. I left very happy. Everyone at Weber Grill is friendly, and I will definitely go back.

More than just bar fare, this place has a huge selection of comfort food, and I found an absolutely delicious French Onion Soup and perfectly grilled skewered beef.  Place is huge but we were accommodated quickly, and the service was surprisingly quick! I have to admit it's a bit touristy, but very very good overall experience if you're looking for wholesome food in big, satisfying servings!

Austin, was magnificent excellent service and very friendly..we decided to come to this steakhouse because of its value and thier menu.. we had the rib eye and it came with a side of mashed potatoes which other steakhouses make you pay for. My steak was cooked to my perfection, medium. I could literally cut it with my fork.. I would choose this place over the others

First time here and really impressed with the atmosphere and food. Their brisket  egg rolls were fantastic. The food is also top notch here. We ordered the Cedar Plank Salmon (delicious), grilled meatloaf (outstanding) and Rib eye steak (well grilled and delicious). Would definitely recommend.

formatted_address: 516 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Maggiano's Little Italy

reviews.text: To our surprise the chef came to greet us with a complimentary sample of one of their famous appetizers as it was our first ever visit to Maggiano’s. The food was delicious, presentation on point, our servers wine suggestions were a perfect pairing, and the staff was very friendly. We definitely recommend to anyone in the Chicago area to try this gem!!

Went for a dinner—spent around $45. Got the chicken parm, side of spaghetti, and split the tiramisu. Portions were huge—def worth it if you’re hungry or tryna share. Vibe is kinda old-school fancy but still comfy. Service was solid, but things moved a lil slow once it got busy. Not mind-blowing Italian, but it's consistent, filling, and hits that comfort food spot. I'd come back for sure.

I was invited here with a private party that was catered by Maggiano's Little Italy and it was the best Italian food I've had in a while. Their sauce is so good. I recommend anything with their sauce. The servers were very nice. The restaurant is clean and has a genuine Italian atmosphere.

Maggiano’s used to be our family’s go to place for celebrations. We would look forward to selecting from the many options available on the family style menu. For around $40/person, we’d choose two appetizers and four plated options. It also included Caesar and Maggiano’s salads, and about six different desserts. It was a feast and we loved it. Imagine our disappointment a few weeks ago when we went to celebrate my son’s college graduation, only to find out the family style menu now came with set appetizers, Caesar salad, two dinner options and two pre-selected pasta options, and tiramisu, cheesecake and cookies were the only desserts offered. On top of the limited choice, the price went up to $50/person. The food was still ok, but the pasta was way overcooked and way too soft. We were a party of seven but they squished us in a corner in such a small table that the server needed one side of the table to pass everything to the other side. We even had to stand up one time to let someone with a walker get by. The family style menu was so disappointing, we are now looking for a new place for future celebrations. On top of that, even though I mentioned we were celebrating a graduation, our server didn’t do anything special. My son was so disappointed. We were all disappointed with the meal, and frankly with our unfriendly server. We won’t be going back any time soon, and can no longer recommend this restaurant.

Our experience at this restaurant was absolutely wonderful!

First, I want to express my gratitude to the amazing server who took care of our table. I couldn’t quite remember his name, but after checking the receipt, I saw “Rigo” written on it—so I hope I got that right! He was incredibly kind and attentive, making our visit even more special.

We made our reservation two months ago and visited on March 11 to celebrate my daughter’s birthday. Since we had noted “birthday” as the occasion, the host had sprinkled colorful confetti all over our table before we arrived. That small but thoughtful touch made our entire family feel special even before we sat down!

The warm bread and olive oil served at the beginning were the perfect way to whet our appetites. After Rigo carefully explained the menu, we each ordered our preferred drinks and pasta dishes. The pasta was beautifully prepared, staying true to its classic flavors, and the extra chili peppers provided allowed me to adjust the spice level to my liking.

After we had thoroughly enjoyed our meal, Rigo surprised my daughter with a special birthday dessert. She was absolutely thrilled and couldn’t stop smiling!

From the friendly and thoughtful service by both the host and our server to the high-quality food and cozy atmosphere, everything about this dining experience was perfect. We truly appreciated every detail and will definitely be back again!

Highly recommend this place! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

formatted_address: 439 N Wells St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text:
I would definitely come back for happy hour (absolutely amazing deals), but never pay full prices again

You can get appetizers, drinks, and single serving deep dish pizzas for $5 from 3pm-5:30pm!

**more details about individual items**

We got The Lou pizza ($15, not happy hour) and the deep dish with sausage (thin layer of sausage instead of chunks! But little cheese) ($5, happy hour). The Lou has a buttery crust, while the deep dish does not—however, I honestly couldn’t tell a difference. Next time, I would probably just get the $5 happy hour deep dish.

Happy hour also includes appetizers ($5 each). We got the bruschetta and crispy ravioli. The bruschetta was a bit garlicky, but still super yummy! The crispy ravioli was unique and had a yummy sauce!

What we ordered:
- crispy ravioli ⭐️⭐️⭐️3/5
- Bruschetta ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️4/5
- Sausage deep dish pizza ⭐️⭐️⭐️3/5
- The Lou pizza ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️4/5

I’ll be honest, deep dish is not my first choice but Lou Malnati’s changed that. We ordered personal sized deep dish pizzas: the malnati, and the lou which I think were the perfect combination. The personal size does not feel overwhelming and has just the right dough to filling ratio. I would order this again!

The location is great, not too crowded vs. the mag mile location where it could go up to 2-3 hour wait times.

We’ve been to Lou Malnati’s before and always enjoy the food, but this time I tried their Hot Chicken Buffalo Deep Dish pizza for the first time. It had a great flavor and just the right amount of heat, though it was a bit oily. We also had the Mushroom Gluten-Free Thin Crust — it was simple and decent, but the crust turned out a little dry. The service was solid as always, and our waiter was polite and friendly. Still one of our go-to spots!

This place was properly hyped up on YouTube, it is good but not that great as it was shown by the influencers. The taste is okayish, but the pizza which we received was not hot. Even the garlic bread was cold. The cutlery was not clean as well. The only saving grace was that the staff was friendly and courteous but will I come back for this? Probably no.

We had “The Lou” based on multiple recommendations but it wasn’t that much great.

I was battling to decide what to rate this restaurant. The food wasn't bad and the staff were nice and accommodating however, the pizza we ordered made my friend sick. We are both vegetarian, her since she was a teenager, and me for just over a year so I am still able to handle meat etc. without getting ill, but she cannot. We ordered the vegetarian deep dish pizza they had and it tasted great but shortly after we left my friend started throwing up. We think there may have been some cross contamination where the vegetarian pizza came into contact with meat or something that had meat cooked in it. This is why I unfortunately have to give Lou's 3 stars. Also my friend ordered a vodka, soda, splash of cran and was charged $17 for that. Either we were charged wrongly or the alcohol prices were a bit outrageous. The restaurant did have a cozy vibe to it, and it definitely provided the Chicago deep dish experience, but for such a popular place I did expect more.

formatted_address: 626 N State St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Quartino Ristorante

reviews.text:
This was my first time visiting, and I completely fell in love with the place. I’ll definitely be back for more.

The food was outstanding—fresh, flavorful, and beautifully prepared. Every dish we tried was a solid 10/10. We especially loved the roasted asparagus, easily the best we have tasted, ever!.

Service was both quick and genuinely friendly, which made the experience even better. The drinks were strong but perfectly balanced—well-crafted and satisfying.

Overall, this has easily become my favorite Italian restaurant. Highly recommended!

I went here for my birthday party, and it was lovely!
The seating is slightly cramped, but we were able to fit our party of 7. The waiter was extremely friendly and helpful (Terra) and we also were able to get tons of free bread from another great waiter, Q.
We decided to share everything as this place is known for their small plates. I think it would have been better to share between less people as the portions are pretty small, but it was nice to be able to try a little bit of everything!
For appetizers, we got the clamari, veal meatballs (POLPETTE AL SUGO DI POMODORO), and the fonduta. I would highly recommend the fonduta- the cheese is delicious!
As our main, we got a half-pepperoni half-margharita pizza, both of which were very crispy and delicious. The margharita half was definetly on the cheesy side though! We also got gnocci, fettuccine alfredo, and penne alla vodka, all of which were great. The portions are on the smaller side, but enough to fill you up and have room for dessert!
The dessert was amazing- we got the tiramisu, hot chocolate cake with vanilla ice-cream (TORTA AL CIOCCOLATO), a gelato with bananas and biscotti (COPPA ALLA BANANA), and a gelato with strawberry sauce and a wafer (SPAGHETTI DI GELATO). They were all AMAZING and I would highly recommed the coppa alla banana!!
Overall, this place was wonderful. From the staff to the free bread to the dessert, we all had a great time! They even put a candle for my birthday! Also, prices are great and the food was so delicious.

This is an amazing and quite authentic Italian restaurant. I love that you can get most of the plates in half portions, which gives more flexibility to try more dishes without breaking the bank. Also, the food is literally the best I've had in a while. Highly recommend the goat ricotta.

I have to also mention the service is superb and fast!!! Skye was my waiter, and they were attentive, checked in at the right points, knowledgeable about the menu items, and just all-around pleasant!

If you're in the area, this is a must stop for great Italian dining for any occasion.

Had a lovely time at Quartino for my friends birthday. Restaurant was packed but the service remained consistent and speedy. Food was coming out just at right times and the taste was on point with each dish. Everything from starters to mains was exceptional. I will definitely be back!

Dining at Quartino was an absolute pleasure, and a huge part of that experience was thanks to our incredible server, Emily. From the moment we were seated, she made us feel genuinely welcome with her warm smile and gracious demeanor.

Emily was the perfect balance of professional and personable—attentive without hovering, knowledgeable without being overbearing. She guided us through the menu like a true expert, offering fantastic recommendations (the gnocchi was a game-changer!) and accommodating our dietary preferences with ease.

What really stood out was her attention to detail—she remembered every request, timed each course beautifully, and checked in just the right amount. Even on a busy night, Emily made us feel like we were her top priority.

If you’re lucky enough to have Emily as your server, you’re in for a top-tier experience. She elevates the entire meal with her charm, efficiency, and genuine care. We’ll definitely be back—and we’ll be asking for Emily!

formatted_address: 11 E Illinois St # 1, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Star of Siam

reviews.text: Had the tom yum soup, pad kee mao, spring rolls, and beef curry. Liked the atmosphere/service and price was good, but some of the dishes like the curry and spring rolls were a bit sweet for me. Good spot for a quick pad thai but a lot of other menus seemed like hit or miss.

Such a great experience to come and enjoy meals here. Actually I just looking for an asian restaurant with no pork in the menu, and I found this place. After Ied-Fitr Salah, we come and was surprised that there is a HALAL’s logo in front of the restaurant 🥹🥹 Since I feel a bit difficult to find a Halal restaurant, I am so happy to find this place.

A cozy-elegant and super clean place. I remember about the mirror beside our chosen-table, it was super duper clean, looks like no mirror anymore there.

About a meals, it was really delicious. We ordered this four meals:
• Mango Sticky Rice (my favorite!)
• Thai Tea Iced
• Beef Star Lover (Almond Beef)
• Chicken Noodle Soup

The portion actually too large for me, and I think I will take away the rest. But I love the taste of the Chicken Noodle Soup and make my bowl clean 👏🏻😄

Everything is good for us. Worth a repeat visit! 🥰
This place is an absolute gem! The massaman curry was delicious with multiple layers of flavors. Mango sticky rice never disappoints, and the edamame was as expected.

Avoid this place and believe the bad reviews. We went for an early dinner and ordered noodles and cashew chicken. I have lived in SEA, and I can confidently say this wasn’t even close to SEA cuisine. I wasn’t expecting authentic Thai, but the food was completely inedible. The chicken tasted stale, and the stir-fry came drenched in a soupy, awful-tasting sauce. Even the veggies tasted off. On top of it, they added a 15% gratuity to the bill and still asked for a tip. When we shared our feedback, the manager rudely gaslighted and dismissed us.

Food was herrible and bad. As a Thai person and thai food lover, this is not a real Thai food. I ordered chicken stir garlic, squid salad they were soooo SALTY LIKE Wth. And also ordered beef noodle which is shouldn’t put a pho noodles on this dish. The noodles soup tastes so bad like just a veggie soup, no any taste at all. Wouldn’t recommend. Very disappointed that i chose this restaurant as a only Thai restaurant i want to try for this vacation in Chicago

formatted_address: 805 S State St, Chicago, IL 60605, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text: This is the best pizza I have ever had! They delivered to our hotel and called us when they got close so we could meet them to get it. They ensured we had plates, silverware, napkins, and toppings (cheese & crushed peppers). The pizza was cooked perfectly, and the cheese pull was unmatched! We got the pepperoni deep dish and highly recommend it. The pepperoni is fresh and seasoned well, and the sauce is gorgeous. If you are in Chicago, you HAVE to give it a try!

Yesterday, I decided to check out Lou Malnati's after coming from the library and I'm glad I came! It didn't take long to get a table and the young ladies who greeted me were nice. I was glad to get a booth so I could do some journaling as I ate. My server was Katie and she was sweet and attentive! I got the personal pizza and I admit, I was shocked because I was expecting it to be a little larger and it was deep dish (I'm not a fan of deep dish and had though about getting a thin crust; I should've asked if the personal pizzas were thin crust). I decided to give it a try and it was delicious! The tomatoes tasted fresh and the sausage was tasty. The crust was crispy and buttery and the root beer that I had was great, too. I had a peaceful experience and it was nice to see others with their families and friends. Thank you for the great service! I will be back.

This was my first time trying deep dish pizza and obviously I picked this top rated restaurant for it.

I did not make a reservation because I didn’t know which part of the town I will be in around dinner time so I did walk in. It was a little over an hour wait till I got a table. Good thing is, they have some benches so that made the wait time tolerable. They ask you to order your pizza while you are waiting so you don’t have to wait for your pizza for too long after you are seated which is a good thing.

I had the calamari as starters and it was really tasty. The seafood sauce was really good. For deep dish, I ordered the vegetarian one and the sausage one. Frankly speaking I didn’t like either. The vegetarian one specially had so much tomato that it because extremely soggy. It was way too tangy and not enough cheese.

Service was alright. Servers were really busy so they did the best they could.

The energy at the restaurant was really great though. Lots of people, enjoying food with their friend and family, conversations and laughter. It felt nice.

I had a difficult time writing a review for this place. I came here because my doctor from back home in Colorado recommended it, and I was eager to try it out. There were six of us in my party, and as you might expect, we all had different opinions about our experience.

Personally, I enjoyed the flavors of the Lou Malnati’s special with added pepperoni. The cheese was perfectly balanced, just the way I like it. However, not everyone shared my enthusiasm. Some in our group felt that there wasn't enough cheese, while others thought the sausage lacked flavor. One person even remarked that the crust was too hard. Interestingly, I found the very elements they complained about to be enjoyable.

On the downside, the service was unfortunately slow. We had to constantly ask for water refills, which was a bit frustrating.

Overall, it seems like there's something for everyone here. While I thoroughly enjoyed my meal, opinions varied widely among my friends. It’s all subjective, and you might find that you enjoy it just as much as I did!

Beautiful atmosphere and very good service. We tried their famous deep dish pizza and we are honestly not a big fan. You can have a slice. Go for smaller one as the portion is big. Tiramisu was good and we also tried the fritter cheese platter, very good!

formatted_address: 2900 W Belmont Ave, Chicago, IL 60618, USA
name: Kuma's Corner

reviews.text:
Amazing burgers! Really loved everything I ate here, my only gripe is that the chips weren’t salted but given how great everything else was I wasn’t upset by it. Personally the cherry cola tasted odd to me (kinda like cherry flavored medicine) but it was alright. I didn’t try the caramel nut fudge but my friend said it was amazing as well and she really enjoyed the vanilla ice cream.
Overall would definitely come here again.
Good food, burgers were delicious, although quite pricey but good portion sizes. Good service and fast. Love the heavy metal/rock band theme. Recommended! Good drinks!

Got the Iron Maiden burger. Asked for medium, burger was overcooked on some spots and undercooked on others. The burger did taste very good despite being cooked wrong. The fries were truly awful, soggy cold and tasteless. Service was spotty even though it wasn't busy at all. The pretzel bun for the burger was served cold. What's up with that? Would have been much better toasted. The Cesar salad was decent, nothing great. I'm shocked that a place that features burgers has such terrible French fries. Overall I felt underwhelmed by Kuma's. My advice would be get a burger and a beer, no side dishes, fries, etc;
I give this business a moderate recommendation

Killer burgers, heavy music, and a badass vibe. Evergreen took great care of us, and they even hooked up our good boy with his own burger! The Plague Bringer was a spicy, garlicky masterpiece. If you love metal and top-tier food, this is the spot.

Fun place with loud metal music and  interesting burgers.  Fries were not great.  Service was excellent.   Had the morgue burger, it was very tasty and the pretZel bun held up, but could have been warmed or toasted since it was clearly refrigerated.

An interesting place to check out or take someone from out of town for a unique experience.

formatted_address: Lower 430 North, Michigan Ave, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Billy Goat Tavern (The Original)

reviews.text:
Doesn’t look like much but service is quick and friendly. Basic menu with affordable pricing considering location. Worth a stop for a dated nostalgic feel of an older restaurant with nothing fancy.
Got a triple burger with chips and a soda. Affordable and tastes good.
Worth stopping in for a quick bite to eat

First time in Chicago and trying this place. Was surprised how a simple burger tasted this good. Service was quick and efficient and food came out quickly. There is a DIY condiment bar that you can add your own ketchup, mustard, mayo and relish, pickles, onion. I got a cheeseburger and also shared the ham one and it was surprisingly good. The place eas super busy,  we were lucky to grab a table of 6 late at night on a sunday.

I had a craving for a burger so we looked at the google reviews and decided to try this place. It’s a dive bar, nothing fancy about it and I’m good with that. There were three of us and we ordered 4 double cheeseburgers. I swear before I pulled out my credit card two burgers were already on the counter, they make these burgers so fast, it’s amazing. They were perfectly done. There are no plates, they slap the burger on some wax paper on the counter and that’s it. The cheeseburger doesn’t have anything on it. There is a condiment station where you add what ever you want, they had pickles, relish, onions, mustard and ketchup. You sit at any table you want.

We paid $54.00 including a 20% tip for 4 double cheeseburgers and 3 fountain cokes. No complaints about this place, I’ll be back for a quick burger

Great experience at the Original Billy Goat Tavern.

Located on Hubbard Street beneath the underpass between North Rush street and Michigan avenue.

Great space with lots of tables and chairs as well as some bar seating in the bar area. Food ordered and picked up in the center station. There is a small condiment counter (onions, pickles, relish...) off to the side if needed.

The bar area has a variety of drink options, including beer and hard liquor.

Reasonably prices and the food was really good.

A few garages as well as metered street parking in the surrounding area.

I visited the location near the United Center last year, but this time my hotel was on Michigan, so I was very close to the original location under Michigan Avenue. This is the location you need to visit.

Get a borger, sit at the bar, and order an Old Style. Talk to the bartender and talk to the other customers sitting at the bar. You will have a great time.

Yes, it's kid friendly, and it's not expensive, especially considering it's location.

It's a friendly dive bar with solid basic food. I visited this location every day I was in Chicago.

formatted_address: 1120 S Michigan Ave, Chicago, IL 60605, USA
name: Yolk - South Loop

reviews.text: Excellent food, great service, and relaxing atmosphere! We came with two kids (elementary and middle school) and two adults and ordered a range of foods, from pancakes, to omelettes, and everything was excellent! They took the youngest's order first and made sure to get the food out fast, which they did, and they really loved the "s'mores" pancakes! The egg dishes were very tasty and perfectly cooked, including the side of poached eggs (all good signs that they really have the fundamentals in the kitchen working well)! Will absolutely visit again!

After seeing Yolk being highly recommended on Reddit, we visited on a Friday morning and had about a 15-minute wait, which wasn’t too bad considering that they were completely full. The staff was running around like crazy, trying to keep up with the demand, but they handled it pretty well.

Though it took a while, granted they were packed, the food was worth the wait. The cinnamon roll was absolutely massive. We also tried a cortado, a latte, an omelet, pancakes, and the chicken and waffles. Everything was tasty. The omelet was fluffy and was LOADED with the veggies and meat I added to it. The chicken and waffles hit the spot. The pancakes were good, but a bit on the thin and dry side.

One thing to note, though—the place was really loud. It felt like the noise from the crowd bounced around a lot. Adding some sound-absorbing features would probably help a lot. Overall, a good breakfast experience, just be prepared for a possible lively (and loud) morning.

Probably one of the worst places to have breakfast. Their fancied pancakes was nothing but a lump of flour. Over easy eggs that I ordered was nothing up to the mark. The eggs didn’t look fresh; probably been sitting there for ages or some low quality commercial grade ones. Same about the sausages too. Hash browns left a bitter oil taste in the mouth. Appears they have been reusing the oil for days. Am not gonna walk into Yolk again ever. I would rather die of hunger! Portions are generous though..

The California omelette was delicious! Pro tip: add cheese grits and a side of French toast for a sweet ending! The restaurant was clean and the cappuccino was YUM!  Recommend Marco T. For great service!
It was an overall decent experience. The food was good, but did take a while to get our order. The cups are small (shown in picture). The French toast was good: the berries were good.

formatted_address: 150 N Dearborn St, Chicago, IL 60601, USA
name: Petterinos

reviews.text: The seafood is fresh. The seasoning is delicate. The service is excellent and the selection is authentic. The Calamari is crispy with a delicious sauce. The burrata is rich and creamy. We also had the toasted ravioli. I've been on a separate occasion and the meatballs are  tender and well seasoned. I definitely recommend.

We got the meatballs, the seafood pasta, steak frittes, tiramisu and the brownie. Everything tasted great. Will say though the meatballs were kind of cold in the center and weren’t my favorite. The seafood pasta and the steak though were great. We loved the desserts too!

I’ve passed this place so many times but never gave it a shot. It was decent for a quick lunch with friends. We went for restaurant week so $30 for 3 courses was perfect. The baked ricotta was outstanding but the texture of the chicken meatballs was really odd. The branzino was delicious, fresh and the skin was crispy. The gnocchi had mixed reviews from our group. If you enjoy mushrooms and other earthy flavors, its good but still could use more seasoning and flavor. But if not, you’ll probably not enjoy this. The peach panna cotta was wonderful and not too sweet

Beautiful cozy warm and attentive and friendly staff. Indoor and outdoor seating. Nice interior and comfortable booths. The pasta (4 cheese ravioli) was good… a bit salty but tasty. Wait staff were wonderful. Fun place for drinks and dinner right before a show (it’s directly adjacent to the Goodman theater) as well as just a big party of fun people eating and drinking. The place is huge and it sits on a corner of the street. Street parking w meters are not really there so only mostly garage parking (you can use Spot Hero to get a discounted spot) or use CTA trains and buses.

BEST FOOD EVER HIGHLY RECOMMEND !!! prior to acquiring such a feastable meal, i was having a nice but mid time. I needed something to uplift me! then, suddenly, i saw this cute corner italian restaurant and thought the atmosphere was quite elegant and aesthetic! I stepped inside, ordered, and quickly got my food. IT WAS DELISH! highly recommend the fettuccine with mushrooms. 10/10. the flavors were immaculate i almost cried from joyousness. Guys this is where the heat is at!

formatted_address: 60 E Grand Ave, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Joe's Seafood, Prime Steak & Stone Crab

reviews.text: One of Chicagos best.  Haven’t been back in 10 years and they somehow knew I had been a regular at one point!. Crazy busy on a Saturday night to include numerous celebrities! The steaks are awesome and they now have delicious Stone Crab claws year round!

I had dinner here with my boyfriend and it was the best service I’ve ever had in my life. Our waiter (I can’t remember his name unfortunately) was amazing. He was kind, attentive, polite, professional, and all around went above and beyond for us. Hot towels served between courses, great wine recommendations AND was on top of keeping our glasses full, always keeping the table clean, amongst other things. The food is incredibly fresh. Flavorful and tastes like it was just pulled from the ocean. I loved my experience and we will absolutely be back!

One of our family favorites for a steak dinner and usually a celebration. This time was High School graduation!

Always happy with the service. Bob was helpful and thoughtful.

The food was delicious as usual. We started with the stone crabs for appetizer. Yum, a family favorite. The steaks were tender and flavorful. I had miso glazed chilean sea bass, perfectly cooked.

Key lime pie for dessert is our family favorite.

Thank you Joe's!

The dishes are packed with flavor, and the authentic taste of seafood really shines through, with a perfect balance of garlicky and lemony notes. I really enjoyed the Grilled Seafood Platter, but the Crab Stuffed Shrimp was definitely my favorite. I also tried the hashed brown potatoes, but didn’t enjoy them much, and the French fries were just okay. The complimentary fresh bread and butter at the start were a nice touch. This was my first time trying lobster and scallops, and I loved them! Highly recommend this place for seafood lovers.

Superb dining experience. Great service, attentive, friendly and knowledgeable. Everything we had was excellent. Started with crab claws and calamari, both great. We had the aged bone in ribeye, sockeye salmon and crab stuffed prawns. All superb, steak in particular was memorable. Best side of Mac and cheese ever. Nice touch at the end with a complimentary  key lime pie for first time diners. Great wine menu and cocktail. Memomable dinner

formatted_address: 1200 W Randolph St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: City Winery Chicago

reviews.text: I love coming here for dinner, concerts etc But last night they hosted the American Airlines James Bond theme Bordeaux Wine Dinner Series and it was spectacular. the wines were outstanding and foods paired perfectly! You gotta go here for good wine and vibes! They host so many events too!

The greeters were very nice and bubbly, and being escorted to our seats was a nice experience. The wings, French fries, and meatballs were good but were slightly overpriced. The service was quick, but the waiters didn't know who ordered what, so they interrupted patrons who were watching the show to ask them if they ordered the food they carried by the tables. The drinks were pretty good. The seating is HORRIBLE because we were too close to each other because the tables were very small, and we felt like we were packed into a table with other strangers like sardines. I didn't like being forced to pay for food after purchasing tickets. Also, my waitress NEVER checked on us after she took our order, so I DID NOT LEAVE HER A TIP, but why did I get charged for a $18 tip for a $90 bill. My bank resolved this, but I gave CITY WINERY an opportunity to address this first, and they didn't apologize or give me an explanation. The stage and sound quality were AMAZING, but the tightly crowded seating arrangements were horrible and made us feel very uncomfortable! The DISHONEST waitress who stole an UNDESERVED TIP and the packed-like-sardines seating arrangements are the reasons why my brother and I WON'T BE EVER RETURNING TO CHICAGO CITY WINERY! Save your money and go to a local bar with good food, space, and good service! This place is OVERRATED!🙄🙄🙄

I really like attending concerts at City Winery. I can usually purchase tickets in my preferred seating area. I enjoy the coziness and intimacy of the venue. The music always sounds amazing. I have enjoyed most of the food and drink items I have purchased at the venue. My only complaint is the way the food and drinks are served, there are servers walking through the aisles throughout the duration of the performance. In addition, I have had to wait 10-15 minutes after the performance for my bill. I don’t have a solution how to resolve this issue; but, the way the food and drinks are being served definitely needs to be revamped.

I visited City Winery Chicago for the first time yesterday. I knew Calvin Rodgers and the Jazz Quintet were going to be awesome but I have to say the entire experience was awesome too! The food (I had a Kale Salad with steak and my friend ordered the truffle fries) was AMAZING and the atmosphere was too. I cannot wait to return. The sound was great and I loved the intimate atmosphere. Great venue and great job overall!

What a great place for an intimate concert!! Don’t think there was a bad spot in the place!
The food was decent- we ate at our venue table (very small 4 person table!) The food was good- we had the Caesar salad with chicken skewers and the kale salad with hanger steak.
In my opinion, they were slightly understaffed and because of how the seating is laid out, it’s a little difficult for the staff to stand on top of everyone. Not bad service just not pinky out Service, which is fine for me.
The acoustics were great. I will definitely come back for more shows.
Cannot personally attest to their wine, but there was lots of it flowing so it must’ve been good.
The picture was taken near the back of the venue.

formatted_address: 223 W Jackson Blvd, Chicago, IL 60606, USA
name: Giordano's

reviews.text:
To truly experience the Classic Chicago Experience, you have to have the best of the deep dish pizza. Giordano's is the best of the best and it never disappoints.

Our first stop after we checked in at the hotel just a short walk away. Surprisingly, we got seated right away. Our server, was upbeat, warm and welcoming- i wished I remember her name. She happily informed us that it will take at least 45 minutes for the pizza. We ordered a small Chicago Classic. To start, the starter salad was excellent, Chopped Salad and  Caesar Salad was fresh. The Chicken Wings is the best I've had ever. Paired well with the draft beer.

But the star of the show is the Chicago Classic. The sauce was fresh and tangy flavor really stood out. Its perfectly balanced not too thick and let the ingredients shine. The cheese pull is impressive, great photo op. Every bite was rich, savory experience.

Amazing food, excellent customer service and definitely made our experience a delightful one.

Giordano’s the Chicago classic was delicious. As my first time eating real Chicago deep dish I was very pleased. The atmosphere was good and laid back. We had the Chicago classic deep dish and it was amazing, the Caeser salad was very good as well. Our server was good but the restaurant seemed to be a little understaffed. Overall the experience and food were good.

We almost didn't want to try a deep dish pizza while we were Chicago but we caved. It was amazing! It doesn't take like your normal pizza and the serving or portion size for a 10 inch is huge. We were glad we tried it.

Came here for an early dinner as I was staying at a hotel next door. Been to other locations, but first time at this location.  Food and experience is identical to the other ones.  Good food and service.

I just missed the lunch hours, so was unable to order the personal deep dish that's only on the lunch menu.  This was a good thing as forced me to order something else. Ordered the Mama's Meatball Sub.  Came out in about 15 minutes and looked great.  It was 3 giant meatballs smothered in mozzarella.  The marinara seemed to be the same sauce from the pizzas so tasted great. Overall a good choice to get the same pizza flavors in a sandwich.

I had an amazing experience at Giordano’s, and a big part of that was thanks to Naomi. From the moment we sat down, she was friendly, attentive, and made us feel right at home. She knew the menu inside and out, gave great recommendations, and made sure everything came out just right. It’s clear she takes pride in what she does—and it shows. If you’re visiting Giordano’s, ask for Naomi. She truly takes the dining experience to another level!

formatted_address: 24 S Michigan Ave, Chicago, IL 60603, USA
name: The Gage

reviews.text:
We were able to grab a seat at the bar. Reservations are recommended. This is one of the few good spots to eat in a tourist area. Bartender was great. He was super busy but was very attentive to us. My date got the chicken fried lobster, a fancy version of the fish and chips. 3 lobster tails fried (Chicken fried steak batter) with some fries and jalapenos. It was very good but heavier of looking for something lighter. I got the diver scallops. Fun and refreshing and light meal. The sauce went very well with the lobster. We ended with a double espresso and a dodgy Sunday! Then went for a long walk down Michigan ave!!

Definitely go back once in the area again. Great Job, The Gage!

I came here after visiting Navy Pier and the other Chicago lakefront parks. The hostess was welcoming but there wasn't any outside dining available. There were open seats when we arrived, but they must have been reserved. The food was great, my daughters and I enjoyed everything that came to our table.  Service was a bit spotty. There was also a tall, middle aged blond man that did nothing but stand in the dining area, staring, and taking notes. He added a weird vibe to the restaurant. The Gage is inviting but very dark inside. This restaurant seemed overstaffed, more employees than customers.  Burgers, steak, salads, seafood, and a great bar with a bunch of unique drink and cocktail recipes.  The wait staff was cautious and thorough when asking about food allergies. This restaurant deep fries a lot of lobsters, so the other fried foods have a risk of cross contamination.  They do a great job of asking customers about their allergies.

My number one brunch spot in Chicago!
Right in front of the crown fountain.
On mother’s day weekend We walked in  around 12:30 pm and were immediately seated on the patio, surrounded by beautiful purple tulips, it was the perfect setting. The food was absolutely amazing, and the coffee was unlimited, rich and flavorful. Our server, Jake, was incredibly helpful and made the experience even better. Don’t miss the crème brûlée
it was perfectly done and full of flavor. I’ll definitely be coming back. A must-visit spot for brunch lovers!
Thank you Jake

The Gage is an absolute gem in the heart of Chicago. From the moment you walk in, the atmosphere strikes the perfect balance between upscale and inviting, ideal for anything from a casual night out to a special occasion.

I have to highlight the fish and chips, easily some of the best I’ve had anywhere. Perfectly crisp batter, flaky fish, and house made tartar sauce that ties it all together. It’s classic comfort food done with real attention to detail.

The service is consistently attentive without being overbearing, and the drink selection is top-notch, featuring a thoughtful list of craft beers and cocktails. Whether you’re a local or just visiting, The Gage should definitely be on your list.

I love this spot. The restaurant was aesthetically pleasing. They had different colored tiles and bricks and cool floor designs. We sat at the bar and were served by two very nice bartenders. It happened to be restaurant week so we got to try a lot. I had a great espresso martini and my husband got an Irish cream hot chocolate, both were excellent. The first dish was a pub scotch egg and I’ve never had one but it was very yummy. I was honestly pretty satisfied with just that but my second course was the steak frites and it was a very decent piece of meat on top of good fries. Tasted like there was some vinegar, garlic seasoning but I could be off. Got the chocolate mousse for dessert and it was very good. My husband got the lobster roll and it was up to his standards as he often complains they aren’t fully enough of lobster but not this one. I’d absolutely come back, great spot in Chi-town.

formatted_address: 100 Drury Ln, Oakbrook Terrace, IL 60181, USA
name: Drury Lane Theatre & Events

reviews.text:
Excellent infrastructure and Decor.
The event was well-planned.
The sound system was a bit too loud.
Seating arrangement didn't allow complete view due to plant decoration.
Children activity was well planned.
Food was awesome.

A very pleasurable first experience at Drury Lane the Saturday after Christmas to see the fantastic performance of The Little Mermaid. The show was excellent!! It’s a lovely theatre and venue overall with a park garage to the side. It was easy getting out after the show but I could see it being problematic if more than one event was going on at the same time. The chandeliers in this place are beautiful and the holiday decor was so warm and festive. It is a very family friendly venue! I would go back for a show in the future. We had front row seats for the performance- even though the speaker was in front of us, literally, it was still very enjoyable and not overly loud. I can’t say enough about the Little Mermaid! Great cast, puppeteers and music/scenery.

As a photographer who had the privilege of capturing the magic of Drury Lane Theatre.The theater's stunning architecture and state-of-the-art equipment provided the perfect backdrop for my work. The space is exceptional for weddings, especially for large ones. We highly recommend it to anyone considering a wedding there. You can see this for yourself in our photos.

Very nice place to go and see a play.
The parking can be a challenge if there are multiple events going on at the same time.
The facility is clean and very well maintained.
The lighting, sound system, and acoustics are very good.
Unfortunately, the seats are not comfortable at all.
Seats are way too close together and are way too small, designed for a child.
I truly love most of the theater production line up they bring to the stage, It's always top-notch.
The Sunday brunch is very good, with an extensive variety of food.
It's definitely worth checking it out at least once.

The best shows ever! Phenomenal talent in one place. Skilled singers, dancers, actors, musicians, the list goes on. The amount of creativity here is fairy tale and wonder. You get so into these shows you forget you are sitting in a chair with a few other hundred people. You also leave with a bunch of songs in your head. The little mermaid for me this New Years Eve. Prices avg 75$ to 125$ per ticket. You get a pretty good view from just about anywhere in the theater. The building is gorgeous. Most people dress formal. You have a doorman that makes the experience enriching and a fine dining restaurant. This can be a great experience for couples. Must do type of outing.

formatted_address: 100 W Ontario St, Chicago, IL 60610, USA
name: Portillo's & Barnelli's Chicago

reviews.text:
First time visiting here and came here after reading the food review and recommendation. The restaurant is very beautiful and nicely decorated. Everything is self-service. You order the food from one of the machine and then collect them at the collection counter. Take the serviette, tomato sauce at the station and find your own seats to enjoy your meal. There are plentiful of seats in the restaurant.

I tried their Portillo’s beef hotdog and they are really good, the fries are thick cut, freshly fried and crunchy. Will come again if I ever come back to Chicago!

This place gets five stars. I ordered the number 2 which was the hot dogs Chicago style!! The line was fast and the prices affordable. Skip the touch screen menu and walk behind them to order from the cashier.

4/18/25- pretty good hot dogs. i’m assuming they’re popular as a Chicago staple. I’m not much of a hot dog connoisseur, but they seemed like nice, but regular hot dogs. They didn’t have any special seasonings to the meat, but the toppings of the original dog were something new to me with the pickle and other ingredients. I also tried the chili dog which was nice with the onions, but again nothing to out of the ordinary. the onion rings were perfectly fried and crispy, little flavor. There are combo specials but I opted a la carte and for 1 regular dog, 1 jumbo dog, and a small onion ring it was 17 dollars. oh they don’t come in boxes so the chili cheese dog was a little messy but not terrible. i went around 3p on a Friday and the wait for food was about 8 minutes.
There was a lot of seating on both the first and second level as well as outside seating. The atmosphere and decor was also great with a mix of historical elements and neon lights.
I walked so I couldn’t comment on parking. but it’s a very short walk, like 5 or so blocks, from the river.  I would definitely recommend for visitors.

First time trying the famous dogs and beef sandwiches. Not bad overall. The hot dog was well worth it, with all the toppings and is reasonably priced. The beef sandwiches was a bit smaller than expected but they do load that thing up. I got it as is without any modifications and it was a bit dry, so recommend adding in peppers and sauce which I’m sure would make it better. Service was quick, plenty of seating as well.

Nice retro setting. I don't eat beef so came here to try the Veg Hot dog (Chicago style) after reading on Maps and reddit about it. Well it was good! Don't have the best benchmarks to compare it to but the hot dog was juicy and well portioned while keeping all the toppings. For kicks I got the hot pepper side (which was deliciously lightly oiled - which I enjoyed)

Def worth the try :)

formatted_address: 622 N Fairbanks Ct, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Timothy O'Toole's Pub Chicago

reviews.text: I was so happy to find this place after walking around downtown for almost an hour. Most restaurants' kitchen closes at 10 pm but open until midnight for drinks. However, at this place the kitchen is open till 2am. I appreciated the choices from a full menu. I did walk right past at first, thinking it was closed, but the restaurant is downstairs.

We were in the mood for some fish and chips while watching the Texas Rangers game in Chicago. We had to show our IDs before entering the pub, which is no big deal. The pub has plenty of TVs showing all sorts of sporting events. The wife ordered a cocktail and we had the spinach artichoke dip for an appetizer. Both the dip and the chips needed more salt. For dinner, the wife ordered chicken mac and cheese, and I had the fish and chips. The wife enjoyed her mac and cheese, but I've had better fish and chips. I am not saying it was bad at all, just that I've had better at other places. The service was hit and miss. The waiter was quick with water and soda and the food came out quickly, but we had to get the waiter's attention to get refills on the water and soda multiple times. We enjoyed watching the game as we ate and the crowd was lively.

stopped in for supper on a sunday night and could not be more glad we did!!! service, food, and vibes were out of this world.
our server was super friendly and attentive, we couldn't have possibly asked for better!! gave great recommendations and good conversation :)
the food was absolutely delicious, and the portion sizes were huge!! the local pretzel trio alone is worth the visit. they were SO crispy and all three dips were so good. the wings are famous, understandably so. insanely crispy and literally the best sauces i've ever had. and the birria grilled cheese was amazing and flavorful.
def will be back for more.
the atmosphere was super chill and they played great music!
thanks so much!

I came in because I wanted food late at night and their kitchen was open. The food was decent, although I think the pretzel I ordered had mold on it? I show it in my last photo. I didnt complain because I wasnt sure, but out of all of the pretzel bits only one spot had this dark spot on the inside that to me could only have been mold. Im not sure why else there'd have been one dark spot like that. But it had been fried ir something after being cut into bits so it wasnt super obvious what that was. The Shepards pie was good. If you order the pretzel bits, be careful the cheese sauce is hot haha. I didnt realize and burned my tongue expecting cold cheese sauce. The staff were great, super busy but the bartenders made sure to check on me frequently.

Our group had a great time here, it was fast service with a very attentive server. The drinks were really nice, we went with beer of the month, guava mule, classic old fashioned with a side of fries. Really great vibes with the music. They have ample seating space and are open till late. Totally come here to have a good time.

formatted_address: 2548 N Halsted St, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: Kingston Mines

reviews.text: Kingston Mines is one of my favorite spots in Chicago. It’s a must-visit every time I’m in town for business. I love the live music, the energy, and the overall vibe. It’s changed a bit over the years, but it still holds that charm that keeps me coming back. It’s a must for any blues lover. The talent they bring in never disappoints. Still absolutely worth a visit.

We went here to celebrate our anniversary, joined by our kids. We absolutely loved it. The music was really good and the atmosphere was fun. The food was a ho-hum, but it did the trick. The service and drinks were great, especially the ginger beer and warm apple cider.
From the outside, I always thought it would be a bit rough. But it turned out to be wonderful inside. Kingston has a great honky-tonk vibe with some really good blues. If you've never gone, be sure to give it a try. Everybody in our group loved it.

Kingston Mines is a great spot! I recently went to celebrate a birthday and had an awesome time.  The music was great and from the moment I arrived , it didn't stop!

I did not try any food but the service was quick and friendly when it came to getting drinks.  Drink prices weren't cheap but not too bad.  Bottles of beer were 8 bucks and cocktails a bit more.  Cover charge is 20 but thats not a bad value for live music from 7pm to 3am!    Preformers were charismatic and seemed happy to be there.

This is a spot for adults of all ages. Outstanding experience.  I look forward to coming back.

First time here (ikr?!) Saw Toronzo Canon & chatted with him a bit before the show. Amazing guy, awesome band. The atmosphere is energized and people are positive/ friendly. If you’ve never been, it’s a whole azz vibe. Check it out. 20$ cover bc nice things cost money
What an amazing experience. People are nice and approachable like before cellphones exist. Good bands rotating all night. Amazing bar staff. Wings are a must. Go all-in

formatted_address: 52 W Illinois St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: RPM Italian

reviews.text: Despite being seated 20 mins after our reservation and being walked to our table to be taken back to the waiting area I thought it was going to be questionable service but… the service from our waitress was great! Abigail was really professional and sweet. They had personalized menus for our anniversary and also complimentary dessert! The pasta was delicious. Smaller portion of the Wagyu than I thought but it was cooked to perfection, I just wish it had more salt. 4 stars for the beginning experience.

While visiting Chicago we we're continuously being told that we had to try RPM Italian and I'm glad we did! Everything was delicious. Shane was phenomenal and had the best recommendations! He definitely elevated the experience. Thank you to Shane and RPM Italian for a delicious dinning experience!

Generally disappointed. Heard great things but the food was just okay. Wouldn’t come back considering the price. Broccolini was just average, pasta was undercooked. Crudo tasted good. Arancini was forgettable. Seemed hip and trendy. Lighting was decent. Didn’t see our waiter often. He was also rough with the silverware.

Amazing food. Amazing.  I had eggplant Parmesan and it was so good.  We also had the steak tartar-fanfreakingtastic and bill's something chocolate thing for dessert.  I had some giggles and spritz to drink and it was...gigglin and spritzin.

The bathroom was lovely and they juat kept bringing forks!  No reusing forks betweek courses, my 4 year old self was very pleased.

Great Italian food! Absolutely loved the garlic bread and meatballs for an appetizer. I had the rigatoni for my main and really enjoyed it. My friend also enjoyed her pepperoni pizza. The atmosphere was really intimate and everyone was friendly. Definitely recommend.

formatted_address: 21 E Hubbard St, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Shaw's Crab House

reviews.text: I enjoyed my food thoroughly. I had the buffalo shrimp and the seafood combo with shrimp, scallops, and a crab cake. All were delicious. You have to like seafood to enjoy. I feel like those who just like simple crab boils, this is not the place for you. The best part of my experience was the service! They were very attentive and polite!

An exceptional dining experience at Shaw’s Crab House in Chicago. From the moment we arrived, we were met with warm, attentive service — Crist provided impeccable hospitality with grace and professionalism. I had the seafood fettuccine, which was perfectly cooked and bursting with flavor, followed by a delicious dessert that beautifully ended the meal. The ambiance, cuisine, and service were all of the highest caliber. A truly memorable evening; I look forward to returning.

Always a treat!

Food: Amazing!! The steak was cooked perfectly.

Service: amazing everything was on point never needed to ask for water refills or napkins or a bowl for shells. They were all on top of everything.

Shout out to Franky!

Definitely going again.

The food was delicious, and the service was excellent, just as I expected. We ordered the seafood tower, which provided plenty of food for two people. Although the oysters were a bit smaller than I had anticipated, the clam chowder was delicious. The lobster bisque, however, was a bit runny. The garden salad was fresh and tasty. Overall, I would recommend this restaurant and would definitely return in the future.

Great seafood and Blues in the loop. The 40th anniversary special had some great specials. Frog legs, crab stuffed shrimp and Seafood Pasta were all winners.  We split the pasta dish it was so big. Pics show 1/2 order.

formatted_address: 3008 Finley Rd, Downers Grove, IL 60515, USA
name: Chama Gaúcha Brazilian Steakhouse - Chicago

reviews.text: Absolutely loved my experience at Chama Gaúcha! The service was great everyone was friendly and the restaurant was super clean well run and organized. Went for my birthday dinner and my Boyfriend Asked them to sing to me and The waiters did which was very kind. As long as you have your card flipped to green the food keeps coming which is awesome! Very delicious and flavorful meat. We will definitely be going back again soon! Remember to go starving and enjoy it to the max! 🔥

This was an amazing experience!
When we arrived to our table, they pull the chairs out, push them in, each table has their own coat rack and the service was Beautiful! Shoutout to Jorge for making us feel so welcome!
The food was SPECTACULAR and Authentic! The music could’ve been better but the overall experience was AMAZING!
The price is well worth the experience as well.

Decent place. Food was good. Felt very rushed, service was awful. Atmosphere has gotten very tacky. You can tell their model was to upsell and turn table quick. Gratuity charge was included. I would’ve liked to give more than what was included as gratuity if my service was merited. I’m not coming back.

Chama is the best Brazilian steakhouse I’ve ever been to. From the moment I stepped inside, I was impressed by the exceptional quality of the food. The cuts of steak are perfectly cooked, and the salad bar offers a wide variety of fresh ingredients. The service is attentive and knowledgeable, and the staff is friendly and welcoming. Overall, Chama is a fantastic dining experience that I highly recommend.

It's always a great experience at Chama Gaucha! We celebrated our sister's birthday and enjoyed everything. Our server Alexis was wonderful and had some terrific recommendations. 10/10
We'll be back soon!

formatted_address: 130 E Randolph St, Chicago, IL 60601, USA
name: Wildberry Pancakes & Cafe

reviews.text: This place was amazing and so well priced! We arrived on a Sunday and even though it looked as if the wait would be ridiculously long, we were sat within 10 minutes. The outside area was nice and shaded so we sat outside. The cinnamon roll pancakes and brisket grilled cheese were AMAZING 😮‍💨 would for sure recommend and go back again.

Breakfast & brunch? This is the place. Generously sized, fluffy pancakes. The omelet was so filling & the portion size so big I couldn't finish it all. Delicious!

It's popular. So you can have up to a 20 minute wait for a group but worth it. I was solo so I waited only for 5 minutes. Reasonable prices.

Highly recommend!

This is hands down one of the best brunch spots around! The veggie burger was flavorful and satisfying, while the blueberry crepe was absolutely delicious—sweet, fresh, and perfectly made. The service is impressively fast despite the bustling atmosphere, but be sure to check the waitlist before heading over, as it can get busy during peak times. The cozy yet vibrant vibe makes it a great place to enjoy a relaxed meal with friends or family. With such a diverse menu and consistent quality, I’ll definitely be visiting again to try more of their specialties!

Delicious food. I love the sizzling skillets! However we got the overnight french toast and it was just a stale bread with pistachio cream topping. Service is not good which makes sense because the restaurant is extremely crowded. Be prepared to wait in line for at least 30 minutes.

You can tell this place gets busy, cos there was a big lineup outside the front of the restaurant. We opted to sit outside on their patio to get a table right away. Not a lot of people were doing that because it was still kind of cold, but they have some heaters near the tables. It was tolerable.

Had the scrambled eggs with ham and cheddar and some potatoes. The food is on the saltier side for my taste. It’s definitely a filling portion.

I had the ‘Signature Berry Bliss’ pancakes as a side as well. The pancakes were great - not too thick and had a good bite and colour to it. I’m surprised that they don’t offer real maple syrup with their pancakes because this was a $6 surcharge to get. They otherwise just offer pancake syrup for free.

It’s a convenient location across from Millenium Park, so I can see why they’re busy. Would recommend if you want to fill up on food in the area.

formatted_address: 737 W Randolph St, Chicago, IL 60661, USA
name: Haymarket Pub & Brewery

reviews.text:
Stopped by Haymarket Brewery in Chicago and had an outstanding experience! I ordered the Pork Milanese and it was absolutely fantastic—crispy, flavorful, and cooked to perfection. Easily one of the best dishes I’ve had at a brewpub.

To go with it, I tried their Speaker Wagon Pilsner, and it was a perfect pairing. Light, crisp, and incredibly refreshing—ideal for a warm day or just unwinding after a long one.
