However, what sets The Chicago Firehouse Restaurant apart is the IMPECCABLE service. The staff here made us feel so welcome and cared for, everyone was extremely attentive throughout the night. Never an empty glass in sight. The coordinator we worked with ahead of the event, Carolyn, was very responsive and easy to work with. Highly recommend this venue if you are looking to host a private event.

Beautiful place! You can see the historic features of the original firehouse. Everything was so tastefully restored and the atmosphere was great. It was dimly lit and had a cozy feel. We had our 11yo son and he felt right at home. Menu was great, we ordered the shared meal that came with 2 filets, 3 sides, salads and dessert. The fish and chips were also amazing. We enjoyed the old fashion with Michters. Our waiter was amazing! Friendly staff, knowledgeable and definitely made us feel at home. Definitely will be back!

On par with any steak house in the US. Plus the offer the Executive special. Two cups Lobster bisque, a wedge salad to share, two 8oz fillets, 3 sides potato’s, creamed spinach and brussels sprouts also a huge dessert to share. For a very reasonable price. Everything was delicious

Was so happy to find this restaurant. very classy inside they have private rooms for parties and outdoor patio and great food and service. Loved the gin Fizz drink too! Bread rolls are very tasty, meatballs were delicious, whipped potatoes smooth too. The sea bass was very good and my friend loved his NY strip sirloin as well. Great place for special dinners!

formatted_address: 835 Michigan Ave, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Garrett Popcorn Shops

reviews.text:
After watching a few videos of place to go in Chicago this one came up a lot. I really enjoyed watching how the popcorn was made with so much love. I was expecting a long line and was pleasantly surprised when it was a short line. I wish I could describe the amazing delicious smells before you even walk in. The location was clean and staff were super friendly. No public restroom here.
The cheese popcorn and caramel crunch and so delicious 😋 we bought them separately and mixed them ourselves. We stored them in ziplocks to stay fresh which it did for three days. It might have lasted longer but I ate it because it was so yummy. Ten out of ten 1000% recommend stopping by any of their locations for the best popcorn ever. I heard you can have it shipped but that popcorn might have preservatives. The fresh made spoils fast because there are no preservatives. Can’t wait for my daughter to go back and send me some overnight from the shop. The cheese popcorn is so fresh cheesy and delicious. Warning: you may get cheese fingers but it’s worth it. MUST TRY!!
Delicious popcorn!!  I got a small of the spicy cheese and a medium bag of the caramel and cheese mix so addictive!!
Must visit if you are in Chicago for quick snacking and amazing popcorns !’

A friend of mine recommended me to go to  Garrett popcorn and order the special mix, even though the mix sounded a little crazy because of it spicy and sweet, of course, I said yes!

It was the best popcorn I have had in my life, with all the respect to everyone else that makes popcorn.

I just wish I could have more and more and more.

The service was wonderful and what I loved about the popcorn is that, believe it or not, my hands were not sticky, it didn’t stick on my teeth either, and it was so crispy.

Went around 4pm on Saturday and waited in line for 15 minutes or so. The line moves faster than you’d expect. We got the Garrett mix with cheese and caramel and it was pretty good! The caramel was my favorite but mixing the sweet and savory was definitely good. If I came back and had to choose the flavor I’d definitely choose just the caramel but overall solid experience.

formatted_address: 702 West Fulton Market Street, 702 W Fulton St, Chicago, IL 60661, USA
name: Carnivale Chicago

reviews.text: First time at Carnival and really impressive restaurant. Great vibe and character. We were celebrating our anniversary and thought that this looked just right for dinner and drinks. Antonio our server was extremely friendly and took great care of us. It was a pleasure to have our table off the main floor which made it a little more intimate for us. Cocktails were awesome, food was delicious and we were surprised with an excellent anniversary dessert. Nicely done!

If you want a special dining experience, this is the place for you. The food is delicious, plentiful, and exotic. The ambiance, music, and atmosphere makes you feel as if you are at a carnival. Dancers conga through the dining floor. Later experience the bar nightlife. Great for couples or groups. Paid parking conveniently across the street.

Check to see when the dancers are performing.  It is a boisterous and fun way to enjoy fine dining.  The conga line was  fun.

Our group visited for restaurant week, and it was a flavorful meal. We all enjoyed our dishes, from steaks to vegetarian options.

Pete, our server was careful to make sure my food was safe and allergen were avoided.

He made sure my friend's birthday was special, bringing out a cotton candy dessert and a candle so we could sing.

It is a special treat, and a better experience for having shared it.

We had a great time at Carnival last night. The food, decor, service, and music were amazing, I was dancing the whole meal. We got the dinner for two. The market house salad, amazing. A strawberry mocktail, and their house old fashion made with tequila. Which honestly is enough for four, huge portions. Everything was juicy, tender, and delicious. The chief even came out to greet us. We are really happy we stumbled upon this beautiful dining experience. Definitely will have to come back.

My husband and I had the Argentinian parrillada and it definitely did not disappoint, meats were cooked to perfection and high quality. The chimichurri sauce is also top tier. We had stopped here one other time for drinks and appetizers at the bar, the empanadas and pupusas are very good!. The service is superior here from all staff (servers and bartenders). The decor is fun and makes you feel like you’re somewhere tropical. I have told sooo many people to come here and give it a try.

formatted_address: 240 Oakbrook Center, Oak Brook, IL 60523, USA
name: Maggiano's Little Italy

reviews.text: Typically, I’m not a fan of chain restaurants, but Maggiano’s has never let me down. The food is fresh, there are large portions, everything is delicious, the presentation is beautiful, and the service is efficient and friendly. Whether you’re up for a date night or a business event, you’re in good hands!

We had high hopes for Maggie’s in Oakbrook, but unfortunately, the experience fell short. My rigatoni pasta was overly salty and unexpectedly spicy, despite requesting gluten-free — which left my stomach uneasy after just a few bites. My daughter’s pasta had a strange milky, sugary taste that she didn’t enjoy at all. On a positive note, the appetizers were okay, and my husband’s seafood pasta was okay. Overall, the food felt mediocre and overpriced for the quality. In terms of pasta, in my opinion, Olive Garden delivers a better pasta experience than what we had here.

Maggiano's bread is absolute god tier. It's always warm and soft, and dipping it in the oil + parm is a heavenly experience. If you're a bread lover, like me, you'll love it here. I usually get the ravioli, but I did the half sandwich & salad lunch special today. OMG! The salad is sooo yummy. I'm not particularly a fry girl, but their's are coated in a garlic butter and are absolutely delicious. Chicken alfredo was pretty good too. Love love love the service & ambience

Visited for dinner before attending a play at Drury Lane. 6:30pm reservations on a Saturday night - definitely a hot spot! We were seated within 5 minutes & started off the evening with a couple drinks. The waitress briefly chuckled when I asked for a kiddie cocktail 😆 wifey got an Old Fashioned that arrived in a smoked box so that was pretty neat! We shared the Parmesan stuffed mushrooms as an appetizer alongside the bread with olive oil & more cheese 🤤 the mushrooms were meaty & flavorful; the bread was soft, warm, & a wonderful vessel to scoop up the remaining sauce. Wifey ordered the Wagyu stuffed shells & I got the chicken Parmesan. She enjoyed her meal but felt the Wagyu should be the star of the show & it didn’t really stand out in this particular dish. I loved the basil leaves atop my dish which enhanced the taste of the chicken. Overall pleased with our visit & happy to come again at another time.

Absolutely fantastic dining experience!
From start to finish, everything was perfect. The food was incredible – the portion sizes were huge, and everything was fresh and flavorful. Our server was attentive, friendly, and made the evening even more enjoyable. Highly recommend this location if you’re in Oak Brook!

formatted_address: 1901 Woodfield Rd, Schaumburg, IL 60173, USA
name: Maggiano's Little Italy

reviews.text: Held a 50th wedding anniversary party here this weekend. The whole process from booking to execution was excellent. I received so many compliments how nice everything was. Food was great, room beautiful. Staff helpful and attentive. I am very happy my party was such a success. Thank you!

Our experience at this amazing restaurant was top notch from the moment we walked in. The team here goes above and beyond. Our group of 7 were greeted by the servers, as well as management. Everyone goes above and beyond. The service was simply impeccable. The atmosphere is beautiful. The drinks and food were all delicious. We had fried ravioli, bread with olive oil, an old fashioned drink that was smoked in a special vessel, grand chicken Parmesan, grilled salmon, and spaghetti with meatballs, just to name a few. The quality and quantity of the food was very good. We observed many tables celebrating special occasions. We will definitely be back if we have a chance.

Beautifully updated /renovated with a spacious parking lot. There are stairs as well as an elevator close to the entrance making it convenient to access the private rooms upstairs. The elevator can fit 4-5 adults comfortably. The private rooms upstairs feature flexibility in size making them a great choice for celebrations of all kinds. Overall, the restaurant can accommodate small to large groups with ease no matter what the occasion. I recently attended a private event at this location and the experience was memorable and pleasant. The service was attentive and cordial, while the food was classically delicious Italian-satisfying and hearty in every way. 😋 I highly recommend the desserts that were featured on the menu, which were the chocolate layer cake and tiramisu.  The decadent chocolate cake was the best I have ever had while the tiramisu was outstanding and not too rich. 🥳

I had a wonderful 50th birthday dinner here on a Saturday evening. The pasta dishes were absolutely delicious. The server was super friendly and professional, and the manager personally delivered my birthday dessert. It was a great experience. =)

Maggianos is always an excellent experience everytime we go there. The only thing that was disappointing was they took the Chicken Manicotti off the menu. That was my wife's favorite dish. The lasagna was amazing and the chicken alfredo was very good.

formatted_address: 864 N State St, Chicago, IL 60610, USA
name: Pizano's Pizza & Pasta

reviews.text:
Went to Pizano’s for dinner on Thursday. Called the E Madison spot for a reservation for a party of 4 but there was none available. Tried the N State St location, and they said I wouldn’t need a reservation - not sure why the disparity, but I was happy! Got there at 7:30pm and we were seated promptly. The ambiance was great and the service was generally good. Ordered a small salad, it was alright. Got a couple of drinks too, they were ok too. Placed the pizza order, it took about 45 minutes to be made, so Nov too bad. When the pizza came out, it was piping hot and generally good looking. On being served, we realized the slices lose some structure and sort of fall off a bit. Got a sense that there was too much moisture overall and the crust felt a little soggy. With that said, the taste was pretty good, just the structure didn’t hold.

I would certainly recommend coming here when in Chicago, perhaps not my first choice if I could only do one deep dish! But not a bad second or third choice.

Don’t leave because you think they are full; they have a back dining room.  Cute Chicago sports themed decor.  I tried to make a phone reservation, but was told they only take reservations for four or more.  Waitress told us all their pizzas, deep dish or thin crust,  take 40 minutes; so, order an appetizer if you’re hangry.  Also, the waitress told us they don’t take Apple Pay or any tap payment.  You have to have a physical credit card or cash (who carries cash?).

We ordered a medium deep dish Mark’s pizza, which comes with sliced tomatoes, basil, and garlic.  The Cabernet was the perfect accompaniment.  Pizza itself was a mozzarella bomb.  Huge amount of mozzarella and I mean huge!  Thin layer of sliced tomatoes in red sauce and topped with what seemed to me as a bit of fresh and some dried basil as well.  I would have preferred more fresh basil.  I could only eat about one and a half slices and my hubby had 2 slices.  The medium pizza still had two slices left.  All in all, a nice dinner.

Ok I did not know that Pizano's Pizza and Pasta has multiple outlets in the Michigan Avenue area in downtown Chicago but if I recall correctly this one is close to the Bean. It was a busy place during lunch hour and it was the weekend. We got a place right away which is great. The menu is largely Italian - pasta, risotto, salad but it was quite the struggle to find vegetarian options sober settled for a pasta in extra spicy marinara sauce. The cabernet I had was great. They have a bar so you can pair pair whatever drink that goes with your food. The lady who looked after us was just amazing - really friendly, quick to respond and in general just fantastic. I should have asked for her name so I could specifically mention our thanks to her for making it a pleasant experience circus despite the weekend buzz. It's funny how you remember a place so much for the place but because of one person who made it a pleasant experience for you. People matter... They also have street side seating which should be nice inn the evenings. I think they can easily accomodate about 80 people on a busy day. I just wish they include more vegetarian choices that is not necessarily a salad...

Pizano’s felt like a warm, nostalgic pause just off the Magnificent Mile—easy to walk to, but far enough from the noise to breathe. We showed up just after 4 PM and had no trouble getting a table. The space has that classic, wood-heavy, red-checkered tablecloth energy that so many places try to fake but few pull off. Gallery walls of Chicago icons, Bulls legends, and faded celebrity snapshots wrap the room in history—and yes, there’s still a little holiday garland wound around the ceiling like it never left.

We ordered a vegetarian deep dish, split it, and paired it with a Pizano’s draft beer, which was much better than expected! The sauce was the standout—bright, tomato-forward, and generously ladled. The crust had character, with just enough crunch and butter to hold its own. The cheese, while serviceable, didn’t wow us, but the pie as a whole hit the spot. It was hearty, comforting, and exactly what we needed after a long day on foot.

Would I go back regularly? Probably not. But for a once-a-trip experience, it earned its place. It felt like the kind of recommendation someone gives you with pride—and after one bite, you see why.

4+ stars: Friendly service, a reliable deep-dish institution with old-school charm and a sauce that carries the team.

Really sad about this experience. The tortellini with meat sauce was bland and terrible. Olive Garden does it better. I’m in the industry and recognize those torts, they 100% come in frozen. Really really shameful that they would serve soulless, unseasoned sauce. Did anyone in the kitchen bother to taste the sauce they served today? No herbs, no spices, no garlic, no wine, no sugar. This is supposed to be an Italian restaurant and you serve bland food? Your pizza is atleast good.

We sat by the person rolling silverware and had clanking metal noises in our ear from them banging around the silverware tub. Maybe do that back in the kitchen?

formatted_address: 1832 N Clybourn Ave, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: Buffalo Wild Wings

reviews.text:
Visited Buffalo Wild Wings on a Monday, and overall, it was a pretty good experience. The place wasn’t crowded, which made for a relaxed atmosphere. We loved the open windows that let in a nice breeze—it really added to the vibe.

The food was excellent—fresh, flavorful, and just what we were craving. Definitely lived up to the expectations in that department.

However, the service was noticeably slow. It took a solid 30 minutes from the time we placed our order to when we actually got our food. Considering the place wasn’t busy, that delay was disappointing.

If you’re not in a rush, it’s a great spot to enjoy good food in a chill setting. But if you’re short on time, be prepared for a bit of a wait.

I ordered a pickup order of 10 wings (BOGO) with Asian Zing, Parmesan Garlic, and Cajun sauce, along with regular onion rings for $7.49. This isn’t my first time ordering the onion rings, but come on—the portion was disappointingly small.

I also informed the cashier that the Cajun sauce I ordered was missing. The cashier was kind enough to check with the kitchen, and they claimed the Cajun sauce was in the box. Guess what? There was no Cajun sauce.

I should probably start going to a different location from now.

The wings are fine. Nothing spesh.
The ice cream was too hard to eat. The cake wasn't great

The seats in the booths are cracked. The carpet is dirty. The bathroom is a bit dirty. Not terrible, but something to point out.

The server was super nice.

I hadn’t been to Buffalo Wild Wings in a while, but wow—what an incredible experience! From the moment I walked in, Jared, the manager, greeted me with the warmest smile and the kind of hospitality that instantly makes you feel at home. His customer service was truly next-level—an easy 11/10!

The atmosphere was absolutely perfect. The windows by the bar were open, letting in a gentle breeze and filling the space with the refreshing scent of spring. It felt like the ideal spot to kick back, relax, and soak in the good vibes. Speaking of vibes—10/10, no question! The energy in the restaurant was lively yet welcoming, making for the perfect dining experience.

But what truly made my visit unforgettable was the incredible service. Everyone was so friendly, attentive, and genuinely happy to be there, which made all the difference. It’s rare to find a place that gets everything so right, but BWW knocked it out of the park. Can’t wait to come back for another amazing visit!

This was one of the worst dining experiences I’ve had in a long time. As soon as we walked in, there was an unpleasant smell in the dining area. On top of that, there was no air conditioning, and it was 95° outside. The place felt hot, muggy, and incredibly uncomfortable to sit in.

The only reason we stayed was because one of my daughters really wanted their wings. Otherwise, I would’ve left. Our food came out at completely different times. My other daughter had to eat my fries while waiting for her kid’s burger, which didn’t even show up until everyone else had already finished eating. Terrible service.

Buffalo Wild Wings has really gone downhill over the years. I’m honestly shocked that a big franchise like this is okay with operating under these conditions. I won’t be coming back to any BWWs again. ✌🏽

formatted_address: 100 E Walton St, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Gaylord Fine Indian Cuisine

reviews.text: Gaylord Indian Cuisine offers a warm and inviting dining experience that captures the essence of traditional Indian flavors. Their Tandoori Chicken is a standout, marinated in aromatic spices and grilled to perfection, resulting in a smoky, tender, and flavorful dish. Complementing this is the Sweet Lassi, a classic Indian beverage made from fresh yogurt, providing a refreshing and creamy contrast to the spicy fare. Together, these dishes highlight Gaylord's dedication to authentic and delightful Indian cuisine, making it a must-visit for both enthusiasts and newcomers alike.

The best kept secret for Indian food in Chicago. Authentic, no frills, reasonably priced, great location in the height of shopping district near magnificent mile. My destination for Indian food in each Chicago trip

Good indian food but service needs work. We really like the appetizers here. Portions are good and priced appropriately but curry doesn’t hit the mark. Service was definitely a mixed bag. One of our servers wasn’t attentive and got us the bill even before we had a chance to order dessert after main course. Another time the service was pretty good.

Liked this restaurant offering Indian cuisine in the heart of Chicago’s Magnificent Mile. The ambience is fantastic, good array of buffet items for lunch, great professional staff. Being an Indian , though I felt the food lacking the authenticity , still I would rate the restaurant 5 stars for their overall performance.

I love Gaylord fine indian restaurant. it is also affordable with a wonderful buffet that includes dessert, Tandoori chicken made to order as part of your meal. Sh o a i b is most gracious with service.

formatted_address: 500 W Madison St #14, Chicago, IL 60661, USA
name: Burrito Beach

reviews.text:
Review written 11/15/2024. Egg and cheese burrito was good but a little bland. Side of salsa was way too small for size of burrito.

Also, the app ordering lists cans of drinks but the location does not actually have cans so just be aware if ordering ahead.

Do not come here. We have been to this location on more than one occasion and they can not redeem themselves at this point. The first time we ordered online here they dropped the burrito on the ground and remade it. This time we ordered online and the food wasn't ready and we had to wait. Okay, no big deal it happens. The person slapped the burrito together and literally threw them in the bags. What we opened when we got home is pictured. Unwrapped, burst burritos in multiple places. One of the burritos was made incorrectly. Sauce all over the bag. Unappetizing, poor quality, and just plain disrespectful.
The burrito doesn’t have anything the quantity is very less … i ordered a spicy chicken burrito for 10$ it doesn’t even worth 1$

Our office had breakfast burritos catered and had forgotten to include corn tortillas for our gluten free folks. I called Burrito Beach and the catering manager so kindly hand delivered corn tortilla breakfast burritos 20 minutes later. Truly such a kind act that we were so grateful for!
So good! Great customer service, fast and efficient! One of my favorite burritos I've ever had!

formatted_address: 1847 Freedom Dr, Naperville, IL 60563, USA
name: Maggiano's Little Italy

reviews.text:
I recently had the chance to photograph a wedding event at Maggiano’s Little Italy, and I was thoroughly impressed. The staff was fantastic—super attentive and accommodating, and they let me use the entire space for photos which made my job so much easier.

The food? Absolutely amazing! Every dish was delicious and beautifully presented. This venue is perfect for wedding rehearsals, receptions, or wedding parties. It’s also incredibly photo-friendly; no matter where you shoot, the space looks classy and elegant.

Highly recommend for anyone looking for a warm, welcoming venue with outstanding service and great food!

We had the most wonderful experiences, starting with the best greeting from Tommy, the manager! After a long day at work, his warm personality, genuine kindness, and perfect smile were such a delight. He truly set the tone for an amazing evening. Our server, Lexi, was equally fantastic—so attentive and kind, and she recommended a wine that paired beautifully with our meal. The entire experience was simply lovely, and we can’t wait to come back. Thank you for making our visit so special!

We have always loved Maggiano's. Our server, James, was a blast. Very friendly and funny. Love that they now shake your Martini at the table, and the Old-Fashioned is brought to the table in a smoke box. The food was awesome!

We celebrated our daughter’s birthday dinner at Maggiano’s in Naperville. Our server, Sarah, was very attentive and friendly. She gave great recommendations on both the dishes and the drinks. We all enjoyed our meals, and everything tasted fantastic. The whiskey pour was especially generous — definitely a plus for me!

The food was good, the decor was fine, and the bartender (I ate at the bar) seemed friendly enough. The portion sizes were large enough that I ate most of it, but couldn't finish the last bit - which is better than eating and still wanting more. I had the lasagna and tiramisu and would recommend both.

formatted_address: 548 N Wells St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Al's #1 Italian Beef

reviews.text: First trip to Chicago and there are many places to go for an Italian Beef. This came highly recommended from many friends who live or have lived here. So, this was my first sandwich and it was delicious. Went with the recommendation of dipped…and for my wife to take her rings off while eating it. Being from Jersey, I’m an cheesesteak guy, this is totally different, but fantastic. Has a bit of heat and soggy in a good way. We also had the Chicago dog which was equally enjoyable. Pickle, mustard, pepper, relish. Each bite was better than the last. If you’re in Chicago, definitely give it a try!! Enjoy!

Wow this place was cheap and sooooo delicious. Super fast service too. Fantastic. One thing though, the Italian beef doesnt come with the peppers or giardinera you have to add that. I was low key dissapointed because I didn't read the menu carefully. But regardless its a fantastic Italian beef and fantastic Chicago dog. Good fries.

Straight in from Texas, our family ordered the beef sandwich,  chicken sandwich and chili dog. Delicious! Clean restaurant,  fast and very friendly service which was really appreciated. This was our first visit to Chicago and this culinary landmark didn't disappoint. Highly recommend.

Al’s #1 Italian Beef on Ohio & Wells delivers big flavor! The beef is top-notch, the chicken is a hidden gem, but the fries? Absolute perfection—crispy, golden, and addictive. A must-visit for Chicago eats!

After watching “The Bear” and being told I need to try an italian roast beef in Chicago, I went on a mission to get over to Mr. Beef’s. However, they were closed this week due to filming so I ended up pivoting to Al’s which still seemed to have a good online presence and it was only a few blocks away. I may never know what an italian beef from Mr. Beef tastes like but oh my lord, the italian beef here at Al’s was unreal.

I ordered the regular italian beef wet with sweet peppers. The bread had just the right amount of juices soaking into it without it being too soggy or falling apart. And the meat, words can’t even describe how flavorful it was. You can tell they put some love into the recipe. The place was also pretty busy so I took mine on the go and ate it as I walked. I felt like I housed the whole thing fairly quickly and probably could’ve downed another one easily. This hands down will probably be the best, most affordable thing I eat while I’m in the city, and I would definitely go back for round 2 sooner than later.

formatted_address: 1303 Butterfield Rd, Downers Grove, IL 60515, USA
name: Original Hooters

reviews.text:
Had an absolutely amazing time at Hooters for my birthday! The wings were top-notch—cooked perfectly, sauced just right, and full of flavor. The service was incredible, with the staff making sure everything was spot on the whole night.

Big shoutout to all the Hooters girls who sang the Hooters birthday song for me—it was definitely a highlight! If you’re looking for great food, great service, and a fun atmosphere, this is the place to be. Can’t wait to take some of my buddies and celebrate their birthdays at this location

Quick service. We love the Daytona wings and the boneless wings. The salad was good, too. Our only complaint is that they sat us near the bar and the music was loud. It was difficult to have a conversation.

It’s been many years since I’ve stepped foot in here and honestly it’s nothing special. While the service was great, the wings were lackluster. Especially the medium wings which just felt oily and really had no taste of spice. The BBQ style wings had too much sauce on them. Don’t even bother ordering the fries. They even charged us for ranch. You’re better off bringing your own. The best part of my meal was the drink, Jolly Roger, as it was delicious. Unfortunately this establishment needs a rehab. The walls were full of skid marks and crayon marks. I would rather see a full gut job on this restaurant before eating here again.
The photo sums up the issue. We got the order to go and rather than 20 drumsticks they put all wings, quite a disappointment. Pretty unreal.
Friendly staff, clean bathrooms, good food, and the good comes out fast.

formatted_address: 3 S, 100 IL-53, Glen Ellyn, IL 60137, USA
name: Subway

reviews.text: Horrible customer service. Asked for a wrap and the man that was working at 7 PM on Wednesday, May 8 told me that they don’t have wraps. Well sir, there is a giant sign right behind him that says “try our wraps” he tried to convince me it was flatbread, it’s definitely not, it’s a tortilla, and I have ordered them many many times from many subways, including this one. I’m not sure what time they close, but he really didn’t seem very interested in helping me or the girl that was ordering in front of me. I get that food and retail is hard in general, but that doesn’t excuse gaslighting me, trying to tell me subway doesn’t have wraps. I promise I’ve eaten them. I never really eat at subway but a sweet onion chicken teriyaki sounded good, guess not. Went to the one on Roosevelt and guess what, wraps galore!

Was taking my daughter to day camp and had ordered my sub at least 3 hours ahead of time since I knew I was gonna stop at the Walmart. Waited in line to pick up my sub. Finally it was my turn and I told him I had an order for pickup. He looked at me like I had 3 heads! He went to go find the ticket and realized he didn't make it, so he started it for me right away. I  did notice that he was the only employee,  and it seemed like they we're understaffed. I was fine with waiting for it. Made it really fast and even gave me some extra chips for the wait. After I got back to the camp to wait for my daughter, I started to eat my sandwich and noticed he didn't put the cheese, the guacamole,  or the fresh mozzarella.  So I basically paid an extra $2 for nothing. I understood he wanted to get me my sandwich as soon as possible,  but don't rush and forget the ingredients I paid for. The sandwich was really good, but overall I might stop at a different location next time if I order ahead of time.

Order 6 different boxes through easy cater got 5. Went back and guy working there said didn't see it at top of list. Then proceeded to say that sandwhich and chips weren't selected yet in confirmation email shows they are. So he decided to just send me with 5 boxes and not says thing about his. confusion even though it was prepaid for. I confronted him about that and 3 families walked out of line. Canonlyimagine how they steal from thier customers when there's a catering order I will never use again
The people working are always very polite, and very quick.  I visit this location 4 out of 5 days a week for that reason. Thanks!
I left a hefty tip on my credit card to be told by employee that the owner keeps the card tips which is illegal  and i will let the franchise know

formatted_address: 2622 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: The Wiener's Circle

reviews.text: Second to last stop on the glizzy tour The charred Chicago dog was the bomb, and it had the poppy seed bun the fries were the best we had all trip. Ask for it with hot peppers this place also has the best seating and restrooms. Definitely coming back. Thank you

This is a lot of fun especially at night. The Chicago dogs are some of my personal favorite dogs. Watched the review of the wiener Circle on YouTube from the Coney bros and I knew I had to go get myself a dog from here. Service is a tad different but makes it the experience it is.

This iconic hot dog joint delivers not only delicious food but also a memorable, interactive experience. The hot dogs at The Wiener's Circle are undeniably delicious, and they offer a variety of toppings to choose from. I enjoyed the classic Chicago-style dog, which was perfectly seasoned and topped with all the traditional fixings. The food is a bit on the greasy side, but that's part of the charm. What sets The Wiener's Circle apart is its lively and entertaining staff. They engage with customers in a playful banter that's all in good fun. The humorous and sometimes irreverent interactions added an element of entertainment to the meal. It's not your typical fast-food experience, and it's not for the faint of heart. If you're up for some light-hearted banter and want a bit of Chicago's famously bold attitude, this is the place to go. The outdoor seating area was clean and well-maintained, and the service was quick and efficient. The prices are reasonable, making it an affordable option in the heart of the city. While the hot dogs are unquestionably tasty, the experience is what makes The Wiener's Circle unique. If you're looking for a fun and unapologetically Chicago-style dining adventure, you should give it a try. Just be prepared for a bit of sass along with your meal. The Wiener's Circle is a must-visit for anyone looking for a tasty hot dog and a milkshake with a side of Chicago humor. It's not a dining establishment, but it offers a distinct experience that's worth trying at least once. Just remember to bring a sense of humor with you! and please DO NOT PUT KETCHUP on the Hot dogs!!

My Chicago Dog was ok, service not so great. My order wasn't correct, I ordered 1 Chicago Dog and 1 regular hotdog with mustard only. I ended up with 2 Chicago dogs. The worker taking my order I wasn't sure if she was talking to me or the person on her phone. My Chicago dog didn't taste any different from a hotdog at a cookout.  So I'm good on my Chicago Dog experience,  won't need to have another.

We were in town visiting friends, and decided on some local flavor.
Grilled or steamed red hots (Vienna beef) is always good, but their cheeseburger today won!! Oh, and cheese fries.

formatted_address: 1040 W Belmont Ave, Chicago, IL 60657, USA
name: Giordano's

reviews.text: Great pizza! Nice place to enjoy food after a Cubs game. Deep dish pizza goes a long way to feeding hungry teenagers. Lol

Went there late night on a Saturday and it was great food. My server was very attentive I do not remember his name but he worked 1.18.25 and he was the only server on the floor. Around 9 pm. He was nice and welcoming. Kiss to the chef!

Visiting from out of town and stopped here during lunch for the deep dish pizza while exploring Wrigley area. Pizza was good and totally different from any pizza I’ve ever had.  Food was slow to come out but I’m assuming that’s normal due to the thickness of the pizza. Worth a stop if in Chicago, this pizza chain is everywhere!

First place I ate when I came to Chicago - also the place where I discovered I don't really like deep dish pizza LOL. Calamari was good though, with a nice crunch. Still giving five stars because I think my dislike of deep dish pizza is a preference problem and not a Giordano's problem.

As soon as you walk in, you are greeted, and the atmosphere is inviting. The food was good. I really loved the sampler appetizer plate. I loved how they tell you upfront that the deep dish will take 45 minutes to cook. The taste was good, I didn't care too much for the crust. I'm glad that we were able to try a chicago deep dish while visiting from California. Will definitely be back next time we are in Chicago.

formatted_address: 2020 Spring Rd, Oak Brook, IL 60523, USA
name: The Cheesecake Factory

reviews.text:
It can get pretty packed here on weekends. We had to wait an hour and 15 minutes for a party of 5 for dinner. The food was decent , however, I am not convinced it was worth the wait.
-Fettuccine Alfredo was creamy and delicious. -Stirfry Thai noodles were pretty good.
-Grilled Fish tacos were decent, however the fish was overcooked.
-Skip their burgers, it lacked flavor and I think was made from frozen patty.
Service was excellent.

Beautiful atmosphere, somewhat loud and busy but it was also a Saturday afternoon. Impossible burger was delicious. Parents enjoyed the steak and mashed potatoes. Crunchy fish and chips! Ice cream needs more hot fudge according to my sister. There was no vegan cheesecake 🥲, maybe next time it will randomly appear on the menu!

This location is a nice one, well from my experience it was. The inside is very spacious, much bigger than the Orland Park location. The service was on point & our cheerful server (Jalisa) was awesome! The manager was present and participating in getting tables ready for the bigger groups. I do think there’s an opportunity for the bus boys to be better trained on filling water when the cups on the table are empty. Aside from that little tiny detail, we had a great experience. The restaurant & bathrooms were clean, the food portions were plenty & pretty tasty too. I’m sorry, forgot to snag pics at the beginning of the meals. Here are some partially enjoyed ones. I’ll head back over there anytime! The parking was an open lot, but very busy on a Friday night, to be expected. Save room for dessert!! Duh! 😜 🍰#OAKBROOK

My family and I came for brunch for Mother's Day weekend.  The food was sensational, even my picky niece loved her pasta. The server was so friendly, positive, and really cared for us. Definitely will come back and ask for her!!

I took my whole family for Mother’s Day, I got there around open time to avoid long wait. We were able to get a big table which was awesome. The food was soo good.
Reminder that after 8+ party, tip is included in the total. I recommend the mojito and the pastas.

formatted_address: 137 W North Ave, Northlake, IL 60164, USA
name: Subway

reviews.text:
HORRIBLE SANDWICH, DEPRESSING PLACE AND DEPRESSED EMPLOYEE.

This review is based solely on my own experience and personal opinion.

I went to this SUBWAY on a Friday night, 12/17/21, and it was my first time.

I was Hungry and thirsty, and I decided to stop by Wal-Mart to get something.
When I got in a saw Subway and since I was very tired, I decided to grab a sandwich and go back to my hotel.

I spent a couple of minutes looking at the different options and then realizing they did not have a ALL-VEGGIES option I asked them man a sandwich with no meat.
The Man was very demotivated, slow and extremely bored.
I asked him an All-Veggies sandwich with no meat and no cheese....
What he did, in order to save money, he put 5 leaves of spinach on the bottom, few leaves of lettuce over the spinach and then he filled the sandwich with cheap onions, banana peppers and spicy peppers.
When I asked him why so few green leaves and no olives, he looked at me and open the sandwich showing me the few leaves. At that point he was NOT happy with me.
He goes ahead and asks if I want some spicy peppers and some veggies in vinegar.... I reply, "just a little bit".
Then it comes the time to pay, and the price had nothing to do with what I had ordered, totally random. He came up with a $9 receipt that made sense in his mind only. I ask him how he came up with the $9 bill and with a nasty attitude he goes "I put what you want, and you pay what I want".
UNBELIEVABLE!!!
I pay, I go back to the hotel and..... the sandwich was disgusting!!!!
It was one of the worst sandwiches I have ever had in my life.

The sandwich was SUPER SPICY, BITTER, SOUR, ACIDIC, NO GREEN LEAVES, ODD FLAVORS and instead of the Chipotle dressing he put Caesar dressing.

CONCLUSIONS: just avoid this SUBWAY restaurant if you can.

Awful service . The Indian guy behind the counter was just talking away for a long time in his native language on the phone. His phone call was more important than helping  his customers. I go back and he’s still on the phone taking . Ridiculous !   Won’t be back.

Make sure you are charged correctly. Bought a chicken bacon ranch sub, he forgot the bacon before toasting. I asked for the bacon that should already be on there and got charged for extra bacon. For only 2 pieces of microwaved bacon. Was probably the lightest subway sandwich I’ve ever gotten for 15$

Terrible service the two Indian employees were so rude specially the chubby short one. They were yelling at my little sister because she couldn't understand them. You can't even see the cheeses or ham they offer. I hated it, please save yourself the head ache and go to a different location. I never want to to back there again.

I ordered online for a pick up and didn’t realize I ordered from the subway in Walmart I had my kids In the car with me that had fallen asleep I called to ask if they would be able to bring it out to me since I can’t leave them alone, they were very kind and brought it to me as I was park right by the entrance and the sandwiches were very good

formatted_address: 5320 N River Rd, Rosemont, IL 60018, USA
name: McCormick & Schmick's Seafood & Steaks

reviews.text: Absolutely amazing! The food here is so delicious. Everything was cooked to perfection. The service was impeccable. Much appreciated to Toby! He made us feel like family. We came in late, and he treated us like we had all night. The house manager Melinda is the best. We were blessed to meet her. She is the mother of the front house and we was family. They made our small birthday celebration special! We will definitely return.

Excellent ambiance for a romantic dinner. Our waiter was new, but very well informed about the food, service was top notch! We made early reservations for dinner (4:45) and got an excellent table. Food was perfectly prepared.
The salmon was cooked perfectly, the Brussels were tender, crisp, flavorful and not too greasy or heavy. The dessert was decadent however there was a large chunk of amazing chocolate that we could eat and have to sadly leave behind. Raw oysters were fresh and flavorful. We tried all three flavors available.
We will definitely visit this restaurant again when in Rosemont.

Absolutely *INCREDIBLE*!!! Deano the best!! I ❤️ the curvature of this space overlooking the street & and the ambience of class & exquisite design!

We tried the Chilean Sea Bass + Crab 🦀 & Shrimp 🍤 stuffed salmon dish (mashed potatoes & broccoli) 🥦 AND it was ungodly!!

The bar area is also gorgeous and on a curve. There are multiple seating areas: a section for elevated seating, private booths, and seats along the cover chair facing the street.. all which I thought were extremely charming.

Can’t say enough great things about this space, place & service.

We went here for Christmas dinner and had a fabulous meal. Our server was great. Our food was excellent. Only issue was we had a reservation and they were a bit backed up but it was the holidays so we just had a drink at the bar. They do valet and validate parking. The deck is quite expensive so make sure to take your ticket.

We had the calamari two ways to share with the table. Both were great but I really enjoyed the Asian flavor. I also had the white fish. It was great! It came with a risotto and it was creamy and rich which balanced the light fish. Really nice.

This might be a classic case of maybe it's me and not the restaurant. The food was quite bland for my taste buds. I correlate flavor and food cost together, in that way this food was a let down for me. The place and service was amazing. But the flavors are a big let down for me.

formatted_address: 2434 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: The Pasta Bowl - Lincoln Park

reviews.text:
Large portions, quality food, and reasonable prices! You can definitely split a dish and both leave full!

What we ordered:
- Strawberry, Walnut & Pear Salad ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️4/5
- Fargfalle Pollo ⭐️⭐️⭐️💫3.5/5

The Pasta Bowl is my go-to spot for a comforting and delicious pasta fix. One of the standout features is their pasta bar, where the chef is continuously crafting different types of fresh pasta right in front of you. It’s such a great concept—it keeps the crowd engaged and adds a fun, interactive touch to the dining experience.

As for the food, their Fettuccine Chicken Alfredo is my absolute favorite. The pasta is perfectly cooked, the sauce is rich and creamy without being overwhelming, and the chicken is always tender and flavorful. Every bite feels like a warm, satisfying hug.

A very cool place, very tasty food, magical pasta, large portions, atmospheric, they cook before your eyes, and special thanks to the waiter Aje, his service, care and great mood filled our visit with additional positivity! We will definitely come back, we haven't tried dessert yet, there wasn't enough room for it)))

Incredible service! Accidentally placed me order to the Lincoln Square location, but they fixed me right up and told me not to go there, that they’d make my order right here, no sweat. They also called the other store and let them know; super understanding, and the food hit the spot. Could not recommend more.
Had this a couple of weeks ago, seated immediately, the order was taken quickly. Our server was very kind and attentive. The food here is decent, and I would come again.

formatted_address: 815 W Van Buren St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: Giordano's

reviews.text: Firstly, this was a to-go order & every dish I ordered didn’t live up to my expectations. Two Individual custom pizza’s that didn’t come cut & were only “ok”. I also ordered a classic dish, fettuccine Alfredo with chicken & broccoli.. it was VERY bland, the pasta was overcooked & the broccoli was mushy. To go with the pasta, I ordered a side Italian salad (mainly for the cheese & meat) but it came without both & the incorrect dressing.

Ordered online to be delivered to Lansing Michigan it arrived three days later packed in dry ice, followed the instructions to prepare and enjoyed deliciousness that evening, felt like I was back home in Chicago 😋😋😋
Never had real deep dish until now. So worth the 45 minute wait. Hands down top tier service from the staff and the fried calamari is out of the world.

As I was in Chicago it would have been rude not to try the deep dish..
Giordanos it was with my Sister!
It felt weird to order our deep dish (we shared the small as I really did think I wasn't going to enjoy it..) and wait for a table, but the ordering staff explained why (it takes 45 mins to make and bake!) and all was fine and they were friendly even though they were so busy.
The wait wasn't that bad and when we went in to our table, blimey, it was busy! There was a fantastic atmosphere and the wait staff were prompt and really good.
Drinks ordered and a couple of sips in and good conversation the pizza arrived.
OMG! That is it. I wish I'd ordered a larger one. It was so good! I really didn't think I'd like it, but oh my.. Go and try it!
5 stars all round and thank you for a great start to Pizza pie!

My niece wanted pizza after her graduation so we decided to stop in at Giordano’s. We are glad we did. The pizza, mozzarella triangles, and wings were delicious. Everything came out fresh and hot, you could see the steam coming towards the table. Our server( Justin) was amazing. He was polite, courteous and attentive. Nobody does Deep Dish like Giordano’s, just the right amount of sauce to crust ratio, then the cheese pull. Oh my goodness. Thanks Giordano’s for a great meal with great customer service.
It was a 10 out of 10 for US, cause we all voted!!!

formatted_address: 400 N Wells St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Kinzie Chophouse

reviews.text: I had lunch here during restaurant week and was pleasantly surprised by how excellent everything was. The mushroom soup was rich and flavorful, the Prime Rib was incredibly juicy and delicious, and the carrot cake was a delightful treat. I left feeling full and completely satisfied. The service was also exceptional.

Awesome spot on Kinzie. Visited during happy hour at the bar in December. It was quiet, the sliders were fantastic and drinks were great. Our bartender was friendly and service was excellent, per usual. Dinner service has been great in the past as well.

The service and ambiance were fine. The food was a let down. Take the mac n cheese, for example —yes it’s large and cheesy but it’s not creamy, flavorful, or decadent. The bone-in ribeye was poorly cooked, served raw in some parts and nearly medium well in others. It left a lot to be desired.
The best steak I've had here in the USA. The atmosphere was high end, very warm, very appealing followed up with great service. These guys know what they're doing!

Had high hopes but they were dashed quickly. We ate upstairs in a private room. Smelled musty and yuck walking up the stairs. Gave ambiance of an old rundown hotel. Staff was friendly and gave great presentations on steaks and what to order. I went against my normal (filet mignon) for the servers top recommendation and it was a too tough steak I didn’t really enjoy. I’m a big fan of French onion soup but this was lacking in flavor and making up for it with unexpectedly almost cracking a tooth on a foreign object of hard plastic. They were super kind and brought me giant shrimp cocktail to make up for it but they were rubbery and yuck too. I just wanted to be snug back in my hotel room. Couldn’t pay me to return unfortunately.

formatted_address: 4999 Old Orchard Shopping Ctr Suite A28, Skokie, IL 60077, USA
name: Maggiano's Little Italy

reviews.text: Went to Maggiano’s for the first time and had such a great experience! Manny was our server and he was amazing—friendly, efficient, and super attentive to both me and my boyfriend. The food came out hot, fresh, and fast, which we really appreciated. The overall vibe of the place was warm and welcoming. Definitely planning to come back again!

Maggianos is fire. I appreciate the staffs and managers kindness to me even though I have autism and their food is amazing and really good.  Zach and Ari were very nice. So did Justin the sous chef preparing excellent high quality food. They cook the food fresh and ready to eat and they maintain the restaurant clean. Amazing chicken saltimbocca. Must come back. 10/10

Exceptional food and service
Apr 2025
Chef Justin went out of his way. Met us at our table and noted every one of our dietary restrictions. We were able to enjoy a wonderful Italian dinner (gluten free and dairy free) without worry. The steaks were cooked to perfection.
Chef Justin also surprised us with a delicious gluten-free and dairy free Bolognese.
Great experience dining and would highly recommend.

Our server Juan was also wonderful

We had an amazing dining experience at Maggiano’s in Skokie (Old Orchard)! Our server Jerome was outstanding—so attentive, friendly, and genuinely made us feel welcome from the moment we sat down. He checked in at all the right times, made thoughtful recommendations, and made the whole evening feel special.

The manager even came by to check on us, which was such a nice touch and really showed how much they care about their guests.

It’s rare to get that level of service and hospitality these days. Hands down, one of the best restaurant experiences we’ve had in a long time. Huge thank you to Jerome and the Maggiano’s team—we’ll definitely be back!

Atmosphere - beautiful
Food - POOR
Service - friendly

We are visiting Chicago and i was in a real mood for Italian. Their signature dish Chicken marsala and Alfredo (especially) very watered down and tasteless Alfredo. First came with chicken (wrong order), then came with shrimp who are were not as advertised 'jumbo' or property grilled  - more like boiled and lightly seared.
Also, investing in proper olive oil I'd say is pretty important - the quality of products is very poor quality.

We were really happy to be seeing different areas of town and this wasn't going to ruin our amazing Chicago tour -
Sadly not authentic Italian by a long shot.
Sorry guys and I hope you may improve.

formatted_address: 26 W Randolph St, Chicago, IL 60601, USA
name: Garrett Popcorn Shops

reviews.text: The staff at this location was friendly and welcoming. My daughter wasn't sure if she wanted the caramel popcorn, so she was given a sample without us having to ask. The popcorn was fresh. It brought back memories from when I was a kid, and my mom would bring it home for my brother and I. I'd go back to this location.

I love Garrett's Popcorn. I always grab a bag to-go, before leaving Chicago and was super excited. It was 5pm and they close at 6pm. I ordered a large and a medium bag. I was really disappointed, the caramel ones were really good but the cheddar popcorn was so stale, I couldn't eat it. Maybe it was just a bad day, or maybe I need to come earlier.

A friend knew I was going to Chicago and asked me to bring back some popcorn. I decided to get some for myself and wow! The kids tasted and I almost loss my popcorn, they said “ you couldn’t have got a bigger bag”? This popcorn melted in your mouth delicious! They better be glad I shared. Can you say online order please. Yes! It was fantastic glad my friend got me to stop by there.

The line was a decent length at 12:30pm on a Tuesday. There 10 people in front of us and it tus about 5-10 minutes to place our order.
I ordered the caramel crisp and it was super tasty.
Quick service, friendly staff members, clean and welcoming, delicious popcorn…as expected…Garrett’s never fails.

formatted_address: 660 N Wells St, Chicago, IL 60610, USA
name: Original Hooters

reviews.text:
nice and the food was great, which I truly appreciated as I was out celebrating myself. However, I did run into an issue that put a damper on the experience. I arrived at 2:50 p.m. hoping to take advantage of the 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. lunch special. After waiting about 5–6 minutes for a hostess with no one greeting me, I realized time was running out. Wanting to ensure I made the cut-off, I approached a kind young lady named Jan who was taking to-go orders and asked if I could place a dine-in order instead.

At exactly 3:00 p.m., I attempted to order the boneless chicken and shrimp specials, each priced at $9.99. Jan, who was very courteous and tried to assist, asked her manager Jasmine if it would be okay to honor the special given the circumstances. Unfortunately, the answer was a firm “no.” I was genuinely surprised and disappointed by that response. Had I been greeted and seated in a timely manner, I would have been well within the time window to place my order.

Despite that, I decided to stay and dine in. However, I ended up waiting an additional 13 minutes without anyone coming by to take my order. Several employees walked past me, but no one acknowledged me. Considering I had also paid for parking to enjoy what was meant to be a celebratory meal, it felt disheartening to be overlooked like that.

I do want to highlight and applaud the efforts of Jan and Roz—both of whom were very kind and professional. Roz, in particular, was extremely pleasant once she finally came over. This review is in no way a reflection on their service, but rather on how the situation was handled by management.

Because of how things unfolded, I will be reaching out to corporate to share my experience in more detail. I hope this feedback can be used constructively so that others don’t encounter similar issues.

Can't go wrong with this classic popped in for a late lunch so no surprised the service was lacking but the food and drinks were surprisingly good. I will def be back to check if the service is better later.  If your close pop in for some surprisingly good food. The chef makes this place since the staff was mia.

Always a pleasure to visit a Hooters. Visited this Sports bar twice in a week. Friendly staff and quick service by a friendly Bennett. And a couple of great beers on draft. And very good cocktails as well. They also have a nice food menu. Their chicken wings and Philly Cheese Steak are great.

I hate to say it, but I call who the girls how I see it. Sometimes the Hooters girls  are good for nothing but looking pretty everything you ask them sometimes they don’t know anything about. They just stand there and look dumbfounded, but needless to say I do still enjoy the environment and the food and the drinks. And they charged me way too much money for that little non-alcoholic drink. Updated on Fat Tuesday 2025 : the more and more I go to hooters the more and more I look at them definitely! The Hooter girls looked a little rough and acted like it too… as if they didn’t even want to be at work! I got an email saying they where celebrating Fat Tuesday… and I was more dressed up for the event then they where.

HORRIBLE HORRIBLE! Everything about this place was HORRIBLE!
1. Table had for sure not been properly wiped or cleaned. Was very sticky and had food crumbs all over it. Entire place had 11 customers (with 7 visible employees) and yet somehow we sat and waited for 15 minutes to be acknowledged.
2. 2 separate groups of people (a group of 4 and separate group of 3 BOTH of which arrived at least 15 minutes AFTER us but somehow received their food WAY before me and my guest)
3. Waited approximately 15 minutes for a beer to arrive and an additional 25 minutes for a small order of wings and crab legs (AFTER 2 other groups that ordered their food 15-20 minutes after we did and somehow received their larger orders WAY before us)
4. FINALLY got our food (crab legs, fries and 10 boneless wings) with no offer of ANY silverware or even an offer of water and were disgusted by the sight of it. (Please see photos)
The glass of lemonade had chunks of 'something' floating in it (was NOT pieces of lemon) and there were black spots all over the cup it was in, the cup of 'butter' that came with the crab was utterly disgusting. It had a brown substance at the bottom of the cup and appeared to have been sitting around for a long time (by no means was fresh or even looked to have been prepared that day!) The boneless wings were sitting in a pool of grease and even worse some yellow-ish substance was floating on top of that!
5. 2 of the boneless wings contained no chicken.  It was just a mass of greasy fried breaded nothing!
6. Then to top off a horrible dining experience, had to wait forever to get our check. By this point, there were still only about 10 other people in the place and at least 7 employees.

Our experience lasted well into the night and unfortunately the morning as we both suffered lengthy "stomach related issues".
How is it possible for a staff of a food establishment be so lacking of ability, common sense, knowledge of food handling and health code laws and  procedures, and training?  Absolutely unacceptable on so many levels. Zero stars ALL around.

formatted_address: 8345 W North Ave Store 1-7A, Melrose Park, IL 60160, USA
name: Subway

reviews.text: Sandwich was pretty good, but when I asked to use the washroom to wash my hands, I was told the washroom was broken.  5 mins later the owner or friend of the owner walks in and went directly to washroom.  After asking a second time to use the washroom they lied again and said it wasn't working. After I told them 2 ladies were just in there, they reluctanty let me in to wash my hands.  and guess what!!!!  The toilet was working just fine!!  Wonder if the health dept knows you dont let customers use the washroom?!?

Put in an online order. Through a fluke issue (power outage) the system ate it. Fair enough, life happens.  Reason for the bad review is because after talking with the franchise owner multiple times on the phone they couldn't cancel/refund the order and our only recourse was to put in a new order and wait for the previous one to be refunded (and if it wasn't then to drive back). Additionally, after the second order was put in (and confirmed within seconds) we were made to wait while multiple other customers came in behind us but were given priority and had their food made first. Arguably the worst service I've ever received anywhere at any restaurant.

My wife stopped there on her way home to get a tuna sub. She has the subway App and had enough points to get $3 off, they would not take the points. In the past I have gone there and they wouldn't let me use any coupons or points. Stay away from this particular Subway. If you're going to own a franchise you should honor any promotions coupons and points programs that the franchise offers.
The customer service was in good and they were rude. To The customer. she was act like they don’t care about the business
I love this sandwich shop it’s open 24/7 which is great because I work 3rd shift. Not a lot of healthy food open 24/7  Place does start to get busy around 2:15AM but your out less then 5 minutes

formatted_address: 2720 N River Rd, River Grove, IL 60171, USA
name: Gene & Jude's

reviews.text: A staple that knows what they are doing and doesn't change. They serve the line faster than any place I have ever seen. The fries are delicious, but let's be real you are there for the dogs. I got the double and loaded it up. I wouldn't change a thing. This is simply one of the best dogs you can find.

These ratings are Joke!!!

They took my order and made me wait 15 minutes while serving at least 20 others ahead of me. Some people literally left because they ran out of food. Should’ve just gone to Costco—at least there you get value for your money.

This hot dog? A 5cm joke. Super thin, tasteless, and honestly you can see the second bite already in my photo—that’s how tiny it was. Fries were just… fine. The only thing that had any flavor here was the fake attitude of “we do hot dogs and fries.” Yeah, you do. Barely.

Wouldn’t come back even if it were free.

I enjoy trying local spots food while traveling. This is a must stop if you're in the Chicago area. This meal is simple yet so flavorful and delicious. Their homemade fries are perfect and need nothing added but a pinch of salt. Bring cash and experience a one of a kind!

Stop by for some fries because I heard they were freshly cut. Well they were cut fresh and fried with onions. They were a little soft for me but I would ask them to double fry mines the next time. Still was some good fries.

Legendary Chicago Hot Dog Spot! Mandatory On the way to or from the airport. Very simple yet tasty hot dog! One of the juiciest hot dogs and the soggy fries on top actually enhance the experience. Saw a Bald Eagle flying over the river while I ate a hot dog on the trunk of my friends car and was arguably one of the most American moments I have ever experienced in my life. 1000% Recommendation for a Hot Dog in Chicago.

formatted_address: 6363 N Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60646, USA
name: Superdawg Drive-In

reviews.text: Really a great Chicago stop. Fun to order through the retro boxes or walk up to the window. Chicago dogs and burgers with delicious fries and ice cream. Make sure if you don't like relish to  ask not to have it put on your burger. It was a surprise lmao.

I came here the other day to get my birthday freebie (a free large drink and supersandwich) and it was great! I really enjoyed the drive-in vibes.
My mom and I were a bit confused on how to order, but thankfully the staff and customers were friendly and helped. We got the superdawg, whoopskidawg, and a large lemonade. The wait wasn't super long and the food was nice and fresh!
The superdawg was a well-made and delicious chicago style hotdog and the whoopskidawg was really good; I loved the 'special sauce' (it tasted like BBQ)! Both of the meals came with fries as well. The prices aren't horrible (~$10 per supersandwhich) considering the supersandwiches come with fries.
Overall, I would definetly recommend this for a cool drive-in restaraunt!

The Superdawg is such a meaty hotdog, you will certainly be satisfied with all the trimmings on top... and the crispy, crinkled fries that surround it. Try the pineapple shake; the chunks of fruit are so substantial many won't fit through the straw. I now realize that I failed to include a photo of the hotdog by itself. It smelled so good and my appetite got the best of me. Before I could take a picture of it, it was gone.

It was a fantastic place to eat! First place I stopped after I got to Chicago! I had always heard about it! The covered parking, the order menus! The food was delicious! Very glad I stopped! Well worth it! Highly Recommend!

Iconic Hot dog stand. Got the super dawg & the super veggies I would rate them both 8.5/10. I didn't understand the monitors where you park. Not sure if they worked or not.. So I parked and walked inside.

formatted_address: 8832 W Dempster St, Niles, IL 60714, USA
name: Portillo's & Barnelli's Niles

reviews.text: The inside of this location was very cool. Easy to find as well. No waiting. Multiple kiosks to order from if you're into that. Restroom clean. Beef sandwich great. Chili dog great. My first time to a Portillos.

Loved the place. Being from Alabama, we usually smother everything with cheese, but this meal had so much flavor that it was amazing as is!! The experience was great with the decor of different historical pictures as well as random family ones. The food quality had flavor but not overly greasy. Extremely impressed with this! Keep up the great work!!

Tried my first Chicago hot dog at Portillo’s. I wasn’t expecting anything out of the world, but I have to admit I truly enjoyed the food. I got a hot dog and a steak sandwich both were great.

I never had a hot dog with tomatoes and a pickle spear but it was great. I recommend getting it with everything on it to get the true experience. I enjoyed the poppy seed bun as well. I’m sure there are better options but as a fast food joint, they did a great job. I would definitely go back.

The beef sandwich was really good as well. I never had a whole sandwich dunked in jus before. But on a cold day it warmed my soul. I can see why locals like it how it’s served. I got mine with a sweet pepper, which actually tasted good on its own.

I would recommend my friends to try Portillo’s as a place to get a bite of Chicago without having to travel from one side of town to the other. Fast and convenient fare.

A great place to get a good Chicago dog.

I came with a friend after being told for years to how cool portillo's was. I was not prepared for how overwhelming it was with its character in charm.

We ordered some Chicago dogs, some fries and milkshakes.

The Chicago dogs were really good. Not the best weiner in the world, but everything else about the dog was good.

The fries were good. Love me some crinkle fries.

The milkshakes each use an entire slice of chocolate cake for them. What could go wrong? Honestly, it was one of the best milkshakes I've ever had. Everything else was just good.

I would absolutely recommend portillo's in a heartbeat. I think if you're in the Chicago area you owe yourself to check them out. If not, just for the audacity of the place.

The food is always satisfying here! I had the single cheeseburger and my family had the Penne Ala Vodka, Mostaccioli with 1 meatball, Fettuccine Alfredo and a jumbo chili hotdog! My favorite was the Penne Ala Vodka, it had a lot of flavor and the perfect amount of sauce! At this location, there were quite a few kiosks that you can just order on your own without waiting in line! The food came pretty fast! I will always go back and try others!

formatted_address: 352 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Protein Bar & Kitchen

reviews.text: Great selection of healthy options – it’s hard not to eat healthy with this place around. The salad was really fresh and tasty, and the keto coffee was a nice bonus. Particularly like the self-ordering kiosk, and the food came out super fast!

Smoothies were really good and tasted fresh.
The wrap was a bit dry and a lot less flavor than anticipated.

Clean and quiet place.
I made a build your own salad and it was great. The ingredients tasted fresh and the dressing was tasty. I got a green smoothie on the side and it was the cherry on top.

Tried PBK for the first time a couple of weeks ago (our office moved in across the street recently) and have been back multiple times since. We order group lunches from here as well.  REALLY enjoying their bowls and wraps! The portions are "just right", the food has a lot of flavor and I really appreciate that it's as healthy as it's possible for fast food to be. I'm having fun trying things I've bever had before. The service is excellent as well. Everyone is friendly, fast and all of our orders have been accurate. Highly recommend.
Fit Mint and PB&J! Great spot, fresh made while you wait, give it a try.

formatted_address: 3101 N Sheffield Ave #1, Chicago, IL 60657, USA
name: Matilda

reviews.text: I had an amazing experience thanks to Nelly, our server! She was incredibly friendly, attentive, and made us feel so welcome from the moment we sat down. She got every order right, gave great recommendations, and checked in at just the right times. Her positive attitude and professionalism really stood out and made our meal even better. Thank you, Nelly, for the outstanding service!

Real nice place. Especially if you’re a Michigan Alum. It’s the Michigan Alumni bar! I’m a Spartan, and still give this a 5 star, GO Green!  It’s cool spot and ambiance and nice outdoor seating with good food!
Taco Tuesday is a great deal, their burger is char-grilled, and the tiki drinks are well-balanced and delicious! I especially loved the fresh oregano in the salsa on my fish taco.

i love it here. i’ve been here a few times just going out and had the absolute best experience here. But i recently celebrated my birthday at back bar and i couldn’t recommend jt enough. Matilda staff made the cutest custom cocktail menu, let us decorate, and we’re all and all so accommodating. The bartenders here are so fun and such a vibe. all of our guests has nothing but positive things to say. 10/10 experience !! thank you matilda’s !!!

(also we ordered food and it was gas)
Well executed pub food. Pretzel is exceptional. Cheese curds are perfect. Solid wings. Great lighting and interior. Fast and courteous service. Perfect spot if you're heading to or leaving the Vic.

formatted_address: 3303 W Touhy Ave, Lincolnwood, IL 60712, USA
name: Olive Garden Italian Restaurant

reviews.text: Great service and meals, got the never ending soup salad breadsticks and the soup was filled with vegetables, the bread sticks were soft and fresh and the salad was arranged neatly. Only thing I wasn't a fan of was how close the next seat was to me it was just separated by a sort of thin half wall, I wish it was higher or had some sort of covering or plants blocking it. The server was absolutely nice and quick with things and I had the best experience I've ever had at a olive Garden.

I would rate them 0 if an option!

I came in with my sister-in-law and brother, who is diabetic, and approached Julia, one of the servers—a skinny blonde.
I politely asked if she could start with my brother due to his condition, whenever she had a moment. However, when she came to our table to take the order, her attitude was really unpleasant. I suggested that if she didn’t want to serve us, she could call someone else to avoid a bad day for all of us. We ordered food and drinks, but she only brought the mineral water instead of the regular. When we asked for the regular water, she took the glasses away angrily and left.

Larry, the restaurant manager, ( with experience of 21 years ) approached our table in an even ruder manner, claiming Julia was upset because we asked her to come to us and that we haven’t placed our order with her, He said he wouldn’t tolerate that. I tried to explain that I approached her while she was in the hallway and I am sure cameras can show that if necessary , but he raised his voice and wouldn’t let me speak.
Also he claimed that we haven’t order our food and were expecting to eat ? Then I clearly said we placed our order with Julia S, she even brought our water to the table.

I will never return to this place, and I genuinely hope these individuals find jobs they love, where customers aren’t subjected to a negative experience just because they’re having a bad day or because are short staffed. They ruined my day and made me not eat.

Additionally we were not served by the unpleasant attitude  lady.  We were served by Larry and look on our receipt.  Says Julia S was our server.  ( the one we have placed order initially and lied that we haven’t placed the order)

I recommend 0 Starts for everything in this place.  !!! Staff,  Atmosphere ,  and makes you not wanna eat !!

We visit Olive Garden all the time but today it was a less than perfect experience on my birthday:

Food: I ordered the 14.99 never ending pasta bowl for 14.99 thinking it was going to come with meatballs discovered the meatballs were extra.

It’s not never ending until you eat all of the sugary pasta. I was given a bowl of meat sauce as a refill instead.

Service was okay. The server Roeup R. Aka “smiley face” and deceitful by charging us twice for food pretending it was a mistake. When you do things like this it puts a bad taste in customer’s mouths.

Atmosphere: okay atmosphere, you can barely read the menu because the lights are so low and the bussers are noisy.

Went there for a birthday dinner.  Was surprised that between 5:30PM and 6:00PM they were already getting busy, families were coming in and saw some waiting to be seated. We made a reservation and I am glad I did. Pleasant ambiance, good food, and decent menu selection. The complimentary birthday cake was superb.. Chocolate Brownie Lasagna. A huge thanks to our server, Mary.  Will definitely go back preferable during lunch time. Their lunch menu is reasonably priced. Dinner entree come with the soup or salad, and Breadsticks.

My best friend and I went to this restaurant recently and really enjoyed the food. Our server Julia was incredibly attentive and on point with her service. She kept our drinks refilled without us even having to ask, which was so appreciated. The meal was delicious and the service from Julia made the whole experience that much better. We'll definitely be back!

formatted_address: 938 W Webster Ave, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: Homeslice Pizza + Patio

reviews.text: We had a nice time at Homeslice. We went in on a Saturday evening and the place was busy and lively. Decor was very welcoming. My friends got the "figgy it in" pizza and I got the Kale Cashew salad. Food was incredibly tasty. Service was on-spot. It was a little too loud and having a conversation was hard but I'd highly recommend the place.

Loved the outdoor space in back by the L tracks. The Pizza on the other hand was absolutely inedible. I must say it was a vegan friendly crust and dairy free cheese pizza due to allergies (dairy), but it was just gross. No flavor and dry, like eating cardboard. I'm pretty sure not even fully cooked in the center. Seemed like some frozen type pizza, a really really bad one. Most annoying part was there were extra fees for each of these substitutions, $3 extra for special crust $2 extra for the special cheese. Sadly the server didn't offer to take anything off the bill. Staff was friendly, but should've really offer more than just a "I'm sorry". I was told by my dinner guest the burger wasn't that good either, so I guessing it's not just an allergy free food issue. Go for drinks and atmosphere, skip the food.

This place was bustling on a Saturday evening! Always a good sign for a pizza spot on the weekend. The decor was cute. They have Christmas lights hung from the ceiling, and it creates a nice mood. I had a reservation for 2 and my friend was running late but they seated me anyway.

I appreciated that they had seasonal cocktails. However, none of them had tequila as the alcohol choice, bummer. I was told that it could be substituted in, so that's what I did. There was definitely an upcharge to substitute. Also, our waiter was under 21 so she didn't know a few things when asked about drinks. She offered to have someone come over.

The Mercenary pizza was so good. I didn't know what to expect, but it exceeded the expectations. The drink was ok. Not the best and not the worst.

All in all a pleasant experience. My biggest complaint was the closeness of the tables. Geesh! That wouldn't stop me from going again l, though. The pizza is worth the trip.
Had brunch here for Mother’s Day and the mix of outdoor and indoor seating was great! Service was excellent and food was delicious. Will definitely come back again soon

My go-to spot for a good slice. Staff is always incredible. I love seeing Catherine and Olivia in the front and it's always a pleasure to be served by the beautiful Georgia!! Satisfies the triple entente—great service, great ambiance, and great food.

formatted_address: 86 Yorktown Shopping Center, Lombard, IL 60148, USA
name: Olive Garden Italian Restaurant

reviews.text:
entrees come with breadsticks and choice of soup or salad. Unlimited soup and salad

Got the Marsala chicken and the meatball + spaghetti (customized). Each dish was good for one adult and kid.

It has been years since we’ve been to an Olive Garden, especially with new restaurants popping up often. We decided to come here after shopping at the Yorktown Mall and I was in the mood for pasta. Parking lot was plentiful. We were seated right away. Our server was very attentive and pleasant. She went above and beyond. This location is also very clean. The unlimited breadsticks are a good deal but even after all these years, they still don't hit me the same way that Fazoli’s did. Fazoli’s has the best breadsticks hands down. Too bad they have very few locations. Prices are reasonable because portion sizes are very generous.

-chicken and gnocchi 5 -well balanced soup with chicken, dumplings, and spinach.
-minestrone 5 -just tastes like regular minestrone.
-lasagna fritta 5 - this is great for lasagna lovers. This is basically fried lasagna with parmesan cheese and meat sauce on top. Delicious.
-ravioli carbonara 4 - I love ravioli but the sauce was a little salty. I loved all of the bacon and cheeses that went into it.
-shrimp carbonara 5 - they added a ton of shrimp in here. No complaints.

Excellent experience if you adjust for price. If you expect filet in your Steak Gorgonzola, well, you may not be happy. The dish was good, but the beef was bit tough and definitely thoroughly cooked. Manny was serving and tending bar and had a solid upbeat personality. Rating based on value, and $22 for the dish is definitely worth the investment.

An Italian chain of restaurants.
The location we visited has a new design. Looks like it was built not that long ago.
The restaurant has a separate room JUST for carry outs!!!
