Majority of the tables weren’t cleaned up. I counted at least 4-5 unbussed tables until I got seated.
Our waitress was so lovely and carrying. She made sure that all of our needs and wants were taken care of momentarily. And made our stay nice and comfortable.
The food is pretty decent for a chain restaurant.
Toscana soup was our favorite dish!!! Creamy, with a spicy kick.  ( I’m so glad we got a couple to-go as well)

P.s thank you for an unforgettable experience, ms waitress. We’ll be back for more breadsticks and Toscana soups :)

Olive Garden continues to impress! The service was warm, friendly, and attentive from the moment we walked in. Our meals were served hot and full of flavor — exactly what you want in a comforting pasta dish. The staff made us feel welcome and well taken care of throughout the entire experience. Great service and delicious food make this location a go-to spot for a satisfying Italian meal.

formatted_address: 7513 Cermak Rd, North Riverside, IL 60546, USA
name: Olive Garden Italian Restaurant

reviews.text: Service was a little slow for pickup...but it's something about olive garden when you haven't eaten it in an extremely long time!  So delicious 😋. I forgot how much I loved the little candy too! Whoever came up with the dipping sauce deserves a raise!

This Olive Garden has always been one of our go-to spots for me and my kids who love coming here! The food is consistently delicious, the atmosphere is warm and welcoming, and it’s always been a great place for families.

On our most recent visit, we were pleasantly surprised to find out that the manager is actually a client of mine! She went above and beyond to take extra care of us, which made the experience even more special. That said, even before we made that connection, we’ve always had wonderful service and enjoyable meals here.

Big thanks to the entire team—and especially the manager Samantha for making Olive Garden feel like a second home for our family. We’ll definitely keep coming back!
Nice meal and drinks and our waiter had like 5 tables so when we got him, we made sure to tell him everything we needed and it worked out perfectly.

Went on my birthday. They served my daughter undercooked chicken, making her feel a bit sick the rest of the day. They ran out of some of take home meals too, didn't offer refills, and...honestly, I'd add more but why bother. You don't serve kids undercooked chicken. It's that easy.

I’ve been to Olive Garden plenty of times. Always have great service and portions. This time the portions were very small compared to before. I called Thursday to make a reservation 4/27/25 at 4pm for a party of ten. I get there at four and I told the girl named Alyssa I believe that I had a reservation, she didn’t even bother asking me for the name and proceeded to tell me it would be a ten to twenty minute wait. We go back in at 4:20 after waiting outside I told her another girl in all black not sure what was her name that we were back for the party of ten and she said I would have to wait another ten minutes therefore I got mad because I told her there’s no way I’m waiting a whole 30 minutes if I made sure to make a reservation to prevent the wait. I proceeded to tell her I had a reservation and spoke directly to the host about my reservation and that’s when she finally checks and sees my name, phone number, and how many we were. I also notified her how I spoke to the Alyssa girl and she proceeded to say no she hadn’t spoken to me and that it was my fault because I hadn’t left a name. Finally at 4:35 my party of ten was seated. Then the server would only come to take orders and give us food and didn’t care enough to check up on us as frequent as I’d appreciate especially after a whole 35 minute wait. I decided to play a to go order also. I go to the to go area, once I arrive it’s three works and I told them I was for a pick up one of them is on the phone taking an order and the second one told me to wait and the other one was just there and they’re all giggling and after like 3-5 mins later the other girl is still on the phone and they’re second one that was just standing there finally took me to pick my food up. an absolute waste of time whoever runs this place better get there staff in check!

formatted_address: 303 E Wacker Dr Suite C-09, Chicago, IL 60601, USA
name: Dunkin'

reviews.text: The location at this address was not visible. May be location closed.
I have been a regular customer at dunkin, for a very long time.  Coffee ☕️, food ,etc.  Always, good.

The worst Dunkin in the world.
Ordered a medium  and they only give me 1 shot of the flavor! Or just one shot of the cream and sugar.
I have to tell them Everytime that it is 3 shots for a medium. If you don’t tell them they will only put 1 shot.

5 stars is based off of other Dunkin experiences.
Really impressed by how nice and fast the service was.
The hot chocolate was terrific!
Nice to have prices not be crazy high like other coffee shops in the city.

Single handedly the worst Dunkin in the city. They burn everything. Online orders only work half the time they never do anything for you when they don’t. The only reason I come here is because I work here and would never otherwise because I genuinely hate having to  get refunds for orders that went through and for some reason they never receive. And getting burnt sandwiches when they do work is no prize.

formatted_address: 1141 S Jefferson St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: Manny's Cafeteria & Delicatessen

reviews.text: Had an awesome breakfast here this morning! I ordered the corn beef hash with scrambled eggs and French toast on the side. I also tried their famous potato pancake (which was incredible). The restaurant was super clean, the staff were friendly and helpful and the food came fast, hot and was delicious. If you’re ever in the area and need a hearty breakfast, I highly recommend you stop by Manny’s 😊👍

After living in Chicago for over 15 years, I finally made it to this amazing institution. I had the reuben with corned beef and it is well worth the price. The portions are generous and the selections on the menu have you making tough decisions because there's so much you want. The staff is wonderful and very personable. Definitely a spot you need to visit if you are visiting Chicago.

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Manny's Cafeteria & Delicatessen it truly exceeded my expectations. From the moment I walked in, the atmosphere was inviting and vibrant, setting the perfect tone for a delightful meal. The decor was tastefully done, creating a warm and welcoming environment that made me feel right at home.

The menu offered an impressive variety of dishes, catering to a range of palates and preferences. Each option was thoughtfully crafted, ensuring that there was something for everyone. I decided to try a few different items, and I was blown away by the flavors and presentation. Every bite was a testament to the chef's creativity and skill.

What truly stood out during my visit was the exceptional customer service. The staff was attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable about the menu, making recommendations that enhanced the dining experience. They were always ready to assist without being intrusive, which added to the overall enjoyment of the meal.

In conclusion, this restaurant is a gem that combines great food variety, outstanding service, and a fantastic atmosphere. I left feeling satisfied and eager to return for another visit. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a memorable dining experience!

This place is great. They serve decent breakfast food in a classic cafeteria/diner environment. It all makes sense. The plates are not huge (which I think removes the need for a 2 person breakfast to be $50), but the food is decent and satisfying. I reckon make the breakfast plates $10 each! Then I’d come back. Feels like they’re playing both sides at the moment having a cafeteria setting with such high prices. French toast looks good, wish I’d got it.

This restaurant is not kosher, despite appearing to be Jewish.
Pastrami was excellent! Thinly sliced and juicy.
Chicken soup is made from bouillon.
Knish was bland.
Rugelah from the bakery was tiny and dense, rather than puffy like they should be.
Overall, I would come back for a pastrami sandwich.

formatted_address: 1079 W Taylor St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: Al's #1 Italian Beef

reviews.text: We had to try Italian beef before we were in Chicago and ours was our first choice! There’s not much left, unfortunately, it’s a little Italy at this point because of the college that built in the middle of that area. But, the food here was amazing, even if the building needs a bit of touching up.Don’t expect fancy, but come with an appetite.

Italian beef in little Italy.  Very cool part of town. Small cozy place. Folks working there are nice . I went early, so no line. Got a regular Italian beef with hot peppers, Gravy on the side.  Sandwich was good. They even have some parking spots.

The Italian beef didn’t have no seasoning. The fries were good, but I had to ask for salt and the customer service was poor. They were not friendly. But the sandwich looked good but it’s not good so that’s what tricked me and the black Foodie couple said that they were good. And I bought a meal and the total cost was like $19 a waste of my money and my time I drove all the way from Villa Park 55 minutes. Personally, I need a refund.

Been eating at this location for over 30 years! Today my hotdog was dry and condiments were scarce. The fries were overcooked and only a handful. I’m extremely disappointed for my cousin taking a 40 min ride for mediocre food! This used to be the best location! Hate I took a few bites before taking a photo. The Italian beef was decent!

Not much to add here from the Tinley Park write-up; but I had to visit the original location in Little Italy.

The beef is super tasty and this giardeneria is tops when it comes to pickling, heat and flavor.  The soft peppery beef is perfect on the gonella-like roll.

Chicago is very lucky to have so many fantastic italian beef spots, try the ones a little bit out of your neighborhood.

formatted_address: 500 W Madison St Suite F-015, Chicago, IL 60661, USA
name: Sbarro

reviews.text: The Italian Sausage, Peppers and Onions are a must at this location! They are pretty quick during the lunch rush and the customer service is A+.

Unlike the bad reviews, the pizza was very tasty and fresh. The owner was really nice and help us to get what we want. He also offered to try their unique Stromboli and I am glad he did. Reasonable price for tasty food when you are in rush to catch your train.

I stopped at Sbarro late one evening after getting off a train. I was served quickly. the prices are reasonable and the pizza silices are very good. the space to sit next to it is nice. I therefore recommend.
Ordered food here & it never came!! Also they never answer the phone how does that work?!

When you ask what's in something trying to confirm if it's just what the ingredient it's sold as. Spinach and mushroom but it also has red pepper flakes in it. That's really bad. It's hurting me Thanks. Also a 50 cent credit card charge is awful

formatted_address: 130 E Randolph St, Chicago, IL 60601, USA
name: Panda Express

reviews.text:
Would have preferred visiting with spouse. Got here after busiest hours, clean but no restroom for diners.
No disabled access button to enter or exit despite panda express popularity.
They have workers but not many options like normal. This is all they've been doing for the past few days, y'all got to do better 🤦🏾

Orange chicken was not good today. Instead of pieces of chicken I received blobs of chicken. I assume when they fried it they just threw it in not caring whether it all stuck together. Good thing I had a knife at my office to cut it apart. Much better at the one at 520 N. Michigan Ave.

Came in at 3:45pm, the store is supposed to close at 5:00pm, and there was barely any food made. Roughly five trays of food were cooked at the time of arrival. The worker rolled her eyes when we asked to still get food. Not very impressed

The food was fresh and it tasted really good. Very good portions compared to other Panda Express stores. The staff is also very friendly and welcoming. Also, being close to Millenium Park means you can enjoy your food with a view.

formatted_address: 381 Brookview Ln, Bolingbrook, IL 60440, USA
name: Golden Corral Buffet & Grill

reviews.text: The food was horrific. it looked like it was old and dried out tasteless. The place was old and not very clean. I did not enjoy my visit. I will never go back again. Yuck 🤮 my clean-up person who cleared the table after each plate was wonderful. She was very nice and polite and helpful 👍🏾 thank you Maria for your service. 😊  you save the day
The pozole is very tasty. The burrerfly shrimp is big.
Friendly staff and lunch time is the best time to go.

I am a vegetarian and I was not expecting much from a buffet restaurant, but I was pleasantly surprised by the variety and quality of the food at Golden Corral. They had a lot of options for vegetarians, such as salads, soups, pasta, rice, beans, and even some meatless dishes. The food was fresh, tasty, and well-prepared. I especially enjoyed the cheese pizza.

The service was also excellent. Our waiter, Ulyses, was very attentive, friendly, and helpful. He checked on us frequently, refilled our drinks, and cleared our plates.

I would definitely recommend Golden Corral to anyone looking for a satisfying and affordable meal, whether they are vegetarian or not. It was a great experience and I will be coming back soon.

The food was good, unfortunately I was served by an unprofessional waiter, in the entire hour we were eating he only came over once to offer us more drinks, he took too long to clear the plates until the pile was noticeable, it was just me and my son… From the moment we sat down we noticed the difference in attention he gave to the other diners and the great lack of empathy when serving us. I took my son to the bathroom and when we came back the waiter had cleaned the table, took away plates with food, drinks and utensils, assuming we had already finished… we took less than 3 minutes in the bathroom… coincidence? I am leaving this place with great desire, it was my son's favorite place 🥲

formatted_address: 2361 Fountain Square Dr, Lombard, IL 60148, USA
name: P.F. Chang's

reviews.text: The food looks amazing but everything tastes sweet.. hot and sour soup was good.. the brown rice was super dry ..even pad Thai was kind of sweet ..where is the spice :(

The food and service wasn’t that great. The food looked good but tasted bland, you’re better off buying from an authentic local Chinese restaurant. Also, there were barely any customers yet the service wasn’t that great, the server took 15 minutes to bring drinks and forgot to put one in. It seemed like the server didn’t care about my table as the table next to mine got better service. Additionally, their menus aren’t that clean, they’re very sticky. If you like their food you’re better off going to the Schaumburg location.

Serafina was really nice and attentive, and made sure we had a great experience dining. The food was great! We always love the dynamite shrimp. Finished off our lunch with a delicious banana spring roll dessert.

Great atmosphere including red and black themed interior, oriental decor, and attractive centerpieces. Seating area is large & roomy, but not the most comfortable or updated dining area. Food is tasty but can be excessive with oil usage, a little tricky to use tap to pay feature dining in.

This establishment has always been a great go to for me went last night. They had a really great deal going on for $20 per person. You each get your own entrée you split an appetizer and you get a soup or salad will definitely return

formatted_address: 8225 W Higgins Rd, Chicago, IL 60631, USA
name: Hooters

reviews.text:
I had one of the worst dining experiences I’ve ever had at this Hooters location. The manager, Antonio, was shockingly unprofessional — instead of addressing a concern I had, he became visibly irritated and got rude with me, as if I was a burden rather than a customer. Completely unacceptable behavior from someone in a leadership role.

To make matters worse, our waitress seemed totally disinterested in providing decent service. She kept scratching her scalp with her long acrylic nails (which is incredibly off-putting when you’re about to eat), and literally threw the plates on our table like she couldn’t care less.

The food was no better. The chicken wings were greasy, soggy, and cold — completely unappetizing and far from what you’d expect from a restaurant that claims to specialize in wings.

The whole experience felt chaotic, unhygienic, and honestly, like they just didn’t care. Antonio and the staff need serious training in professionalism, hygiene, and basic customer service.

I don’t leave many bad reviews, but this visit deserves it. I won’t be coming back, and I wouldn’t recommend this location to anyone.

Always a pleasant experience when I order for pick up. My order is always ready on time when I arrive & the ladies are professional & friendly. Great experience in and out. I’ve also dined inside with some friends & it was also a great experience. Usually my order is the honey Thai wings very tasty! Curly fries, tater totes are fantastic. Food is never cold & drinks are perfect. Great atmosphere, won’t regret visiting this restaurant.

Absolutely terrible experience at Hooters. From the moment I walked in, it was clear this place was a mess. The restaurant was dirty — sticky tables, garbage on the floor, and the whole place smelled like it hadn’t been cleaned properly in weeks.

Then came the staff. The waitress was incredibly rude, acted like we were bothering her just by being there, and got our order wrong. When we tried to get it fixed, she rolled her eyes and gave us attitude. And don’t even get me started on Manager Antonio — completely unprofessional and dismissive. When we voiced our concerns, he barely listened, offered no apology, and acted like we were the problem.

And the food? Disgusting. The wings were soggy, greasy, and tasted old. Definitely not fresh, and honestly I’m surprised they’re even serving that kind of low-quality food.

I don’t usually leave reviews, but this place deserves to be called out. Waste of money, waste of time. Never going back. Save yourself the headache and go literally anywhere else.

Not bad but not great either. Service wasn't overly friendly and the building seemed like it had seen better days. The margarita was pretty small given its price! Fries were great and burger was fine, although I wish I got wings now. Wings seem to be what you get when you're at a Hooters.

We waited 35minutes for a table because the wings at hooters are so delicious.

Great service, cold beer and fantastic wings. What more can you ask for....

formatted_address: 17W280 W 22nd St, Oakbrook Terrace, IL 60181, USA
name: Giordano's

reviews.text:
Fast, friendly and attentive staff. Helpful and informative.

The food was hot and amazing. The cheese pull on our pizza was amazing. Tried to get good videos of it but it didn't work out, still had an amazing time trying and enjoying the atmosphere.

The drinks we got were perfect too. Priced just right and made with perfection.

Definitely amazing deep dish pizza 🍕😋

A GEM OF CHICAGO! Amazing pizza, both the deep dish pepperoni & the chicken bacon alfredo thin crust. There was a bit of a wait for the food, but it came out warm and fresh!!! Would definitely recommend for those visiting Chicago 😊
First time... Wanted to try some Chicago style pizza. I was not disappointed! Did a build your own, with meats, as well a caeser salad. Both were great!

My sister and her husband did a road trip through Chicago and had dinner at this location. They had a great time, their chicken and mushroom pizza was delicious and they had really good service. They ordered 2 frozen pies to go for me to try. If it was just a regular cheese pizza, I would give it 5 stars as the pizza was delicious. Following the instructions, the crust was baked to a nice golden brown and flaky. The sauce is very flavorful and not too sweet. The mozzarella cheese is of really good quality and came out nice and gooey. Unfortunately the box I opened and was excited for was the pepperoni pizza and as you can see from the photos, there was only 1 pepperoni. I guess technically that does count 😅. It was missed during the final check before being sealed. I'm sure the unopened cheese pizza will be just as delicious.

*Edit - The owner replied which goes to show their outstanding customer service. I gave the benefit of the doubt at first thinking the pepperoni was going to be inside the pizza maybe under the sauce or cheese so I baked it. My uncertainty became a realization once I cut the slices and found no pepperoni.

First time at this location with my wife and sister!
We were seated immediately and our order was taken shortly after.
The restaurant has a nice reddish ambiance.

We ordered the following items:
- Deep Dish Pizza ( Half Cheese/Half Veggies)
- Calamari
- Cheesy Garlic Bread
- Root Beer Float

The calamari is not that good would not recommend, the cheesy garlic bread was ok, Root beer float was good, and last but the least the deep dish pizza which was good.

formatted_address: 216 W Jackson Blvd, Chicago, IL 60606, USA
name: Jimmy John's

reviews.text: This Jimmy John’s location looks a little run down, but it fits in a run down area of downtown Chicago! I was in a huge rush, and this location lives up to their reputation of being freakishly fast. That’s what I needed and I got an “as expected” Jimmy John’s sandwich. Friendly service.
I ordered a tuna sandwich and they gave me a double cheese sandwich with no tuna. This experience made me want to fight to lower the minimum wage.
It's always nice to rely on quick service. I love the food. If anything, I should get a poor review as a customer for not "freaking" when delivered my sandwich fast 😁
This Jimmy John’s location looks a little run down

On my second catering order (from this location), & haven't been disappointed! The bread is soft the veggies and meat taste fresh. The catering presentation looks awesome. Everyone at the office loves it! I've never seen people grab second's before. & I've order from numerous Catering spots, this seems to be the best option so far.

formatted_address: 200 E Ohio St Ste 1, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Dunkin'

reviews.text: This place had lots of employees too concerned with each other. I was greeted by the cashier and asked what I wanted, I replied and she was more concerned with what other employees were saying and doing. After a few seconds she looked back at me and asked if I wanted anything  else I replied and again her attention was on the other employees. Plus the doughnut selection was weak and not fresh.

the person working today at night is really bad at service all tho they had donuts in the store. the person refused to give the donuts and started serving ppl and all tho i waited for so long the person didnt give me the donut and latte on time amd when i got the donut it was not stirred properly.
Bad service ordered a Carmel latte and I release basically a cup of warm milk ! New night person need 4-25-25

Absolutely Terrible Experience – Never Coming Back!

This Dunkin’ Donuts location was an absolute disaster from start to finish. First of all, the staff spilled our coffee all over the counter and didn’t even apologize. The cups they handed us were dirty – like visibly stained and disgusting. It was shocking.

To make things worse, the service was beyond awful. The employees weren’t listening to us at all, and it took several tries just to get our order right – which they still messed up in the end. It felt like no one there knew what they were doing, or even cared.

If I could give zero stars, I would. Save yourself the frustration and go literally anywhere else.

I placed an uber eats order friday night. The driver contacted me because they were having an issue with the employee at the location. I want it to speak to the employee and the employee was extremely rude to the driver. The driver had me on speaker therefore i heard all the racist stuff the employee was telling the driver. I want it to speak to the employee because i thought there was an issue with my order but the employee stated “ i dont care”. If this location is open 24 hours and the order went through just fine then what was the issue. The employee did not need to be so disrespectful to the driver. The driver like the employee is working so why does the employee feel like they need to be racist against people. Such a horrible experience.

formatted_address: 1500 Butterfield Rd, Downers Grove, IL 60515, USA
name: Portillo's Downers Grove

reviews.text:
So, I don’t usually eat at Portillo’s but for some reason, Americans love eating at breakfast places on Sunday’s. We tried going to Buttermilk and Honey Jam, they were jam packed. Other breakfast places were a 30-45 min wait. I’m not sure what the deal is since it’s not busy on Mon-Sat.

We went to Portillo’s across the street. They have 4 kiosks that you can order from. Depending on what you order, they can make it fast. I ordered chili cheese dog, double rodeo burger, and breaded whitefish sandwich. Food overall was very mediocre. I’m not sure why Portillo’s is always busy, but the food was kind of bland. I had a better rodeo burger at Burger King, which costs less. The fish sandwich is better at McDonald’s for half the cost. Even the chili cheese dog was meh. This is 3 out of 5. There are better places in the area.

I recently visited Portillo’s and had a fantastic experience! I ordered their French fries and the Char-boiled burger, and both were absolutely delicious. The fries were perfectly crispy, and the burger was juicy and flavorful.

What really stood out to me was the quick and amazing service. The staff were friendly and attentive, making my visit even more enjoyable. Surprisingly, the drive-thru was much less crowded than usual, which allowed for a smooth and speedy experience.

Overall, I highly recommend Portillo’s for anyone looking for a tasty meal with excellent service. I can’t wait to go back!

What’s not to love about Portillo’s? Great atmosphere and great food. I like the prohibition era theme. Always busy, but food doesn’t take too long to get. Any time I’m in the Chicagoland area, I always make a stop at Portillo’s. The hot dogs are awesome. The Italian beef is awesome. The burgers are awesome. Everything is awesome.

First visit as a tourist & I fell in LOVE with this place! Ordered the Italian beef & sausage sandwich with fries & strawberry shortcake shake & was STUFFED! That sandwich is AMAZING & I only ate half of it. Portions are great, customer service was remarkable. Place is clean, cozy & decorative. Service was quick despite the lunch rush. I’m hooked!

The food at Portillo's is always so good. We were surprised that the prices keep going up. My chop salad was $12.50 with a cup of water. The high price of a meal makes me consider going to a sit down restaurant. I've been getting the chop salad for years. There is less chicken. It's mostly leaves and onions. Sadly, the new management seems more concerned about cost than customer satisfaction.

Aside from the cost, the service was fast and the room we sat in was quiet and clean. We had a great time and the food was good.

formatted_address: 650 N Northwest Hwy, Park Ridge, IL 60068, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text:
A decent place to get Chicago Pizza.

Came with some co workers while in the Chicago area.

We ordered wings and bread, both of these were fantastic.

We also each ordered a personal pizza, get were really good. The beer selection was just average.

Our server was really nice and overall it wasn't even that expensive.

Would recommend.

This woman is absolutely obnoxious. She has been for as long as I’ve seen her at this location but today was just outlandish.

For reference, you couldn’t find a more respectful delivery courier than me, even if you try with all your might. I never give anybody a hard time and I’m extremely patient, though I’m not at all obligated to be.

Today, while picking up an order, I called in advance to see how long the wait time was. I had multiple orders. The only reason I asked, is so if the wait time happened to be longer than expected, I would have prioritized the other customers in the meantime. I treat all of them evenly and want their food to still be warm when it arrives. THIS restaurant is EXTREMELY serious about customers not receiving cold food, so the lack of professionalism and understanding is mind-boggling to me. They know exactly why I asked.

Over the phone, we got in an argument because she claimed that “this restaurant doesn’t give that information without physically seeing the driver, and that none of the 70 Lou Malnati’s locations do that either”. That’s blasphemous. EVERY Lou Malnati’s location provides that information, ESPECIALLY this one. Had she at least told me that with more respect, I would have just kept quiet regardless of the lack of accuracy in the statement. It’s wrong, to put it simply.

I have called HUNDREDS of times to ask, just so I can stay organized and provide customer satisfaction, and never in my life had an issue. She just looks for excuses to cause a dispute. I was MORE than happy to wait for the food. I didn’t call the restaurant with intentions of rushing anyone, and even vocalized that while speaking to this lady. I would have happily waited an hour if I had to. I didn’t raise my voice nor did I give her trouble.

I value everybody’s time including hers, but she had no intentions of being helpful, and rather, chose to be problematic for absolutely no reason whatsoever. This isn’t new with her, but this was the reason I felt the need to make this known. Please keep in mind, her employees completely agree with what I’m saying. I have talked to them about this. Let it be known.

I’ve been picking these orders up from this location for many years, and have never endured such an immensely problematic ordeal. I get no benefits whatsoever from “lying” that they do in fact give this information over the phone. I would know, as I’m the one calling. The last time I called and received this same information (wait time), was less than a week ago, and for this exact same reason.

At the end of it all, when I tried to explain my reasoning for the call, all I ended up with was being told that she would call DoorDash to “ban me” from the restaurant. I’m a very nice person and everybody else in this restaurant would rightfully admit that. I’m VERY disappointed in the service I received today. Working my day job, I would never be so neglectful towards a person/client present at my business. Absolutely flabbergasted.

*please do not remove this review. I have it written down and will repost it again if I have to.*
The pizza was a bit small, but after trying it, it packed a nice punch ✋️ enough for dinner. TASTE very nice not salty like other places. Good 👌

Another "not my first time here, but first Google Review" for this place! Recent visit was a few days ago for "Pi Day." Ordered a medium Deep Dish Malnati Chicago Classic pizza. Juicy because of the sausage but the dough and crust, if you don't know, are out of this world. I'd probably add additional mozzarella next time but still a winner without extras. Favorite all time is The Lou!

Although I did have to wait about 20 min for my pizza to be ready, I really enjoyed the pizza. I did not have much experience with Chicago style pizza but this pizza was better prepared than the one I had at Giordano's a couple nights ago. Saucy and tasty, cheese melted correctly and crust was cooked good. Price is a little bit more than what I am used to paying for pizza but it's worth it. They did not have an area where I could sit and eat it, but I went to sit on the benches outside to enjoy it white it was hot.

formatted_address: 53 Woodfield Rd F301, Schaumburg, IL 60173, USA
name: The Cheesecake Factory

reviews.text:
My girlfriend’s family invited me to The Cheesecake Factory for her birthday. The dining room was busy but had a fun, celebratory vibe, and our server was friendly and attentive.

I got the Chicken Madeira, which was tender and savory though it could’ve used a touch more sauce because I just love it! She tried the Crusted Chicken Romano, and it was crispy with just the right amount of cheese and seasoning.

For dessert, they brought out a slice of classic cheesecake with a candle and a little “Happy Birthday” fanfare. It was creamy and sweet without being overly rich. Portions are big and prices felt fair for the amount of food.

Overall, it was a great spot for a birthday dinner—good food, good service, and a fun atmosphere.

Had lunch here with my family while we were visiting the mall. We had a reservation and had to wait about 5 minutes to be seated after we checked in. The server was very prompt and courteous during our visit. It took a little longer than normal for our food to arrive, but everything was correct and hot when it was delivered. All the food was delicious and the portions were huge. The menu is very vast with multiple options in each category, so there is a lot to choose from, but everything is good, so you really can't go wrong. Don't forget to get a slice of cheesecake to finish off your meal. You will definitely leave here satisfied!

Finally we got to this place, the people's dishes looked very tasty, unfortunately I can't say the same about mine. The pasta was dry, because it was heated in the microwave. There were traces of someone else's lipstick on the wine glass. Little bit expensive. We paid 150 for 3 person (food and one drink to each)

Food was great and delicious, the atmosphere was a tiny bit crowded for ME but it’s okay!! Would come here again! Busy day but the server could have done a tiny bit better to attention to detail if my group wanted something extra or more of something but it’s okay. Overall great experience!! The wait for my group was 10-15 mins so not too bad and it’s by a mall so waiting will be just shopping or just looking around the mall!!!

I typically don’t like leaving negative reviews, but I tried reaching out directly and never received a response.

Our visit was really disappointing. We waited nearly an hour to be seated, and once we were finally at a table, it took over an hour to get our food—even though several tables who arrived after us were already finished and leaving. We only ordered basic items like a hamburger and a couple of salads, so the delay was frustrating.

That said, the food itself was good once it arrived. But unfortunately, the biggest issue came later. I took a slice of cheesecake to go (the chocolate Oreo one), and when I opened it at home, I found a long blonde hair completely mixed into the chocolate frosting on top. It was honestly gross—especially after paying $15 for one piece of cake.

The whole bill was very expensive, and this experience was a letdown overall. I was genuinely looking forward to dining here, but this visit really missed the mark.

formatted_address: 1880 Tower Dr, Glenview, IL 60025, USA
name: Yard House

reviews.text:
I was really disappointed with this plate of nachos. Despite being a large portion, it completely lacked the flavor and balance you’d expect from a good nacho dish. There was very little cheese — barely noticeable in taste — and the meat was bland and underseasoned.

There were way too many tortilla chips and beans, but not enough of the other key ingredients like tomato salsa, jalapeños, and other toppings that usually bring nachos to life. The overall taste was flat, missing that satisfying blend of textures and flavors that makes nachos enjoyable.

For anyone who truly appreciates authentic, well-balanced nachos, I wouldn’t recommend this one.
Absolutely delicious food! Wait staff is on their game.Huge selection of beer.Happy hour with most apps half off 4- 6pm.  Comfortable  seating as well definitely  one of my favorite places to eat.

Beer lovers this is your place, so many choices from bottles to taps. If you can, come during the happy hours to get $2 off beers and 50% off selected appetizers.

The food here is the standard bar food, not great but good enough. Not sure it would be worth it without the 50% deal 🤣
I enjoy this spot at The Glen particularly because of the atmosphere and feel. The food is wonderful! The service is great and the bar tender is the best.
Great place , great food [Tacos !!!] big choise from beer list . Place is big and clean, friendly service and stuff !!!  Always happy to go beck there. See you soon.

formatted_address: 810 N Marshfield Ave, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: Carbon Live Fire Mexican Grill

reviews.text: It is my first time in Chicago , I am from New York and have a Mexican background. We ordered this food through uber as it had a good rating. It’s a lie. Unfortunately the food was very soggy and not appetizing, it was leaking everywhere due to the corn and beans it all became soggy. There was no taste it was bland. The tacos had so much onion and no flavor at all. No lemon as well. The food also got here cold. I spent $50 and it was not worth it. I suggest you save your money !!! Do NOT purchase.
I got the elote steak burrito delivered. It was incredible! Traveled well and huge! This is my new go to!

The Stelote burrito is my favorite but I’ve had literally every specialty burrito on the menu and NEVER have I been disappointed.

The steak is flavorful, cooked perfect medium and is abundant! You need protein, there you go. I moved out of state and drive 1.5 hr to get here that’s how good it is.

Really great tacos, I will be back for sure! Rice wasn’t great, might have been an off day, tasted just boiled not very flavorful, seemed like they didn’t toast the rice before adding water. Either way I’ll be back because the tacos were great and maybe they’ll up the rice game!

Great American-Mexican food. I’ve been coming to their two locations for over 15 years. Their “burrito bowl” (basically a taco salad) with marinated chicken is my favorite with their house made green tomatillo salsa — terrific. Their famous Mother Clucker chicken burrito is huge and has a sweet lime sauce that’s memorable. If you like elote, theirs is very good. No frills, order at the counter, service. Friendly staff.

formatted_address: 899 S Plymouth Ct, Chicago, IL 60605, USA
name: Chicago Curry House (Indian - Nepalese Cuisine)

reviews.text: Great experience and wonderful food. All the meat was tender and tons of flavor. We got level 8 spicy and was perfect. The chicken Momo's where so good and the sauce that comes with them was delicious!

I got many items as a takeout- Samosa Chaat (didnt expect it to be a cold chaat, extremely sour and lacked any taste whatsoever), Veg Chilli momo (got 8 pieces of fried momo sauteed in a chilli sauce, this was ok, the filling lacked any flavor, the sauce was ok), Garlic naan (thick naan, not very good), Paneer Bhurji (flavorless, spiceless gravy, small portion), Lamb curry (small portion for the price, the mutton pieces were hard and didnt cook well, again flavor could be improved), Shrimp biryani (good, with large shrimps), Mango lassi (this was the best one of all, tasty and good quantity for a good price, does not have that typical mango puree smell that other places have, which is a good thing). Disappointed with the food from this place, if I had to go again, I would only get Mango lassi and nothing else.

Fantastic food! Came here for the lunch buffet on a weekday--they had it on the weekends, but just started doing it all week. Excellent variety, with many options for vegetarian dishes as well as a good selection of proteins (four different meat dishes!) Decently priced for an AYCE buffet!

Would definitely come back. Cheers!

The weekend lunch buffet can carry on its variety of flavours alone. Variety of options, including veg and vegan choices. The veg selections, namely the Dal, are some of the highlights.This quiet restaurant in the south loop is a great spot for a weekend meal. The dining spacing is classy and the service uncanny.

One of the best places to stop by if you love authentic Nepali and Indian cuisine. The buffet is the Best. I love the taste of food, gesture and friendliness of staff,  cleanliness, perfect location, walkable in downtown, have it's own parking lot, and even if you are late they have pickups available. Would say must go for a bunch 🙂

formatted_address: 1500 W Taylor St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: The Rosebud

reviews.text: My family and I stopped in on their soft opening yesterday, and all I have to say is, wow! The food and service were absolutely amazing.  The quality and care for each dish is next level. The staff from our waitress to the manager made us feel like family.  I can't recommend this place enough.  We will be back!

So the food here was amazing, the service is outstanding but keep in mind there is a dress code when you go in, and the Atmosphere was superb! Our Host name was John I believe and he was amazing he also said that he was from Indiana, witch happened to be where we where visiting from. I highly recommend this place.

This was an incredible experience. From the wonderful service to the absolutely exceptional food, it was awesome. I will warn you, DON'T think these portions are like your typical restaurant. They are HUGE! I had the chicken parm and had never seen a portion so large. It was the same with the "piece" of carrot cake my wife and I intended to share, only to find it was a quarter of the entire cake. Add to that the quality of the food's taste and you have a winning combination.

This is no exaggeration and I've attached pictures to prove it. Did I mention the ambiance? Thank you to the wonderful staff for making this experience so special for us!

Ok guys, hear me out…. PROBABLY ONE OF THE BEST HAPPY HOURS IN CHICAGO! The happy hour menu is attached. Sliders were absolutely delicious! The fries…. 🤤 the burrito… spicy and delicious! The crispy Brussel sprouts were not crispy, so if you love crispy, ask for them if they can make sure they’re crispy. The flavor of them were delicious! You literally can not go wrong with the 5 bucks deal! The location is fantastic! Downtown Chicago, can’t ask for a better location! Definitely coming back! The service was great! Very attentive!

I recently visited Rosebud and overall, it was a decent experience. The atmosphere was cozy and inviting, however it was a bit on the dark side in there. The menu had a good variety of Italian dishes to choose from. While the food was well-prepared and presented nicely, the temperature of my food was warm at best. The service was friendly, although there were a few minor hiccups with timing and attention to detail. Despite these shortcomings, it was still a decent meal.

formatted_address: 521 S Dearborn St, Chicago, IL 60605, USA
name: Gino’s East - South Loop

reviews.text: Julio was outstanding as our server. We arrived at happy hour and he made sure the drinks and appetizers were to us quickly. The wings and hand rolled cheese and spinach sticks were fantastic. Then the deep dish pizza came out to the table. It just got even better if that is possible. Highly recommend if in Chicago especially staying right across the street from Hotel Blake.

Drinks were pricey but that's probably every where in Chicago.  Bottle of miller light was 7.50. Only had dessert. The "famous " Eli's Cheesecake ($11.24) was terrible!  It was rubbery and hard on the outside. Not smooth and creamy like it should be. The chocolate chip cookie was baked fresh and ooey and gooey, which I loved.  Was going to go back and try dinner later but there was only one person working in the kitchen and just dessert took way too long, in my opinion. Location was conveniently close to the hotel I'm staying at.

We visited Gino’s East over a couple of days and got to sample a bit of everything—hand-rolled mozzarella sticks, the Meaty Legend on thin crust, and the Gino’s Supreme as a deep dish. Both pizzas were excellent, but next time I’d flip it: the Meaty Legend would be amazing as a deep dish, and the Supreme really shines on thin crust. Speaking of which—the thin crust here blew me away. Perfectly crisp with a dough that tastes like it was made in-house, it’s hands down the best I’ve had anywhere.

The service was top-notch too—staff went out of their way to make us comfortable and accommodate special requests. The vibe of the bar is laid-back with classic Chicago charm. Whether you're a tourist or a local, Gino’s East delivers a great experience all around.

Friendly staff it was around time it was beginning to get crowded there table outside but we were able to sit inside. I’m glad I always carry wipe because the table was dirty. We did build your own pizza thin crust it was delicious.

Visiting from England it was a tough decision which place to pick that wasn’t a tourist trap, after asking a few locals we picked Ginos, we are so glad we did!
Firstly the staff are outstanding, the black guy who was the main server was so hard working, helpful and just a nice guy.
The food.
I’ve never seen chicken wings so big! They are so juicy and up there with the best I’ve ever tasted.
Now the deep dish, omg, we’ve never tasted anything like this, simply awesome, the Chicago fire was fire!
10/10

formatted_address: 2373 S Archer Ave, Chicago, IL 60616, USA
name: Connie's Pizza

reviews.text: Their pan pizza has been consistently amazing over the years. The sausage is flavorful and the crust is light and fluffy. They have the best salad dressing ( Parmesan garlic). 😋 I will say, if you are a plus size person, please be aware that many of their chairs have a curved arm rest that will most definitely dig into your thighs and will not be the most comfortable. I was able to switch out a chair with no arms but it was very rickety. ( Unless you sit in the bar area where the high chairs are) Overall, I do love the old school feel of the place and their pizza is great. The service was also prompt and friendly.

I wanted my Indian Mother to experience an authentic pizza place in Chicago and Connie’s DID NOT DISAPPOINT!. It was everything we wanted and more!. From the moment you walk in, there is so many cool interesting decorations to look at, the vibes were a 10 and service was fast despite it being super busy! ( I highly recommend making reservations especially on the weekends).
This place is huge! And has different seating sections but out of all, the best place to sit is the main hall boasting a high ceiling with interesting old machinery.
We ordered the strawberry daiquiri (I couldn’t taste the alcohol at all!) and the tropical mango (it was ok, also very light on the alcohol).
For appetizers we got the fried zucchini sticks ( flavor was good but it would have been better if the zucchini wasn’t super soft, almost mushy)
We ordered 2 small things crust pizzas, one veggie and one bbq chicken (both were delicious!).
Overall the experience was positive.

Unique atmosphere. Friendly staff. I ordered truffle fries, a caesar salad, and a small sausage pizza. Everything was good. My favorite was the truffle fries. I feel the salad could've had a Little bit more dressing.
Got seated at the bar right away. Beer was ice cold. Salad was crispy and tasty. Pizza was delicious and cheesy. First time having their pan pizza. So good.

our search led us to Connie's Pizza, we were drawn in by the promise of tradition and the tantalizing images of cheesy, saucy goodness. But what truly sealed the deal was a single review - a tale of a family wanting to share the true Chicago pizza experience with their Indian mother. Intrigued, we decided to embark on our own Connie's adventure, hoping to replicate that heartwarming and delicious experience.

And let me tell you, Connie's Pizza did not disappoint. From the moment we stepped inside, the bustling atmosphere spoke volumes about its popularity. Luckily, we had made the advice and made a reservation, ensuring we wouldn't have to wait too long to dive into the pizza perfection. Our mission was simple: to share the authentic taste of Chicago with our mother. We decided to sample both the thin-crust and deep-dish pizzas, they were delicious.  We will be coming back and thank you Connie’s Pizza for giving my mother an great experience.

formatted_address: 1050 E Higgins Rd, Elk Grove Village, IL 60007, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text:
Best pizza in Chicago, in my personal opinion. Made when you order, absolutely fills you up and makes you wish you could eat here every single day.

Our waitress, Linda, was the best! She was so kind and informative and genuinely just the coolest person on the planet. We loved her. Would come back just to hang at one of her tables again, even if the food wasn’t phenomenal.

Stopped in for some Chicago-style pan pizza. Pizza was good. Toppings were great but thought the crust was a lacking in flavor.  Appetizers were average and beer was a little pricey.  Overall experience was good and worth stopping in.

What is going on with Lou’s Deep Dish?
Way more dough than cheese.
Cutting cost saving some $$$ on cheese.
I had family visiting out of state they wanted to try Chicago’s famous Deep Dish I went with Lou’s and we get this. NOT COOL.
After more than 20 years being Lous customer all the birthdays and other events, c c c.
No more.

Order number 34159734419652611

We were here on Friday night. Tables are almost 100% full even though it was after dinner rush.
Deep dish is just right! Not salty at all which I like! And the portion was huge! The salad was sweet and vinegary! Small was Enough for 3 ppl. I’ll probably pick up their frozen pizza next time I pass Chicago!

Although pizza is the most distinctive food here, their pasta and children's meal are also very popular dishes for children! And the price of the children's meal is very reasonable! The spaghetti bolognese and mini burgers in the children's meal are delicious! Coupled with great service and unique decoration style, this is worthy of being one of the classic restaurants in Chicago!

formatted_address: 85 S Buffalo Grove Rd, Buffalo Grove, IL 60089, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text:
Our first deep dish and it was phenomenal.  Our waiter was great!
Only thing is the personal size that's labled for 1 person, is definitely too small for a grown man. As a suggestion,  it would be good to write the sizes on the menu.

Deep dish classic sausage pizza was delish, though wish the sausage was a bit more flavorful and in roundish chunks, not flat and spread out over the pizza. Our server Kelly B was wonderful: great service, attentive, friendly.

Came with my wife, son, brother, and a few friends for a good deep-dish pie, and Lou's satisfied all expectations.
Wonderful service, fun atmosphere, and excellent food.
Be sure to pick up the two-pack of $50 gift cards for Lou's from Costco for only $80 for some savings on scrumptious pizza.

Very good Chicago deep dish pizza.
We got sausage, onion, green pepper and basil.    The crust was something special.  Tasty 😋

Order what you want or go for their standards: The Lou or The Malnati

The service was phenomenal.  The server played our pizza for us.

Mixed drinks available, too
A Chicago classic. Great food and service. Francesca was fantastic. My out of town guests loved it! Pizza will never be the same for them!

formatted_address: 33 N Dearborn St, Chicago, IL 60602, USA
name: Roti Mediterranean Bowls. Salads. Pitas.

reviews.text:
Great food, so-so dining space. That’s a short summary of this restaurant. While Mediterranean is in the name, I don’t know how correct that is. This is not the kind of food I’ve seen around the Mediterranean.

That said, it’s good. I got a street falafel and both the pita and the falafels were great. Highly recommended.

The seating area was a bit dull though. And both ordering machines were offline.

Polite, but not overtly friendly counter service - nothing to be ‘wowed’ by. Expedient service. Great selection of proteins and toppings. Their seasonings are excellent. The portion sizes are excellent. The build your bowl options are great, but the menu selections available for the combos they provide are definitely worth trying.

This is the healthier ‘fast food’ option !👍🏾

Fantastic Mediterranean dishes. Whether you order gyros on pita, rice bowl or salad you'll enjoy your meal.  I selected the chicken as my protein, add any veggies (big selection), add hummus. Select sauce which you can have on the side and you're ready to pay & enjoy your meal. Ask for a lid if you order a rice bowl because it's so yummy & usually eat a third and take home the rest. Roti employee staff is very nice. Food smells wonderful. Tastes terrific. In the big city of Chicago support this business to keep it open for all to enjoy. Easy to find. It's next door to the f o o d   h a l  l where we are the day before on our vacation. Bon appetit.

Roti Mediterranean Grill offers a delightful fusion of fast service and diverse, flavorful cuisine. The menu boasts a tantalizing array of Mediterranean-inspired dishes, showcasing fresh ingredients and bold spices. From savory kebabs to crisp salads and hearty wraps, there's something to satisfy every palate. The service is efficient and friendly, ensuring a pleasant dining experience for patrons on the go. Whether you're craving a quick bite or a leisurely meal, Roti Mediterranean Grill delivers both speed and quality in equal measure.

I love Mediterranean food. I eat it all the time In Egypt and Dubai.
This was spectacular. My mouth was full of different flavors,  It was so exciting. I didn’t know what was going on inside my mouth. Flavor, flavor flavor. The Cumin, coriander, garbanzo beans, marinated red onions, sweet potato, and the pomegranate, vinaigrette salad dressing was tasty.
The staff  were welcoming and friendly Julius is a super star. His professionalism was top notch.  Also Jesus made my salad with love thanks so much for a spectacular experience.

formatted_address: 1850 Sherman Ave, Evanston, IL 60201, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text: I went here with some friends. It was a great experience.  Our waitress made suggestions that made our ordering process easier.  We ordered a salad for 4 and a large sausage and cheese pizza. I'd never ordered a salad there before. The dressing, a sweet vinaigrette, was delicious. It took the salad to the next level. Our pizza was also very good. Lou Malnati's - arguably the best pizza in town.

The loud, chaotic atmosphere led us to get take out. We waited about 40 minutes for a small deep dish, but the employees were very helpful despite being slammed with business. The deep dish was pretty good, the crust texture and cheese were great, but the sauce was a little bland.
The pizza was good. However, the server did not fill up water until I asked after waiting like 30 minutes and I had to call him out for it. Even I was not asked if I need anything.

Jennie, our waitress at Lou Malnati’s in Evanston, gave us absolutely incredible service that made our visit unforgettable. After driving five hours to get here, I had high hopes—and Jennie exceeded every single one. From the moment we sat down, she greeted us with a huge smile and handed us crazy colorful straws that instantly made the experience more fun. She was incredibly friendly, took the time to chat with us throughout the meal, and made us feel genuinely welcome. Our food came out quickly, and she checked in on us often to make sure we had everything we needed. Jennie’s kindness and energy turned a simple dinner into a truly special experience.

This place should not be 3.5 stars. Read the lower reviews and it mostly has to do with delivery from DoorDash. Issues with your delivery should be rated on DoorDash not here.
First time in Chicago and of course needed to try the deep dish. Lou Malnati’s was a recommendation from a local friend and it did not disappoint. Pizza was great. Had the Malnati, sauce was very good. We also had Elizabeth as our server, and she made the visit even better. Check with us on our order to make sure we were getting what we expected. For example we ordered the small chocolate chip cookie dessert and she guessed we might be sharing so she let us know the size it was which we were definitely needed a little bit more and switched to the larger. Don’t let the lowers reviews be a concern unless you’re ordering DoorDash and think twice about that. Get off your butt and pick it up to get the best 😂. We also sat outside on a beautiful early evening.

formatted_address: 2217 S Wentworth Ave, Chicago, IL 60616, USA
name: Triple Crown Restaurant

reviews.text: I enjoyed our visit to Triple Crown.  This is my 2md visit here (it's also where I first tried dim sum a few years back).  We came on a Saturday evening after finding out the chef was not present at our normal dimsum spot.  There was about a 45 minute wait.  A bit long, but also testament to the popularity of this place.  Once we were seated we were greeted promptly by their waitstaff. The dimsum menu here is about average size for a dimsum restaurant.  The normal menu a bit larger.  We ordered a variety of dishes.  Food all came out promptly. Everything was good.  Nothing that I would consider "the best,: but all still much better than the average Chinese restaurant.  Serving sizes of the regular dishes we ordered were good, but not huge.  Needless to say, we still left with a lot of food.  I do recommend this place.  Its still mot my #1 choice in Chicago, but it's not too far behind.

I finally tried Triple Crown in Chicago which many people say is the BEST place to get authentic dim sum. It’s family-owned and also serves true Cantonese cuisine. The crew started off with some tea, before diving into the food. I also think this rotating surface is such a nice touch to really share things in a quick way. Let’s start with the salt and pepper soft shell crab, the perfect texture, and well balanced in the seasoning. We also had shrimp fried rice, because we had to do it for the culture, as well as the roasted duck because duck is my favorite thing to get at Chinese restaurants. Their duck was wonderfully roasted, salty, and fatty just the way I like it. But I digress, the reason why we chose Triple Crown is for their famous dim sum. The scallop dumplings were different, but very mild flavor, you definitely should dress them up in some chili oil. The pan fried shrimp & chive dumplings were very packed, but my favorite dumplings of the rainy afternoon were the pork and shrimp. Their appearance even was everything I was expecting, but the flavor phenomenal. The fattiness from the pork mixed with the shrimp really sells the dumpling, and the cherry on top of course is the chili oil.

I was craving dim sum and our friend brought us here so glad they did! The food was great, with generous portions at reasonable prices. They also offer lunch specials that are really affordable. The food came out quickly and everything we tried was delicious. I’ll definitely be coming back to try more dishes.

We came on Lunar New Year’s, so it was very busy. The staff was still efficient and polite, if not overly friendly. The atmosphere was nice, though drafty…many people wore their coats at nearby tables. Most importantly, the dim sum was delicious and spaced out perfectly. We marked our choices on the paper picture menu and they took care of the rest. There’s a reason this place is a classic. Recommended and will make a point to return!

Such a wonderful spot. The food is absolutely delicious, our best experience dining in China Town yet. Not one dish was under our expectations. Yum! The service is so fast and the staff is very accommodating.

We visited for the first time during China Town’s Lunar New Year celebration. We arrived 10 minutes before 11am, and were seated! We were happy and surprised as it was quite busy downtown. They handed out complimentary New Year gifts which made the experience so fun. Highly recommend!

formatted_address: 1924 W Chicago Ave, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: Roots Handmade Pizza - West Town

reviews.text: We have chowed here so many times and always kill the food before I remember to take photos but finally got it done. This place is amazing. The malt crust on this pizza is spectacular and holds it structure well. Absolutely amazing. They don't shy away from toppings and salad portions are huge. Recommend this place to anyone that loves thin crust pizzas, good chow and and a lovely atmosphere.

My husband and I had lunch at Roots in West Town, Chicago, during the CHIditarod, a fun event for a good cause—Chicago’s epic urban shopping cart race and charity food drive.

We ordered the Korean fried chicken pizza and the Not a Carrot in the World salad. The pizza was delicious, flavorful but not too spicy, and the fresh salad paired nicely with the heavier pizza dish. The salad had delicious mango and avocado and a refreshing carrot tahini dressing. The server was friendly too.

During our visit, we saw the CHIditarod contestants’ decked out shopping carts which was a delightful experience, and the restaurant/bar was full of life with a great DJ!

Honestly this place is very overpriced. 10 wings for $25 is not reasonable especially since the wings were not great, they were okay. I asked for a side of Nashville sauce (the spiciest on the menu - that was very spicy, which I was presently surprised with) I disliked that you had to pay extra for the ranch and blue cheese. I even saw that they charge for celery sticks with your wings.
The Southwest salad was a big portion, the pic only shows what I served myself. The dressing is a bit sweet for my liking. There's so many other options around this area that I regret not choosing to go to instead.

The restaurant has a lively sports bar atmosphere, perfect for catching a game or hanging out with friends. The crowd was laid-back and it never felt too packed, so you can enjoy your time without feeling overwhelmed. Service was impressively quick, keeping things smooth and efficient.

If you're a cheese lover, the cheese sticks are a must-try. They're loaded with gooey, melted cheese, and every bite leaves your mouth full of rich, cheesy goodness. It's definitely the standout item on the menu.

However, the rest of the food falls short of expectations. While not bad, there's nothing particularly memorable about the other dishes, especially considering the higher price point. For what they charge, you'd expect a bit more quality and flavor in their offerings. Overall, it's a good spot for a fun night out, but maybe not the best value if you're looking for a standout meal.

First time there on Saturday. The place itself is nice and clean. Except the bathrooms. They were sooo very gross. It was very hot outside so sitting on the roof top was not an option. We did walk up there with intent to eat upstairs but it was so hot and smelt like BO. Sat downstairs hoping for AC and nope it was just as hot and uncomfortable. Service was okay but slow and there were not many people there at all. We ordered their homemade root beer and it was really good. We ordered their "famous" mozzarella sticks and yikes, they were flavorless...  We also ordered the Quad City style pizza (half veggie and half pepperoni) was not fans either. The sauce is too sweet and cheese was flavorless. AND to top it off.... the dough was still gooey! Quit depressing over all. Paid $85.00 for a meal for 3 people. Sorry but will not be going back. I gave them 3 stars for atmosphere because the roof top is very cute and the bar areas looked pretty cool to chill at.

formatted_address: 203 Yorktown, Lombard, IL 60148, USA
name: Panda Express

reviews.text:
Chinese fast food restaurant in Yorktown centre.
It is located in the food court of the mall.
Similar to other Panda express restaurants.
Service was fast and professional.
Many tables to sit close to the restaurant. I like sitting by the window where you can see outside.

The food was okay, it tasted a bit bland, but overall it was decent. The service was good and overall they were kind and quick, which is something I liked. I thought the atmosphere was decent, but it was a bit dirty; it didn't really affect my experience. Overall I think my rating was justified.

April 7, 2025, at 6:47 PM
The staff was disrespectful. The girl who served my food gave me a very small portion of rice and chicken. I asked her politely if she could add a bit more, and in response, she rudely threw just one more piece of chicken on the plate and tossed the food toward the cashier. Usually, other places serve much larger portions—you probably know that if you eat here. I could clearly see how small the portion was.

Never been treated so poorly. I greeted them kindly ordering my food , said please and thank you, and yet still the young teenage girl working was nothing but unkind and rude to me. She was short with nearly black hair and looked no more than 19. You’d think I had insulted her by how rude she was to me and my friend. She greeted us by asking “what do u want” and that was all, and even rolled her eyes at me when I said thank you after she handed me my food. I don’t understand how she was even able to get the job there in the first place with the terrible customer service
Food is horrible, raw noodles hard and tasteless.

formatted_address: 118 S Clinton St, Chicago, IL 60661, USA
name: Dylans Tavern & Grill

reviews.text:
The owner, bartender and main waitress are so welcoming and helpful!

Especially when nothing else is open at the times you need them open! They are open!

Decent choice of food, though I've heard it's upgrading!!

And the most amazing staff!

We had a 5-Hour layover before our next bus so we decided to stop in and grab a quick bite and a drink. We weren't told that they were closing in less than an hour she said that their menus are only on QR codes right away gave us the happy hour options we each ordered a wings one drink each and some fries. Food was good just like any other bar pub that we've gone to but at 7:20 something she comes back and lets us know that they close at 8:00 and basically was rushing us to hurry up and eat and get out I gave her a tip and we left in all honesty if we had no they were closing at 8:00 we would not have gone in

Very convenient location. Right across from Union Station. Our waitress was Isabel and she was absolutely wonderful! Very attentive and super friendly. Also my hubby wanted ribs and they stayed open later to cook them for him. He said they were amazing! I had their chicken strips and fries and that was very good. The one thing I didn't like was they charge a convenience fee for using a debit card or credit card. Also a Great place for big parties. Large place.

This place was so amazing!! Heather, the bar manager personally introduced herself to us and thanked us for being so awesome! I can't remember our other server's name, but she was beautiful and had a lovely accent.
The food was hot and on point too! Definitely highly recommend this place!

I appreciate the host who accommodated our party of 4 to have a table away from the front door. Actually—the only reason this place received any stars was because of that.

Let’s set the scene- the night was slow, there were 4 other tables, and it appeared to be well-staffed. Drinks took forever, no napkins or utensils were provided until we asked for it, twice. Maybe an off day for the server but this was just bad news bears. Don’t worry, we still tipped well. Quick rundown- Dylan’s lack good service and good food- I wouldn’t recommend this place at all.

formatted_address: 131 W Jefferson Ave, Naperville, IL 60540, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text: I loved the location it was cute. Server was amazing and attentive even though it was a Togo order.  I'm from Texas and wanted to try deep dish.  I got a small Lou and was not very impressed. The dough had this off taste.  And came out soggy.  Was much better the next day heated in the oven.  Considering it's there most popular pizza I was shocked at the lack of flavor.  And I'm not sure the going price for pizza but $25 for a small that didn't "blow my skirt up" seemed a little outrageous.  The service and cute environment is why I'm giving more stars. Also the salad my sister got was an amazingly good portion, but I wasn't I impressed with the quality of the veggies.  There might be better options if you're going to spend this much

Pizzas are absolutely amazing! We were merely driving through Chicago on a long car ride and decided to fulfill a heartfelt request for a Lou Malnati's frozen pizza. We decided since we were stopping anyway to take our lunch break. Our visit couldn't have gone better! We were able to sit on a covered patio with a dog, too. It does take 30 minutes for the deep dish, but definitely worth your time, the calamari and salad servings were plenty enough to share. Perfect lunch!

I tried Lou Malnati’s after 4 years this is what I got in the name of deep dish. First of all, this was not at all “deep dish” at all, it was just a big chunk of crust and a little bit of sauce and toppings on it. It was very dry and did not taste good. We ordered it especially for our guests who came to Chicago and wanted to try Chicago’s famous deep dish. I was embarrassed serving this to them. Very disappointed. I know they used to be really good in the past, I’m not sure what happened.

This is my first time enjoying Lou Malnati's pizza, the deep dish is the best I've ever had! I added butter crust to my deep dish. Good thing there is not a location in my state, I'd eat it at least 3 times a week, lol! I'd love to try some other items on the menu.

Food was great as always, the Lou’s classic is perfect, thin crust is delicious, and the salad is very good. Service was alright. Took a while to get anything and it was pretty slow there. We like Lou’s and will continue to come back.

formatted_address: 8520 Fernald Ave, Morton Grove, IL 60053, USA
name: Pequod's Pizza

reviews.text: I stopped by the Morton Grove location of Pequod’s Pizza and had an awesome experience. I ordered the sausage and pepperoni deep dish, and it was seriously one of the best pizzas I’ve had—super flavorful with that crispy caramelized crust they’re known for. The sausage was well-seasoned, the pepperoni had a nice kick, and everything just came together perfectly. I also had a Blue Moon beer with it, which hit the spot. The place had a chill vibe, the service was solid, and overall it was a great time. Definitely coming back.

So far this is the best deep dish pizza I have ever had, in from out of town and had to try this place, a friend and I stopped in and ordered both a deep dish and thin crust pizza with pepperoni and fresh garlic. Both pizzas smacked!! Could not finish and took the leftover pizza to go, and it was even better hours later.

The atmosphere at this place is pretty cool as well, situated in a neat little neighborhood it feels like a little local bar with killer food, go here. Service was good as well.

Ordered the deep dish with with four veg toppings. The pizza was a little dry with not quite enough sauce, but it was still good. I wouldn't call it the Best Pizza In The Universe.  I like the authentic old style look that has been preserved at this Morton Grove location.

You are stepping into a time capsule at this location. The decor immediately brings me back to the 80's with the plastic cups and vinyl table cloth, wood paneling, and sport/beer memorabilia.

We ordered 4 different types of pizza in a large group, but the highlight for me was a pepperoni, garlic, spinach, onion, and tomato. It was fantastic, but with the sauce it becomes pretty acidic, so be prepared if you're sensitive.

Go with a group and enjoy watching everyone not eat the burnt caramelized edge.

It's a classic.

Was looking forward to trying this pizza when planning my trip to Chicago.

Was not disappointed, the pizza was amazing.

We got Italian sausage and pepperoni and there was plenty on there.
A medium was more than enough for us both, they do not slack on toppings.

The caramelised crust went beyond expectations, absolutely loved it.

formatted_address: 3859 W Ogden Ave, Chicago, IL 60623, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text: I absolutely love this place, everything is a 5/5. If I could give it a 10/5 I would! Food was amazing, our waitress Sam was super helpful, and stayed on top of everything to make sure that we had a great time. We will be stopping in every time we come out to Chicago.

The absolute best experience! 1000% will be back and make it a tradition to stop in. They were so unbelievably kind, the food was amazing, and overall, one of best parts of our whole trip! Oh and the lemonade, Amazing!
This was our first time trying Chicago style pizza. The service, food and atmosphere were all impeccable. Highly recommend

We had an awesome evening tonight. The staff here is so genuine and wonderful. There was a mix up with our order and they were very gracious in the situation. Food was awesome. Pizza amazing as expected but the malnati salad and hot wings were low key stellar as well. We had such a great evening and we can't thank them enough for such a great evening! Thanks again!

Lou Malnati's Pizzeria is a culinary landmark, and my recent visit only cemented its legendary status. From the moment I walked in, the aroma of freshly baked crust and simmering tomato sauce enveloped me, setting the stage for what was to come.

The deep-dish pizza, the star of the show, was a masterpiece. The crust, buttery and flaky, provided the perfect foundation for the generous layers of toppings. The cheese, a molten blanket of mozzarella, stretched with each satisfying bite, while the chunky tomato sauce, bursting with sweet and tangy flavors, tied everything together in perfect harmony.

What truly elevated the experience, however, was the exceptional service. Our server, Donnel, was attentive, knowledgeable, and genuinely passionate about the food. He guided us through the menu with expertise, offering insightful recommendations and ensuring our every need was met. And when a minor issue arose, the manager, Kerry, went above and beyond to resolve it, demonstrating a level of care and commitment that is rare to find. Lou Malnati's isn't just a restaurant; it's an institution, a place where you can gather with friends and family to enjoy a truly exceptional meal.

formatted_address: 1531 W Taylor St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: Pompei Restaurant

reviews.text: They have free parking, accessible entrance and bathrooms with bars for my mom who uses a wheelchair. The food is reasonably priced and sooooo tasty. The staff was very friendly and helpful. Definitely coming back with my family! Spent $20-30 per person including dessert and appetizer.

You want a great casual Italian experience that has amazing food. Stop here.

Also if you want to be ruined for bread pudding the rest of your life...
Seriously, they said it was good, but I was not ready. It is so good that bread pudding anywhere else will taste like sawdust.

Will be back for the fried calamari and works pizza! Food came out super quickly and everything was hot and fresh. I know Italian places love cocktail sauce and marinara but if we could get an aioli dipping sauce for the calamari that would be a game changer. Looking forward to going back and trying some more things off the menu.

reviews.author_name: Al’s On The Stop Auto Body work
reviews.text: We are from Crown point, Indiana and when me and my family are in Chicago, we always make sure to stop at this restaurant. It is always on point. The food is great. The staff is friendly absolutely love it and I’m sure you will too.

Pompei is consistently good. Order at the counter and they bring your food to you. Good pizza slices and strudel. Marie’s special salad is a must. Chopped romaine with blue cheese, onion, crispy prosciutto n Marie’s special dressing. Give it a try.

formatted_address: 3114 N Lincoln Ave, Chicago, IL 60657, USA
name: Chicago's Pizza

reviews.text: If you're looking for a true Chicago-style pizza experience, you can't go wrong here. Delicious perfection, 10/10, no notes. Attention to food allergies was especially appreciated. Went for the gluten free deep dish and it was SO good. My boys had a thin crust and were delighted to find the pepperoni UNDER the cheese. IYKYK. Thanks to the very friendly staff for such a wonderful meal, we will definitely be back!!!

This place is a fantastic choice for anyone with celiac disease, and it’s incredibly family-friendly! Our 4-year-old had a blast making his own pizza, and the staff made the experience even better. As soon as we were seated, they asked about any allergies and were extremely knowledgeable about gluten-free options. The food was delicious, and we felt completely at ease. Highly recommend!

**Only rated pizza, delivery

LOVE it!  Being a celiac it is hard to find a decent GF pizza option, so typically just skip it.  We've tried several places and Chicago's Pizza is at the top of the list!

Crust is perfect, a bit crunchy, flavorful and can hold the ingredients.  My hubby even eats it with me.

Thank you for making something for those of us who can't eat gluten (not who choose not to)!  Really appreciate it!!

My wife has gluten free allergy (celiac), and they had an amazing pizza (thin crust and deep dish). She loved the place so much, we came back here twice during our 5-day trip in Chicago. Our server was very friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable.

There name should be Chicago's BEST Pizza.  I love their pizza and crave it when I'm not in Chicago.  It is one of the first things we order when we are back in town.  You can't go wrong with any of the pizzas.  It is by far the best gluten free crust around.

formatted_address: 6649 Lincoln Ave, Lincolnwood, IL 60712, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text:
I recently dined at Lou Malnatis Pizza and had such a fantastic experience that I felt compelled to leave a glowing review. From the moment we walked in, we were greeted with warm smiles and the irresistible aroma of fresh, cooked pizza. The ambiance was cozy yet nostalgic, with just the right touch of rustic charm.
We started with Lou’s Bruschetta that was clearly made in-house. For the main course, we ordered a deep dish The Lou’s pizza. It was phenomenal—the crust was crispy with a beautiful char, the ingredients were incredibly fresh, and the flavors were perfectly balanced.
The service was equally impressive—our server was attentive, knowledgeable, and made great recommendations without being pushy. It’s clear the staff takes pride in what they do.
Whether you’re a pizza purist or looking to try something new, this place has something for everyone. I’ll definitely be coming back soon!

The Malnati Chicago Classic pizza is very delicious! Lou Malnati’s uses fresh, high-quality ingredients, from long term, top quality providers.
