The high quality of each ingredient stands out: Vine-ripened California tomatoes form the tomato sauce; the mozzarella cheese from Wisconsin has a unique flavor and texture; the flavorful sausage blend is made exclusively in Chicago; and the secret recipe dough forms a delicious, flakey, buttery crust. The pizza is consistently excellent! Friendly staff and service!

I haven't been here since the mid 1980's so it was a real treat to return, to say the least. Our pizza was excellent and the  Malnati salad that we ordered was delicious. Our waitress was Liz and she was friendly and very efficient. It's clean as can be and was very busy, but not crazy busy for seating. Lots of places to sit in different rooms. We chose to sit in a booth in the bar area where it was pretty quiet with only one other person at the bar. I am so glad that we got to go back to the original place I remember when I lived down in Chicago for a couple summers while I was in college. I also bought two bottles of the salad dressings to take home. It's so good; I recommend you get a salad so that you can try it too. I am attaching lots of photos. Thank you Lou Malnati's for an excellent meal in a cozy setting.
Outstanding food. Pizza is amazing. The Chocolate cake is marvelous.  Gotta try it. Service was slow, took a while to get our Pizza. But amazing food. Definitely come back soon
Wonderful diner, absolutely delicious food, super nice service, will come here again while visit Chicago next time!! Brilliant!!

formatted_address: 310 W Adams St, Chicago, IL 60606, USA
name: Roti Mediterranean Bowls. Salads. Pitas.

reviews.text: Food is delicious. I customized my own falafel pita. Several good toppings and the ability to add sauces based on preference. This was great as I like my food more spicy.

I took 3 bites before I had to throw the food away. It was disgusting. I ordered the Za'atar chicken bowl, and the chicken was so dry and stale, it tasted like it was days old. The rice did not taste fresh either. Really gross food.

Today I was Blessed with Great Food , Great Customer Service and a Great Smile from This business. I personally wanna say thank you to Xavier for encouraging me to try the food , you got Potential to Grow ! Kim thank you for having a Great Team with many others I didn't name , thank you all for the services I received . You guys are awesome.

This was a place I stepped in to crab a quick bite without a recommendation. I ordered a chicken medley. The food was of good quality and the chicken delicious. Would highly recommend it. Good value for money!!!

They assemble your food according to the options chosen. Kind of Mediterraneanish faster food, great for lunch or takeout.
Really, who is kidding you, it is a far cry from authentic, but, perhaps good enough for North American tastes. Surely great for fast moving, instant culture in the loop setting.
They do play up healthy food like organic ingredients, antibiotic free chicken, whole  wheat bread, sustainably raised (farmed) salmon etc.
Also they seem to be very good at catering office parties and other events. Good and fast, not great. Surely worth a try.

formatted_address: 7501 Cermak Rd, North Riverside, IL 60546, USA
name: Sbarro

reviews.text:
We always go to Sbarro for pizza for my son, and we always get as many pop refills as he wants, but this time, the manager Jorge for this location said he was only allowed to have one refill... when did that change?
The manager in duty, Jorge, just needed to give my son his refill, but instead, he kept arguing with me that he would not give me a refill. What a bad manager.
I thought customers were always right, but not this time.
We ended up with no refill, and this location ended up with one less customer.
We will not be back to this location.
Good god save your money I wanted to reminisce on the old days at the food court at my local mall and this place made me regret ever stopping here is my $10.00 slice of pizza 🙃

i have been to this location twice in the past year and it appears that it is almost always the same employees there. they don't really give the best customer service but i honestly don't look for great customer service in food courts within malls so it doesn't matter as much to someone like me.

although i do think it is somewhat ridiculous to pay over eleven dollars for a stromboli and a drink but that's on me because i don't care for pizza.

save your money and get something else from the food court unless you want pizza THAT badly then just get pizza later on that day from little caesar's.

I have been a big fan of Sbarro pizza for years. I have never seen them outside of malls & it is my preferred food court item if I ever go shopping. The staff at this location is minimally friendly unfortunately but the pizza still slaps.

Had a double charge on a single purchase....I was dredding going to show them the account charge and see how they can remedy this situation....I showed them the proof pnc statements and we talked about the order....mr George and Mrs Wendy were super accommodating and apologetic....definitely made an experience i wasn't sure about turn into a reason me and my family come to this mall for this particular pizza.....God bless them both

formatted_address: 641 Plainfield Rd, Willowbrook, IL 60527, USA
name: Giordano's

reviews.text:
My family and I were in Chicago for a day while we laid out dear great aunt to rest. After the services, we wanted to try deep dish pizza for the first time. I accidentally placed my order at the wrong shop. Patrick Norton, Manager, was so kind to us as we had already been waiting for 45 mins. He placed our order with a rush. His staff helped by providing us with waters. He made sure that we were fully taken care of. He was so kind, polite, respectful, professional, etc. And…. The food was absolutely delicious! I’m so grateful for this experience.

Thank you,
Tia

I went here for a small family celebration and I have nothing but excellent reviews. Not only was the mood light and airy, but the food was amazing. The best part of this experience was the server, Faleesha, who never once stopped smiling and even recommended this delicious tomato and bread dish. She would've been the star of the night with all of her jokes if we weren't actively celebrating. Lovely experience, wonderful food, and a hardworking server.

I friggin love Giordanos. Been going since I was a kid & the pizza always slaps. My wife & I are thin crust fans, but the deep dish is also rly good & filling. Our waitress was nice to us which is always appreciated. Mozzarella sticks are top notch!
I visited this place with my family, the pizza was delicious, of course, and the female staff was especially friendly, which I really appreciated. ^^

The restaurant was very welcoming to everyone, I saw families and couples enjoying dinner. It was very bright, they had some TVs playing sports but you were able to have a conversation without having to talk over the TV.
I got the bacon and sausage pizza. I asked the server if there was bacon in the pizza because I didn't see it or taste it and they made a cup of bacon to order for me to distribute it on the pizza. I was unexpecting that, they want above and beyond there.
The pizza's were very tasty, I will definitely be back.
My only complaint is the sinks in the bathroom pour out water close to the edge and it made it hard to wash your hands without touching the sink.

formatted_address: 9501 W 171st St, Tinley Park, IL 60487, USA
name: Lou Malnati's Pizzeria

reviews.text: Well, the little personal size deep dish pizza was delicious, but too small.  Needed to be a bit bigger.  Service was short handed a d a bit slow.  And you have to wait a bit for it to be made. I did tell them it was my first time but was not provided with meal options.  And for dinner time they do not offer a small side salad or I guess anything else. Just the little pizza I have pictured here. The meal was not what I would call a complete meal. An appetizer cost almost as much as the little pizza at $12.85. That is why only 3 stars. It needs to be a more rounded meal. Just a side salad and it would have been 4 stars. I drove almost an hour just to experience true Chicago deep dish pizza and this is all it was. Disappointing.

The food here is always good, but what really set our meal here today apart was the outstanding service. Our server was exceptionally attentive, made sure that we were well taken care of, and was extremely friendly. It’s exactly what you want when you have a casual meal at a place like this.

My family and I went to Lou Malnati’s today to celebrate before I go back to college.

The atmosphere had a somewhat nice ambience, with stained-glass portraits lining the backs of the eating area and decent crowds of people grubbing it up.

The service was solid, with our waiter checking on us multiple times and being very friendly.

The food, on the other hand, was subpar.

The pizza was pretty good and the salad was delicious, but the pasta is a never-again order. The crust was crispy, the dough was slightly sweet, and there were a decent number of toppings. The salad had a delicious, sweet, and tangy dressing and a lot of add-ins. But I could’ve made a better pasta at home for way cheaper.

The price in general was a bit over-the-top. The pizza was about 35 dollars, and the pasta was 15 dollars. For the portions, it was not worth it. But for a once in a while experience, it was decent.

At the end of the meal, I felt very full, but also somewhat lacking in quality. I recommend the pizza and salad, but the pasta left me wanting more from it.

Had a deep dish to go since I was in the area and I wasn’t sure if I ever had a proper deep dish Chicago style pizza before. Ordered a small veggie one w sausage added along with tiramisu about 40 minutes ahead of pick up. This size of pizza was enough for 2 with  leftovers for another meal/day. It was delicious and I can’t wait to have more next time I am back in the area. Tiramisu was ok, just average, but good enough for a sweet bite after the meal

We get Lou Malnati's take out pizzas when driving near Chicago. This unique Chicago style deep dish is delicious! Lots of cheese and toppings. The tomato sauce is fresh and tasty.

We love that we can buy frozen pizzas to bring back home with us 150 miles and the family loves it too!

Highly recommend giving them a try.

formatted_address: 5343 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60640, USA
name: Calo Ristorante

reviews.text:
Quick lunch with mom today...went to this spot on her recommendation ,and glad I did!

Couldn't help but try the lobster stuffed ravioli...yum!

Add a Kentucky Mule and some pistachio gelato for dessert?  Yes please.

The meal was delicious...definitely would go back and try another dish.

I'd heard good things. I went there and those things were confirmed.  I ordered grilled Calamari with a side of pasta. It was so good. My first time having grilled Calamari. It came with beans and I wanna say kale. It was delicious.  My pasta was as well. There are many items on the menu. I have to return to try more. Oh, my waiter was great. He made recommendations that were suitable to me. Great place. It fills up quick so it's best to make a reservation.
Good food, friendly server, however charged same amount for pasta dish that had no scallops. Forgot contorni. But cheerfully offered to bring it. Check your bill before leaving.

Calo Ristorante in the heart of Andersonville is a phenomenal Italian restaurant full of vibrant and energetic people! The food of course is top-notch. We have been here many times and every single thing we have had was served to perfection.

Outstanding restaurant!!! My Frutti Di Mare was the best I have had, and it is an entree I usually order when on the menu. My wife ordered the Gorgonzola Gnocchi which was amazing. Like a nice bourbon with a different finish, each bite hit the pallette with 3 different flavors. It was amazing, and I am under selling it.
Finally, any restaurant that has almost a dozen different Belgian Ales on the menu gets 4 stars as a baseline. The food should add another 6, but alas, I can only give it 5 stars.
Updated: I have nothing to change about my initial review. Still awesome.

formatted_address: 3135 W Addison St, Chicago, IL 60618, USA
name: Little Caesars Pizza

reviews.text: I visited this store on 23 Apr 2025 at 1:38PM. I hope the corporate sees and reads this review. This branch is located in a very trendy neighborhood and a central intersection. I was shocked to see the condition of this place. There were dead roaches in the store where people grab their food. It was really bad because they were big roaches. I took photos and will report this to the City of Chicago to make sure this place gets inspected properly. Such a pity, they are damaging their image instead of thriving in a nice area. I dumped the two pizzas that I bought and there goes my $20!

Absolutely terrible delivery food I received today. I’ve been coming to this location for years and never encountered a problem here. Pizza is clearly raw and doughy at the bottom and they wouldn’t offer to make it right by replacing it. I was even willing to drive for the replacement. I will never order from here again.

Hello reader, I came to this little Caesars for a regular box of pizza. With tax in total that should come out to 8.30. Now let’s do simple math. If I hand over a 20 for an 8.30$ pizza I should get back 11.70. Well the cashier actually only handed me 1.70.
I’ll take accountability for not double checking or asking for my recipe( that never printed out).but how do you forget to give a whole 10 dollars change.
I went back the next day because I honestly didn’t notice until I got home. The owner( I assume) and the guy who took my order tried to tell me that there was no way they owed me 10$ because the cash register “wasn’t short”, that’s not how it works it would’ve been over 10$ not short 10$. After a bit of explaining him simple math he gave me my 10$.
Don’t go here, not because of this mistake but because it’s tasteless pizza with mediocre customer service and an establishment with the same rundown look from when I was a 7. I know about three other little Caesars that actually make really good pizza; made by teens who don’t mind fixing their mistakes.
We came in for lunch tinking it is a good option , guess what , food is sucks service not professional not friendly , I won’t even think recommending pass by!!

Horrible customer service. Argumentative that they didn’t make a mistake. They literally handled us the pizza like this and my son always checks it before we walk to the car, so one minute walking back in this never happens. If you work in customer service, please learn not to be argumentative with nice paying customers. I insisted on a refund and will no longer go to this location. I will contact corporate. Guess these girls think they own Little Cesars. Thanks my son really wanted his pizza.

formatted_address: 5608 W Irving Park Rd, Chicago, IL 60634, USA
name: Little Caesars Pizza

reviews.text: Cheese came undercooked, and the sausage was overcooked. 🤔 They forgot the marinara sauce for the order of breadsticks. Aside from all this, they've got pretty bad service.  I'm good, I'll gladly go somewhere else.

The manager was really nice but who ever made my pizza vale pura Verga photo speaks for itself wish I should have opened my pizza there to return it what a joke two sausage pieces and nothing else lmao

I attempted to have my food delievered today, only to wait over AN HOUR for a place that is less than 5 minutes away from me. I had about 8 people attempt to pick up the order for me and every single time it was rerouted to someone else. If i could walk, I wouldve easily gone to go and grab my order, but I would’ve thought delivery would’ve been convenient. Nonetheless, I tried to call the restaurant for 30 minutes and NO ONE ANSWERED, not even to put me on hold. Safe to say if you want your food delivered, please DO NOT CHOOSE THIS LOCATION, clearly their staff does not even care about servicing anyone.
I gave it four stars because they have never gotten my order wrong,  which is rare but nice. Very limited parking. On Saturday afternoon call in for faster service.
I did delivery, and I expected better from Little Caesars. Half of my whole pizza had NO sauce. I'm disappointed.

formatted_address: 3033 N Ashland Ave, Chicago, IL 60657, USA
name: The Art of Pizza

reviews.text:
Have wanted to try this place for years based on awards and other mentions.

Tried 2 different slices of their stuffed style (what friendly employee said they are known for and the vast majority of what was available by the slice). Style is somewhere between Giordanos and Peaquods. Very bready crust with sauce that’s oregano forward without much/any sweetness. Not particularly my taste but it’s affordable and quick friendly service. Bare bones but clean interior.

I am not going to lie this is probably the only time i have posted a positive review for anything but Carlos left me no choice but to break that streak. In a day where it is hard to not just find someone who wants to work but to be so passionate about the product. I ordered my food and mentioned I had never been here before and Carlos read off the food they had with so much description you would have thought his grandmother owns the place. In fact if she doesn't I will be shocked. If I owned this restaurant I would hope I was aware enough of how lucky we are to have Carlos as the first person they see when my customers walk in the front door. Give that kid a bonus, a raise or a car or something.  He is definitely worth the investment.  Carlos if you are reading this stay the happy, passionate and welcoming person you are. With just who you are and your great attitude you will go far. BTW the food was great to. What a good combination with great service and great food. Sorry the pizza was so good I ate most of it before I could take a picture

I heard good things about this place so I had to try it! The good reviews are well deserved.  The sauce is somewhat sweet but it tastes good, the cheese is plentiful and tasty too. The dough is well cooked and crispy. Lots of searing inside too. However, a bit after eating the pizza I felt very full maybe even stuffed haha! Overall very good!

I’m really a 4.5 stars so gotta give the whole 5. I got the spinach, mushroom, onion deep dish pizza. Very tasty sauce, not overly sweet, but flavorful, garlicky and yummy. The crust is more bready than I prefer but would reheat well if I had any leftovers. I’d heard about this place, so circled back to it when in the area on another errand. Appreciate the non-meat options. Friendly and patient staff guy appreciated as well!

I was very excited to try Chicago Deep Dish pizza for the first time and I was told to come here. To be honest, I get it but I didn’t like it. I feel bad writing this because I don’t feel like I have a say being that I’m not from Chicago.
The crust was very flakey, it was basically a pie crust. As a pizza goes, the sauce was pretty good, the cheese was layered up so I appreciated that.
I would definitely get another slice while I’m in Chicago but I wouldn’t seek it out if that makes sense.

formatted_address: 2022 Central St, Evanston, IL 60201, USA
name: Celtic Knot Public House

reviews.text: Corned beef and cabbage is excellent.  It is a warm and inviting pub and grill.  With great uris fare and drink.

We love the new Celtic Knot. The fish and chips are great with light breading and excellent Cod. The corned beef sandwich is very tasty, and the spicy mustard (ask for it) has a nice kick. The only issue we have had is that, since they have opened in the new location, the amount of corned beef in the sandwich ranges from overflow to not enough to cover the bread even when spread out.  The owners are great and if they see this post we are sure they will correct it. The ambiance is lovely and the Irish music creates a warm and inviting place to sit with loved ones and share food.
Great new neighborhood bar. Good food, excellent draft beers, they did a good job on remodeling of the outside and interior. The staff have always been friendly and attentive. Highly recommend.

Very happy the reopened Celtic Knot is finally here! Stopped in for a Guinness and take out. Looking forward to next time. (Check the recent menu pics for pricing! The Google menu looks like it's showing the pricing from before)
The Celtic Collection is a tasty sampler of some of the best things on the menu! Wash it down with a pint of Smithwicks and you're good to go.

formatted_address: 200 E Randolph St, Chicago, IL 60601, USA
name: Jimmy John's

reviews.text: Not very friendly...visitors of the Aon building and needed to grab lunch due to a meeting delay. Ordered 2 combos, includes sandwich chips and soda. Turkey was plain with just meat and cheese...they charged me $1 for a slice of cheese! Did not realize they didn’t give me the chips until riding 3 banks of elevators and had to go back. Lady said “You were supposed to grab your chips under the register!” Really?! You could have at least told me that when I paid! I’ll NEVER eat at another Jimmy Johns again. Cold, plain sandwiches! Pot Belly has you guys beat!

I wish the Jimmy John's was open inside the Aon Center when I worked here, but it is a welcome addition to one of my favorite Chicago office buildings. The manager is really nice and they are very fast.  I've ordered numerous catered lunches from this location and they do a great job and deliver quickly.
Good sandwiches, location and quick service. It's kind of hidden off the main road so you definitely have to look for the entrance.

I went in to the aon location and asked for a turkey. They gave me tuna, I told the woman I order turkey, the 1st prep guy came down and said rudely you said tuna! I said no I dont eat tuna, instead of apologizing for the mix up he insisted to argue with me and tell me I ordered tuna.  You need to loose the attitude. You just lost a customer I'll take the walk and stand in line for potbellys

The people who run this location are totally incompetent! They never get your order right. Some days they have no bread. Some days they randomly close in the middle of the lunch rush even though you can see them making sandwiches through the window. They must work really hard to be this bad!

formatted_address: 4999 Old Orchard Shopping Ctr, Skokie, IL 60077, USA
name: California Pizza Kitchen at Old Orchard

reviews.text:
Read through several of the reviews to see if I would experience any of the things other people found good or not so good.
Here is my experience.
We signed in online and when we arrived the host sat us within about a minute on a Friday at 6 pm.
The server was at the table within a few minutes and we ordered drinks and our food. Not our first time so we were ready.
Wedge salad arrived at the table before our drinks. Good chucks of bacon a generous portion of dressing.
Endless Sunshine drink, good and refreshing. See photo.
I had the Mushroom Pepperoni Sausage pizza. My favorite and still good.
With gluten allergies in the family I appreciate the separate prep area for gluten allergies.
Well, for dessert they were out of the Pumpkin Cheesecake so I went with the Butter Cake. Pushed through and ate for sport to get it all finished.
And Nick was great!

This is my first time at the California Pizza Kitchen located in Old Orchard (Skokie, IL) and it's been since pre-COVID when I last ate at another location. Met a friend for an early dinner on a weekday. We stood at the front of the restaurant before anyone acknowledged us and seated us. There were only three tables occupied and several people at the bar. Our waiter was friendly and attentive. Bread and seasoned olive oil is complimentary. We ordered Mexican Corn and the Wild Mushroom Pizza. It was very good. Our waiter told us about the Take & Bake $9 Pizza, so I got the Margarita Pizza for tomorrow. Thanks and I'll be back to try more pizzas.
Excellent experience! Food and service were perfect. Highly recommend!!!

Worst pizza I've ever had
beer, rather piss water
coffee, no, no, no cold slop
bad experience, terrible pizza

This restaurant holds a special place in our heart, we love going to CPK for birthdays and special times. The buffalo cauliflower and artichoke dip are incredible appetizers. The garlic cream fettuccine and pizzas were extremely fresh and delicious! Lastly, don’t forget to get the butter cake, the texture is so incredible and the ice cream goes extremely well with the butter cake.

formatted_address: 18162 Harwood Ave, Homewood, IL 60430, USA
name: Aurelio's Pizza of Homewood

reviews.text: This place is really, really cool!  Very old school pizza parlor vibes.  The pizza here was delicious!  We ordered a sausage and garlic cooked in the old oven.  Definitely request the old oven because it's better!  I highly recommend this place.  We will be back!

There are many places to enjoy Chicago-style pizza and this place has years of experience and deliciousness that many families have grown to appreciate. The atmosphere reaps of nostalgic expectations and desires when visiting the south suburbs of Chicago. Located near the train station and downtown Homewood.

As a loyal Custumer since 1995 , I can confidently say that Aurelio’s Pizza in Homewood is a true gem! The moment you walk in,you’re greeted by a warm and inviting atmosphere that perfectly complements their delicious food.

The Pizza here is nothing short of amazing.the sauce strikes the perfect balance between tangy and savory,and the toppings are always fresh and generous. Every bite is a reminder of why I keep coming back. Whether I’m enjoying a classic pepperoni or one of their specialty pizzas, I’m never disappointed.

The spacious layout of the restaurant makes it ideal for family gatherings or casual nights out with friends . The staff is always friendly and attentive, adding to the overall positive experience.

If you’re in the area and craving some great Pizza, Aurelio’s is the place to be it’s been a staple in my life for decades, and I can’t recommend it enough.

Excellent pizza - good structural integrity and it holds the toppings well. The pepperoni is flavored so well! It’s charred and the extra Parmesan cooked onto the pizza is so good and adds a good flavor.

I loved Aurelio’s! I got the Sausage and Pepperoni pizza, which was delicious, and the breadsticks were honestly better than Olive Garden! Overall, this is a great place, but it might be very packed when you visit because of its new publicity from Pope Leo XIV. It’s a great place to visit if you want pizza. -Henry

formatted_address: 200 N Jefferson St, Chicago, IL 60661, USA
name: Jimmy John's

reviews.text:
By far the worst JJ location I’ve ever been to. Not taking cash, slowest service, nothing freaky fast about this location.

Staff allowing homeless people hoot and holler and accost people in the lobby. Restaurant had a strange funky smell to it, i wish I could’ve taken a pass on the free smells.

The absolute worst location.  The workers here don't care at all.  I was behind two women and the workers did not even greet or acknowledge our presence at all.  The women eventually left.  I left too.  It's so egregious, it's almost funny.

Line out the door. Confused orders. No Whole Wheat bread!  I tried the Unwich and it just felt like it had half the food as a whole wheat bread sandwich. Liquid all over the floor as you enter but no wet floor sign. I told them about it but they said they knew about it. Lawsuit waiting to happen.
Employees were inside but the door was locked despite the signs on the door and Google maps saying it was open. The employees on the inside gestured that they were closed.
This is probably the best fast-food chain in Chicago. The french is bread is amazing. The quality is great. I recommend it.

formatted_address: 3737 N Western Ave, Chicago, IL 60618, USA
name: Pete's Pizza

reviews.text: Ask for Carlos!!! He is AWESOME and a great worker!  The food is always great!  We had the thin crust sausage pizza (delicious as always)!  We also had the ribs, mozzarella sticks and buffalo chicken wings!  Everything was PERFECT!  Will definitely go back again and again.

I've been coming here since high school, and it’s always been consistently delicious. The morning slice deal is still super affordable, and the pizza never misses—crispy, cheesy, and just the right amount of grease.

On my most recent visit, there was a new bartender—an absolute beefcake named Mike (or maybe Michael?). Honestly, between the killer food and the view behind the bar, it's hard to know what to focus on. They’ve got these big garage-style windows that let in tons of light, but trust me—you won’t be taking your eyes off the bartender.

Mike recommended the pulled pork sandwich, and let me tell you—it blew my mind. You wouldn’t expect a pizza joint to have one of the best pulled pork sandwiches in Chicago, but here we are. Do yourself a favor and try it.

And hey—don’t forget the RORO Battle Pass.
Our go-to pizza. Today's stuffed spinach was delish. Crust perfectly cooked to a near pastry. Just the right amount of their amazing sauce. So good

Not what it used to be. This place has gone completely downhill since they started offering BOGO deals on uber eats, which they no longer even offer. Yet even after removing the deal, the sauce is disgustingly salty (instead of nice and sweet which was always THE reason you buy from here), clearly was made hours ago and sitting under a heat lamp (yet the wait time is still the same), and seriously undercooked. Did they replace their entire kitchen staff and replace all the ingredients? Today’s pepperoni pizza made us sick to our stomachs and could barely eat it. Depressing, because this used to be one of my favorite spots for tavern style in the city and I have decades of memories of loving their food. I don’t think I’ll ever order from them again if it stays like this.

We love Pete's! Their regular pepperoni pizza is our favorite.  The others aren't as amazing but this one is killer.  Great drink selection and open air feel when it's nice out with their big open windows wall. Pastas are ok,  cheese bread is great. Salads are good,  great ranch dressing. Like the mozzarella sticks too.

formatted_address: 1424 W Chicago Ave, Chicago, IL 60642, USA
name: Five Star Bar

reviews.text: The service was great. The bartender was attentive. I wish my wings were a lil saucier but overall the wings were okay. I appreciated the thickness and flavor of the ranch and blue cheese. Sunday morning/afternoon time was a very lively environment. I loved the look of the bar but the bathroom that day needed some upkeep. I will most likely be giving this bar another chance and I will try more of the food.
Great place. Great buffalo chicken dip & the pizza, beer, shot combo is a must! Pizzas also very good as well. Would highly recommend.

I ordered a beer that was $9 they gave it to me, I ordered a second one and they were out so they gave me something else that was $8 but charged me $9 for it. I don’t care that it was only 1 dollar different it’s the principal of running a business to charge me for what I actually got. I left a tip in cash but they still chose to charge me an extra $10 on my card. Their bartenders are scammers, please avoid. This happened 5-24-25 so make sure you take a photo of your receipt!
Fun bar to hangout after work.   Had a very tasty pizza slice.  Decent prices and drinks were good.  I'd go here again.
5 star is receiving 5 stars from me. Awesome people, delicious food, and vegetarian burgers! Fair priced everything. Go take a seat and fill your tummys

formatted_address: 840 S Waukegan Rd Ste 110, Lake Forest, IL 60045, USA
name: Jimmy John's

reviews.text: The bread is the star of the show; that’s for sure.  Fast, friendly service and good, consistent quality makes this chain a leader in the sandwich industry.  Can the sammie’s have more meat?  Yes.  Can they have more cheese? Yes.  Do you get “lockjaw” with every bite?  No.  Are you satisfied when you are done?  Absolutely.

I've ordered deliver from this location for 7 years. Order is always correct, and it's FAST!

I was in a bind today - I ordered take-out and unfortunately, my car wouldn't start when I went to go pick it up. Called the store and they had it delivered to my office. Great service!!

Today I went in everything seemed okay except when I got my sandwich the young black girl asked if I wanted my receipt but I did not hear her the first time, so when I asked it’s the receipt ? I said no thanks since I was given the option.  and while I was walking out she starting talking about me to her co workers making fun of my reaction when she asked me. I only knew cause I heard her say that girl something and then  the gentleman walking out behind me told me I was being made fun of, which confirmed my suspicions. I told him , why ask me if I want my receipt after i already paid because I should have got it then and the cashier didn’t give me one.?I should have got it when I paid, my opinion. Which I don’t care but This also happened to my co worker Samantha just a few hours before me today and when I got back to work I told her what happened and she said the black girl did the same thing to her. Inappropriate and unprofessional for one. Two just make the sandwich and put the label on it if that’s the receipt she’s referring to cause other locations just slap the order info on it. Three your job is really not that hard. It made us feel not good. We both work at LF school district as teachers and her behavior is unacceptable. I’m sorry.

Delivery service was terribly slow. We were told they were a little busy for lunch, expect an hour delivery, 2.5 hours later after being promised multiple times our lunch was on the way, our food finally showed up. While waiting for an order for 7 people, orders placed later for individuals were delivering to our business address. Don't trust that your food is on the way when they claim it is.
The staff are extremely friendly and it is always such a welcoming environment stepping foot into this place. Wonderful spot for lunch if your in the Forest lake area, they won’t ever disappoint

formatted_address: 3552 N Southport Ave, Chicago, IL 60657, USA
name: Southport Grocery and Cafe

reviews.text: Spent a nice weekend morning walking around Southport and finally stopped in here to try and it was delicious. Nice casual vibes inside, and there was a fun selection of all kinds of jams, sauces, and other fun baking items for purchase. The breakfast we got was also delicious, with the breakfast sandwich being as tasty as can be and the bread pudding pancakes being a perfect savory bite to share. The sausage on the sandwich was delicious and it was light but filling. The bread pudding pancakes were so good but just note, they are a little dense. Maybe more cake-like compared to standard pancakes. But definitely worth getting. Really looking forward to going back.

Went on a Sunday, sat right away (group of 2). Service is quick, seating is a little tight, but the food is high quality and pricing is fair.

The pancakes are exceptional. Order the breakfast sandwich if you don’t know what to get!

Gluten free cupcake pancakes are great! Chorizo and eggs were also excellent.
The cortado was a nice way to start the meal.
Parking on Southport can be difficult but lucked out and there was a spot right in front of the restaurant.
Picked up some marshmallows on the way out. If you like marshmallows stop by and pick some up.

​Stopped by Southport Grocery and Cafe for brunch after hearing all the hype. The place has a cute vibe, but man, it gets packed—had to wait about 30 minutes for a table. Ordered the famous bread pudding pancakes and the brisket & gravy. Pancakes were solid but didn't quite live up to the buzz, and the brisket was tasty but kinda on the small side. With a coffee and tip, dropped around $25. Service was friendly but slow, probably 'cause they were slammed. Overall, decent spot, but not sure it's worth the long wait.

I had one of the best brunches of my life here! The bottomless coffee was amazing, and all of the house made food was absolutely delicious. I highly recommend the bread pudding pancakes or at least the side of one.

formatted_address: 5 Woodfield Mall Space D313 Spc D313, Schaumburg, IL 60173, USA
name: P.F. Chang's

reviews.text: Been going to different PF Chang’s since the 90s. First time here in Woodfield Mall in Schaumburg, and the old standby favorites of mine are still as good as ever. If you happen to be in the NW suburbs of Chicago, and visit what used to be one of the biggest mall in the US, this place is worth visiting for your old favorites. Friendly service and we were able to get in quickly in the evening.

Brittany, our waitress was amazing. We were a party of 12 and she was extremely patient and wonderful.
Also, 10000 points for sitting our group as we arrived and not having to annoyingly wait for everyone to be here to be seated.  There was traffic and parking lot was full, so we truly appreciated this.

If you are in the area and need to grab a bite after 9:30 pm PfChang is open to serve you. I overslept at my hotel after a long day at work. Most of the restaurants in the area were already closed. Opened google maps, search restaurants and found PF Chang opened. Ordered take out sushi and a house salad and it was quick and fast.

P.F. Chang’s never disappoints! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, and the service is always top-notch. The food is absolutely delicious—everything is fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. The lettuce wraps are a must-try,  I also love their cocktails. Whether you’re here for a date night, family dinner, or just a casual meal, P.F. Chang’s delivers a fantastic dining experience every time. Highly recommend!

Med-high class Chinese (American) restaurant. Definitely better vibe than random Chinese restaurant. They have good Chinese-inspired food and also vegeterian options. Lo Mein is pretty solid. Vegan wrap(?) with tofu was pretty amazing. Vegetable spring rolls are great!!! I don't recommend Korean fried chicken here though.

The service was pretty good: welcome with smile, server comes to check occasionally, and answer questions kindly.

Parking was a bit terrible. It was a random weekday lunchtime, but how could there be tons of cars near the mall?

formatted_address: 519 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Beatrix

reviews.text: Gluten-free menu was just shy of the full menu, which is great. Waitress was super thorough, because we also have a dairy allergy, and she came back and told us that the cream corn for the fish tacos was made with coconut milk. We certainly appreciate that kind of thoroughness. Staff was professional, ambience was great—overall very nice experience.

We had a great meal here. I compared the gluten-free menu to the regular menu and there were very few differences, except for the desserts. Plenty of choices here — even a gluten-free fryer! Our server double checked items for my other dietary restrictions, as well. Highly recommend!

Great spot with chill outdoor seating and great service. The fresh ginger lime kombucha was light, crisp, and gut friendly. Chicken meatballs were packed with flavor, and the slow-roasted short rib was fall off the bone tender and insanely tasty. Solid all around definitely a place worth revisiting.

I visited Beatrix during a trip to Chicago and had a great breakfast experience overall. The scrambled eggs and chicken sausage were absolutely amazing—flavorful, well-cooked, and definitely the highlights of the meal. I also tried the orange juice, which was tasty but didn’t seem freshly squeezed, which was a bit of a letdown. The avocado toast was just okay—not bad, but nothing standout. I also had the green juice, which seemed fresh but could have used a bit more flavor. Despite a few minor misses, the quality and vibe of the place made it worth the visit. I’d definitely go back to try more of the menu!

Very beautiful restaurant and the atmosphere is welcoming. The food itself is okay, not the best brunch in the city but good; I ordered the Migas Breakfast Scramble. Their biggest selling point might be the atmosphere and the fresh squeezed juices. Nice for a cute brunch.

formatted_address: 600 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60610, USA
name: McDonald's

reviews.text: Went there for ice cream, we were a group of 10 people. Ordered through display, everything went smooth and pretty fast. The only thing was their parking lot entrance being closed, so we had to drive around to get into it from the exit. The building itself it very big and spacious,  and lots of seating available.

The food is exactly what you expect from McDonald's - it's fast, relatively affordable and offers a tasty dose of nostalgia. But what I really liked about this McDonald's is the unique architecture. This flagship location has a large and airy dining room with visible greenery and solar panels designed like a pergola over the building. It's quite striking inside and a nice spot to have a quick and indulgent meal.

Parking was a bit confusing, but wasn’t tight. Didn’t interact with staff, but the kiosk was quick and efficient. Wait time was at max 5 minutes, and the food was hot and delicious! I loved both aesthetic and the trees in the roof. One of the best McDonald’s in the Midwest!

Learned that McD HQ are located in Chicago at Burger University. This location is located in River North and have a modern study spot vibe. The ambience was very calm, quiet, and many tables with outlets. The menu is not different from your usual McD. I would go to Burger University instead if you want to explore the international menu items!

The wall of plants is mod but in need of attention especially with a more feasible way to water them. The homeless seem to gravitate inside at night which requires the staff blocking off areas so patrons can only come in one door and exit out another. Conceptually it's cool, like something Epcot should bring in their watering system to help out.
This has great potential, it's just needing a few tweaks.

formatted_address: 301 S Halsted St, Chicago, IL 60661, USA
name: Meli Cafe

reviews.text: I travel often through Chicago and love stopping here for breakfast or brunch. Having tried several menu items, I am happy to review Meli positively for flavor, portion/price ratio, and overall atmosphere.  If you're in the area, consider supporting this small business. As a nice bonus, this location is block away from the LaSalle Blue Line

We take our company guests and interviewees for breakfast here.

The entrees including omlette, pancakes and waffles are huge. Good for two.

After trying many combinations I have found the following to works for me without wasting food.

Parfait
Toast

Or
Greek yogurt
Special oatmeal

Or

The shakshuka (sometimes they have lamb shakshuka)
It comes with one pita but you get more pita if you ask

Or
Parfait
Cherry chicken sausage side
Chai tea (seasonal)

Or
Yogurt
Toast side
Apple cider (seasonal)

Or
Greek yogurt
Cheddar grits
Coconut (seasonal)

Highly recommended.

Nice diner experience. A great place for brunch. Minus a tiny bit because everything says no substitutions, so if you don't like feta you can't get a veggie omelette with cheddar for example, and of you don't eat meat you can't get eggs and pancakes without paying extra for 2 meats you don't want. Good prices

Delicious food and excellent customer service. Went with a party of 3 around brunch time on a Saturday. Was a 15-20 minute wait, and they have a lobby, which you can sit and wait. Very spacious. Loved the menu and drink selections. Tried the Meli's Sunrise, which is a mango mimosa. Staff was on it and quick on the move to clean tables, get orders, and make sure clients were all okay. Will certainly return!

I guess a dedicated gluten free and vegan menu as well as fresh made juices (except orange) is what makes this breakfast restaurant special. Other than that, nothing extraordinary. Customer service could be better. Atmosphere was nice but thankfully it was not busy, otherwise it would feel too crowded in there. Expensive prices but generous food portions and meals had a good taste. Eggs Benedict needed more hollandaise. Apple juice was perfect. They do not serve alcohol in this location. Also, there is a 90 minute table limit.

formatted_address: 3123 N Broadway, Chicago, IL 60657, USA
name: Intelligentsia Coffee Broadway Coffeebar

reviews.text:
The best coffee shop in Chicago. The espresso is bold and rich, and the milk is expertly frothed—consistently top-notch quality. Becca is fantastic at this location, always delivering great service!

I also appreciate their commitment to fairness by not upcharging for non-dairy milk, unlike some other places. Well done!

That said, a couple of small improvements would make this spot even better. A punch card or rewards system would be a great addition for regulars. Also, they should offer 16 oz “for here” mugs to match their drink sizes—right now, if you want a 16 oz drink, you’re stuck with a disposable cup, which doesn’t make much sense. I am a huge believer that cafes should not only use disposable cups.

Aside from those minor tweaks, this place is truly exceptional. Highly recommend!
I missed Intelligentsia in Pasadena, so I visited this one. The coffee tastes best, as always.
The coffee was great, matcha latte so milky and i can feel the good match power quality. that might be why it cost over $8 for a regular one. But the service was cold. The environment is quite noisy.

Their drink selection is delicious but a little on the pricier side compared to other coffee shops in the neighborhood. The food is all really tasty and well-worth the price, and the staff is always super friendly. My only issue with Intelligentsia is that their wifi is unreliable more often than not, with either very slow speeds or random connection dropping. It might not be a great place for doing remote work, but it's a great place to meet up and enjoy a drink.

Great coffee. They have a pretty large sitting area inside and they also have outdoor seating. I love their iced coffee with oat milk and Stevia. They don't have Splenda. The oat milk and half and half are out for you to put in yourself. They don't have sugar free syrups. They have regular syrups. Also they have a great app but no rewards program. I wish they offered their customers some kind of incentive for choosing them over all the coffee shops in the area. All in all a nice place. It's clean and the staff are friendly.  They do offer coffee beans and ground coffee to take home. They do have some pastries for sale.

formatted_address: 955 W Randolph St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: La Colombe Coffee Workshop

reviews.text: The quality of their espresso has gotten worse over time. Try Drip Collective instead or stick to their mixed drinks. I loved coming here for espresso and their ceramics set them apart back in the day, but it’s just not what it use to be.
The oak mill draft latte is such a great drink. One of my all time favorites. This is also my favorite brand of coffee. The take home cold brew gallon Is also nice and strong.

Been to many coffee spots and always try to get something different. I had the draft latte with oat milk. Tastes great! Very creamy and smooth not overly sweet. Excellent service and if in the area again will try something else

The coffee here is OK for me.  I am a big Blue Bottle fan, and the only thing I drink from Starbucks is the flat white, the flat white here is comparable but no size selections, basically a tall and not served very hot.  The mocha tasted like water down hot chocolate, couldn't really taste the coffee last part whatsoever.
Good service, there is free sparkling or flat water self serve.

I get their oat draft latte with simple syrup hits every time! 10/10 recommend if you are a fan of coffee and oat milk! I ordered this drink twice once in the morning and once in the afternoon. Consistent! Taste amazing!

formatted_address: 26 E Congress Pkwy, Chicago, IL 60605, USA
name: Cafecito

reviews.text: A cute destination. Cuban rhythms coming through speakers fill the air with a festive feeling.  You wait in anticipation of an exotic meal. It comes and it does not disappoint. My meal was delicious.  The flavors of the food were there with every mouthwatering bite.  They do breakfast, coffie, sandwiches, and have pastries as well.  Certainly worth your hard earned dollar. I think you'll enjoy.

Food was fantastic, great portion size for the sandwiches. The plates were also great. Cafe con leche pleasantly surprised me, almost like a light latte. Would definitely go again and try a sandwich and coffee. Bathrooms are a bit dirty though and service could be slightly more approachable

TLDR: affordable, delicious

This place is a gem that is always busy but never overcrowded. The Tilapia sandwich is a personal favorite. 🤩 vibes are good, not over stated. A reliable lunch option.

Fast service even when busy, and the food is fantastic! Super kind staff with serious hustle. Don't miss the black beans and plantains (in many dishes). Big vegan menu with lots of different flavor options. Breakfast and lunch/dinner menus. Loved the natural light and high exposed ceilings.

The food was great! Felt and tasted very authentic and it was really nice hearing music from the culture. The cashier was really patient with my questions and gave me great recommendations. Got the steak chimmichurri (the steak was a tad tough BUT absolutely loved the chimmichurri, rice and sweet plantains. This is definitely a go to place for a solid and tasty meal!!

formatted_address: 738 W Fullerton Ave, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: Bourgeois Pig Cafe

reviews.text:
There’s something magical about stepping into Bourgeois Pig Cafe—like stumbling into an old storybook where every corner is filled with charm and history. Tucked away in what was once a Lincoln Park apartment, this café has transformed into a cozy, vintage hideaway with warm lighting, mismatched furniture, and the kind of character that makes you want to settle in with a good book and stay for hours. It was packed when I arrived, buzzing with conversations and the comforting hum of an espresso machine, yet somehow it still felt intimate, like a well-kept secret.

I ordered The Old Man & The Sea, and let me tell you, this was no ordinary tuna sandwich. It arrived stacked between two thick slices of house-made multigrain bread, its golden crust speckled with seeds, offering the perfect balance of softness and structure. The first bite was a revelation, the World Famous Tuna Dill Salad was creamy yet airy, with fresh dill adding a bright, herbaceous lift. The celery brought a subtle crunch, while a whisper of red onion gave just enough sharpness to keep things interesting. The ripe tomato slices added a juicy sweetness, and the crisp romaine lettuce gave a refreshing contrast, preventing the sandwich from feeling too heavy.

But the real standout? That multigrain bread. Slightly nutty, with a gentle chew and a toasted edge that gave just the right amount of resistance, it elevated the sandwich from simple to spectacular. Every ingredient worked in harmony, making each bite more satisfying than the last.

Bourgeois Pig Cafe isn’t just a place to grab a bite, it’s a place to experience food in a way that feels nostalgic and comforting, yet refined. I already know I’ll be coming back, not just for the food, but for that feeling of finding something special, hidden in plain sight.

Great coffee shop with fantastic vibes. Lots of seating options and table choices. Huge food menu - I had the breakfast panini and it was delicious!! Huge portion and great tasting. The coffee was not very good and it tasted burnt, I had the iced coffee with almond milk. I’ll try a latte next time

l haven't tried the food here but my reviews will be on the coffee and pastries. I loved the vibe of this cafe. Downstairs was busy but you could still have a conversation and some space, upstairs looks stunning but it was a quiet working area. I got a latte with some sort of fruity raspberry syrup, it was delicious but towards the end I couldn't handle the sweetness. I would suggest ordering with less pumps of their syrup. The have such a wild selection of teas which I adore as a tea lover. The pasties were basic but delicious and I enjoyed them!

Every time I come here, it feels like traveling back in time. Looking at the books on the shelves, I can’t help but wonder who might have read them back in the day. The ambiance is incredible—so unique and original. The coffee is delicious, and the Italian panini might just be my favorite. Also, the blueberry muffin is absolutely perfect for me!

A truly inspiring place, beyond their delicious food. If you enjoy  laptop cafe remote work, this place will take your experience to another level.

PROS: great food, delicious sandwiches and beverages. Staff is very professional and welcoming. Unique indoor vintage atmosphere and gorgeous/quiet garden seating available.

CONS: It's hard to think of anything really. Parking is a bit complicated, which enhances the quietness and relaxing atmosphere.

formatted_address: 1462 N Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: The Wormhole Coffee

reviews.text:
Nice atmosphere. Cool niche posters and knickknacks! There aren’t a whole ton of spots to sit down, especially during busy hours and days. We came at 4pm on a Saturday and it was super busy. I can’t imagine what it’s like early on a weekday. Because of that, the service slowed down, but the staff were doing a good job staying on top of it.
I honestly wouldn’t say the coffee or other drinks were anything spectacular. We got a green tea, the Lavender Town, and a hot chocolate. They were all pretty standard.
I would come back for the vibes and to sit down to work or read, but I wouldn’t come back just for the drinks.

I have tried lots of coffee shops in Chicago, by far this place is the best. Taste was very similar with stumptown coffee in nyc.
Only cons were I visited Saturday morning, there were only two workers, the line was very long and it took about over 15 mins to order and grab my coffees. Staff were very friendly though.

Laid back atmosphere with clear values and fun decor. We were there around 10am on a weekday and seating was sparse- clearly a lot of people working remotely there. But, we were able to snag seats. Coffee was well-made.

The drinks were fine but the staff were pretty rude. The barista who took my order didn’t look up at me the entire interaction and came off as very annoyed to be doing his job. I asked if I could please customize something and got a ‘we don’t do that.’ Just weird vibes. By other reviews, sounds like this is the norm. Bummer because it’s a cool spot otherwise.

top tier espresso drinks, 80s style decor and baristas who act too cool for you pretty much summarizes this place. plenty of seating and great for people watching.

the ghostly trio is a perfect fall drink with a perfect balance of sweet, salty and savory

formatted_address: 1039 W Granville Ave, Chicago, IL 60660, USA
name: Metropolis Coffee Company

reviews.text:
Cozy coffee cafe with a solid selection of pastries, hand pies, and their own in house roasts.

Plenty of seating and lots of nice art of the wall that is up for consignment sale. Nice spot all around for a quiet read or working remotely.
I love the oat milk matcha paired with the lentil hand pie and chocolate croissant—never disappointed. That said, I enjoyed the egg and cheese hand pie even more than the lentil one.

Cute coffee shop loved the art work but was less than impressed by the lattes. We got a vanilla one and a specialty holiday latte and the texture was off the milk was super watery and thin. Maybe they use skim or 2% but it wasn't for us. Would not go again.
They make an excellent cappuccino and it is always fun to work there for a little while. It is a great coffee shop to have in the area and worth a visit.

One of my favorite coffee shops in the city. Their coffee is roasted locally and it is served at other coffee shops in the city which is so amazing! They have pastries and food options from local shops and art work from local artists. A coffee shop that really wants to support and promote the community. They always have seasonal menus with clever names & creative flavor combinations.

formatted_address: 2521 W Chicago Ave, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: Dark Matter Coffee - Star Lounge Coffee Bar

html_attributions: Dark Matter Coffee - Star Lounge Coffee Bar

reviews.text:
Cortado on the menu? Yes
Correct size/ratio? Yes
Temp(start/finish): Just right
Foam: not a big head of foam, but very frothy all the way through.  Very good
Flavor: very good flavor
Cup: really cool cup. The texture on the rim felt cool on my lips
Extras: none
First time at this location and they made me a cortado. Coffee and milk tasted great without a burnt taste and service was great.
I really liked the dolor de Oro. The spiciness from the habanero was very prominent compared to some of the other lattes with peppers that I've tried. For me, a spice enjoyer, that's a plus.

I love coffee and chocolate, and they have many mocha options. I love the coffee, the art, the music, the spaces and that it’s open until 9pm. I come here and work for hours. It’s an inspiring place to be at and perfect in every sense.

Impressive taste and unique blends is what drives me there., Different barista every visit, yet the taste is on point every time!  Absolutely enjoy….

In need coffee product and merchandise plenty to choose from, and you can actually sit outside to enjoy your hot/cold beverage.

formatted_address: 68 W Hubbard St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Firecakes Donuts

reviews.text:
I ordered the old fashion donut. It wasn’t too sweet, which I loved! I probably wouldn’t order that specific one again, but I would go back to try another flavor.

Few things to keep in mind:
-They can’t reheat donuts (they are fried, and therefore, do not own an oven)
-We went at night and they only had 3 different donut flavors, if you want a specific one, you will most likely have to go early
- It is only takeout, there is nowhere to sit

It was a pretty decent donut shop. Small but serving many flavors with coffee drinks.

✨Cake donut would be the one I recommend. It was fluffy and soft. Not super moist but not dry. I got a basic glaze one which was nice cause it was not too sweet.

Vanilla yeast donut was unfortunately my style. Taste was normal, and the texture was kinda solid, although not oily which was good.

☕️🥛Cappuccino was good, pretty classic and creamy enough.

We came in at 8am and the display was brimming with unique and beautiful donuts! We got 4 and they were all very FRESH and DELICIOUS! Though they were quite expensive, I would say they were worth the price! The strawberry cheesecake had a good fresh  raised base, complemented by a nice strawberry flavor and cream cheese filling. The coconut cream was NOT TOO SWEET and had a nice crunchy coconut coating. The pistachio old fashioned was one of the BEST old fashioned donuts that I have had! It had a crispy crust; soft, light interior; crunchy nuts on top, and a good nutty flavor. The strawberry jelly was great as well! The jam looked, tasted, and felt like it was made from REAL strawberries! And they weren’t too skimpy with the amount filling too. I would recommend all four!

Tried the classic brioche like valrhona chocolate iced doughnut. Not overly sweet I really like the icing.. you don’t walk into the door you go on the side in the alley and there is a pick up button where you can order and pay. They seem to have quite a few coffee options. I did not try this time, very fast worker with good customer service

I recently heard a lot of great things about Firecake Donuts and their small batch artisan donuts and stopped at the W. Hubbard St. location on my recent trip to Chicago.  I ordered a Pistachio Old Fashioned donut, which is a buttermilk cake donut coated in a Sicilian pistachio glaze and topped with chopped candied pistachios and the calories were worth every bite.  We happened to visit on National Donut Day and recent an additional  free donut as a treat.  I would highly recommend a visit if you are in the area. Unfortunately, I was so excited to try my donut I forgot to take a picture. lol

formatted_address: 210 W North Ave, Chicago, IL 60610, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: Great location. Large interior to hang out or study/work. Good music and cute interior design. Kind staff and manager that check in on guests, helps with ordering, and sometimes gives samples of new drinks. 10/10

I always come here it’s my favorite Starbucks I love how Joe attends to me very friendly very helpful polite like the rest of the staff for this reason I always come here I like to be given good attention and as here I always receive it I always come here

Remember to visit places where you feel happy

I had the most amazing experience at this Starbucks location today. For a few years I have been sticking to 1 specific "Blonde Vanilla Latte",  and hadn't really tried anything else, but my friend ordered Pistachio latte and as I was ordering my BVL, I mentioned it to the manager, who happened to be taking orders, that I had  never tried Pistachio latte, and he was so kind to have one of the baristas make me a small cup as a sample for free. We were also given a pumpkin & pepita loaf on the house. Manager's name is Michael, and I have to say, this Starbucks location really goes above and beyond to make customers feel welcomed and comfortable,  wanting to come back. The store was spotless clean, although it was snowing outside.  Baristas were friendly and nice. Our order was made within a minute, quick and served hot and delicious.  I give 5 stars for Excellent service and great drinks!

It took a few minutes before anyone took my order, just a simple acknowledgment would’ve been nice! Otherwise the store itself is clean and plenty of seating with 2 cute outdoor spaces. Ordered a shaken hazelnut espresso and was delish!

I had an amazing experience at Starbucks yesterday! The customer service was a solid 10/10. The manager, Mike, went above and beyond to help me with my order, especially after the recent change in the matcha recipe. He was super helpful, patient, and made sure I was happy with my drink. Thanks to Mike and the team for making my visit such a positive one!

formatted_address: 5707 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60660, USA
name: m.henry

reviews.text: Excellent place for breakfast. All of the food was exceptional. The staff was super friendly. The coffee was hot and the water glass stayed filled. I would def go back. Short way and great seating inside. All of our meals were served hot and tasty. First come first serve.

Came with a friend and had a great time! We had no reservation and walked in and were promptly seated, however, we did beat the rush and so definitely depends on the time of day and number of people when you come.

The food was very good, well-balanced and made us both big boys comfortably full (haha). Our server came over several times to check up on us and refill our waters, and so we never felt thirsty. A great meal that I would recommend for others to come and dine.

I heard some really good things about this diner so had high expectations.

This is a very ordinary diner. Nothing to write home about. The service is good and the food is okay.

We ordered an Eggs Benedict, an Omelette and some hot drinks. Paid $25 for a person. They also added an automatic 3% which you can ask to not include (I do not appreciate when restaurants do that).

m.henry has been part and parcel of Andersonville for over 20 years. The food is amazing,Service is friendly and informative. Hot coffee is ever flowing. The whole experience is seamless. A great team work that results in an awesome experience. Hot cakes are fluffy  and French toast made with homemade brioche is yum 😋 I had  Pastrami Benedict with perfectly poached eggs.FYI : This place does not take reservations  and closes at 2.pm. A must visit place👍👍

I got to M. Henry at 1:30pm and they close at 2. They seated me and within two minutes said I had to place my order because the kitchen is closing. I would have rather been turned away than be seated and rushed. I ordered a chai latte that came out lukewarm at best. I ordered a below mediocre $17 pancake that was cold in the middle and seemed to be sitting out as well as a sandwich with rock hard fries. The cherry on top of my bad experience was when I ordered a slice of pie to go and when I got home found mold on it. It grosses me out even more thinking about how many people were served moldy pie at that restaurant. Additionally, I’m pregnant and if I ate it would be a major health concern. I called back the next morning and shared with them that the pie was moldy and they said they are busy with other customers and call back around 2. If I ran a business I would have not prioritized serving new customers before making this issue right. I did end up getting a $6 refund on the pie but I feel like I should have been compensated a lot more for that terrible experience. It was never about the $6 just about the principal behind it. Will not be coming back.

formatted_address: 53 E Randolph St, Chicago, IL 60601, USA
name: Intelligentsia Coffee Millennium Park Coffeebar

reviews.text:
I was downtown with a buddy, and we were looking for a quick coffee. This coffee shop was highly recommended by a few different people.

The environment was cozy and comfortable, and the coffee was pretty good. Enjoyed two cortados and a coffee to go.

Really good coffee, fast service too! The staff were super nice and helpful. Their mocha was actually so incredibly delicious, and the iced latte was amazing as well. The inside is super cute and very warm, nice on a cold day. Not too expensive either.

My partner and I recently stopped by Intelligentsia Coffee in Chicago and had a great experience. We ordered a couple of flat whites and tried a few pastries—all of it was really tasty. The coffee was smooth and well-made, and the pastries were fresh and delicious. Even though the space is a bit small, we didn’t have any trouble finding a seat, and the cozy atmosphere added to the experience. The staff were friendly and attentive, which made the visit even better. Overall, it's a great spot to grab a quality coffee and relax for a bit.

My favorite cafe in Chicago! I always get the signature Avena Latte because I love the little kick from cayenne pepper on top of the drink😚 I recently tried Smoked Salt Maple Latte (because it will be gone from tmr) but it was pretty sweet, and I could barely taste salt. I recommend Avena Latte :3

Really good fresh coffee roaster.  Very freundly and kind service.  Great location in the city near the park.  Not a lot of seating but its plenty to stop in for a coffee.  Many not be enough to work from.   Great stop for coffee lovers

formatted_address: 2557 N Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60647, USA
name: New Wave Coffee

reviews.text: Very spacious and trendy coffee spot!! Black Cold brew got a kick to it, and the husband loved his soymilk iced matcha with strawberry syrup! Coming back to try the bagels for sure. Patio is dog friendly! 🤎

Cute shop with an artsy vibe,  spans the width of a corner building so there's an entrance on both sides.

Service. Pastries,  and coffee were good. Very much the type of shop to set up in and work out read a book.

I gotten an almond milk, caramel latte with their oats and banana muffin… pretty good! I loved the latte and especially the sweetness from the foam. I would rate the muffin a 4.5/5 just because the texture was a bit off and I wished the banana flavor was a little stronger… but that’s my preference. Overall, the place was a vibe, they care about the environment. I would definitely come back here for some more and maybe even try out their sandwiches.

The coffee was really good it had a lot of flavor! I got the cold brew with caramel. Be ready for a long line though and minimal seating! It’s in a good location close to the farmers market. The bathroom has a ton of graffiti that is fun to read haha

I have been a patron for many years.  I have many food allergies so I was elated when I found a coffee shop with a vegan sandwich option.  It is always super full with the chickpea blend.  Unfortunately, on at least two occasions now, there has been barely any salad.  I made sure to tip because the service is great, but spending $14 and getting bread and arugula is insane.

formatted_address: 2021 N Stockton Dr, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: Café Brauer

html_attributions: Kait Schmidt Thabet I Celebrait by Kait

reviews.text:
Café Brauer was my absolute dream venue, and the entire experience exceeded every expectation. The space is stunning, the architecture and historic charm speak for themselves and hardly need additional décor to feel wedding ready.

We had the pleasure of working with Ellen from our first tour to the day-of (and even after!) and she was incredible every step of the way. Ellen answered every question and handled every request with such grace and care. I always felt supported, and she truly went above and beyond—coordinating seamlessly with our planner, florist, and other vendors to ensure our day was nothing short of perfect. It meant so much to feel like someone genuinely cared about our day through it all.

We also used Café Brauer’s in-house caterer, Tigerlily, and the compliments haven’t stopped rolling in. Guests are still reaching out to us—as well as our parents—saying it was the most beautiful wedding they’ve attended and hands-down the best wedding food they’ve ever had. I couldn’t recommend Café Brauer and Ellen more. It was everything we dreamed of and more.

reviews.author_name: Kait Schmidt Thabet I Celebrait by Kait
reviews.text: Cafe Brauer is a fabulous wedding venue!! It is such a gorgeous space and I enjoyed working with their team. As a Wedding Planner I highly reccomend this space!!!

A truly stunning venue. Over 14+ years capturing weddings in Chicago, we have had the pleasure of working with a lot of venues. This is by far one of Chicago's shining stars. The perfect mix of location (greenery galore, skyline views, private-esque gardens, close to the lakefront) and history.

I want to love this place, the view and patio are wonderful.  But the service the last two times I’ve been has been really lacking.  Slow, maybe understaffed, or no leader.  When asked about where our food was a waitress said, “I have no idea” and walked away…big potential- not activated…

We can’t say enough wonderful things about our experience at Cafe Brauer and with Tigerlily Events as our caterer—our wedding day was truly perfect, and so much of that is thanks to this incredible team.

From the very beginning, working with Ellen, our event coordinator, was an absolute dream. She was unbelievably organized, incredibly responsive, and endlessly patient. Her knowledge, calm demeanor, and clear communication made planning feel manageable and even fun. We truly owe so much of our stress-free day to Ellen—she thought of everything before we even had to ask and handled every detail with such care and professionalism.

Our guests are still raving about the food—it was creative, flavorful, and beautifully presented. From passed apps to dinner service, everything was top-notch. And the service throughout the evening was just as impressive. Everything ran smoothly from start to finish, with no hiccups at all. We felt so well taken care of, and so did our guests.

The venue itself is absolutely stunning, and the layout worked perfectly for our group of about 165 people. We rented the Honeycomb for our ceremony, which was a gorgeous and unique setting to exchange vows. The Loggia was ideal for cocktail hour—spacious and scenic—and we had zero issues with bathroom capacity even with our full guest count. The main reception space felt full of energy but never overcrowded, and the dance floor was lively all night without ever feeling cramped. Our wedding party loved having access to the upper balcony to tuck away bags and take a breather when needed.

From start to finish, we felt completely supported and so grateful to be in such good hands. The beauty of the venue speaks for itself, but it’s the people behind it—especially Ellen and the Tigerlily team—that make it truly exceptional. Thank you for helping us create the most unforgettable day! If you’re considering booking Cafe Brauer for your wedding, just know you will be in great hands, and you are choosing one of the most beautiful, vintage, unique venues in Chicago!

formatted_address: 412 E Devon Ave, Elk Grove Village, IL 60007, USA
name: Krispy Kreme

reviews.text: I've gone to this location twice in the last 6 months when the hot sign has been on. I prefer them when they are still cooling down. Both times, the staff served me cooled donuts. This time, I asked the staff to serve me donuts off the line, and they rolled their eyes and said they were taken off the line. Even after I opened the box and touched them in front of the staff. The hot sign brings in customers because they want a hot fresh donut, and this location doesn't serve them. Go to the location in Hillside. They serve hot donuts when the hot sign is on.

Staff refused to give me fresh donuts from the belt like they always they do . Ignorant. Possibly racist . Lecturing customers as if it’s first time we order from this place .

The lady who served us must had some trauma in the past. She definitely needs some time off like PTO or something. This should help .

Parking lot is full while there is no single customer in the store.

The cashier was not overly friendly, she was quite dry in her service. I don’t live close by the store and was super excited to grab donuts for my family. I haven’t had Krispy Kreme in over 5 years however with this lukewarm service I won’t be back for a while.

One of the few Krispy Kreme locations actually left. This location is amazing because they actually make the donuts here fresh all day long. Lots of room to sit and have coffee and enjoy also. Highly recommend.

Krispy Kreme consistently delivers a fantastic experience. From the moment you walk in, you're greeted with the aroma of their always hot and fresh doughnuts. The variety is excellent, and I always look forward to trying their new creations – today's Hershey's collaboration is a must-try! My only disappointment is the distance to my nearest store. Delicious pastries that are well worth a 5-star review!

formatted_address: Monadnock Building, 53 W Jackson Blvd, Chicago, IL 60604, USA
name: Intelligentsia Coffee Monadnock Coffeebar

reviews.text: Stopped by here to get some coffee before work and I’m glad I finally got to try it out! It’s a small space with a couple of tables to sit at to enjoy your coffee or to do your work remotely. They have a lot of merchandise as well as some coffee brewing equipment, such as a pour over and French Press for sale too. They have a relatively small menu and only a few syrups for flavoring, such as vanilla (they do not have caramel flavoring). The coffee itself was very good. A little pricey for an iced latte, but the taste and flavor made it quite worth it.

Great spot that feels straight out of the 1920 / 1930s featuring pastries, coffee,  and pour overs.

Service was quick and friendly, and everything i was delicious.  Really liked the wide varieties of coffee they had on offer!

My husband and I stopped by for some coffee and the baristas were very friendly and nice. We ordered Avena latte as well as an Iced Americano. Avena latte had some kick! With cayenne pepper and I thought it was a very nice touch and an interesting flavor 👏🏻
All in all, nice place for a quick coffee stop or to work on your laptop while enjoying their delicious coffee.

Located in the Monadnock building, entrance on W Jackson Blvd.
We were on a "Foodie Tour" and our guide walked us through the Monadnock building. As coffee lovers, we noticed this place and made sure to return after our tour simply because it smelled so good.
I ordered their 'Latte' and a 'Snickerdoodle Cookie'. The latte was the best I've ever had, anywhere! The Cookie was delicious too, very soft with the perfect sweetness to go with my drink. Their 'Daily Batch Brew' is also very good.
There's plenty of tables to sit and enjoy. They also sell merch and coffee bags. Our cashier, Alyssa was very sweet and welcoming.
Overall,  we had a great time here enjoying our evening coffee time and will definitely return when in town.

Elevated coffee experience in a classy well run shop. Batch brew was the seasonal Celebration coffee, which was astonishingly good. Lots of beans to buy and merch to wear, plus gear for brewing. Excellent shop.

formatted_address: 1746 N Wells St, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: Nookies on Wells

reviews.text: Loved it here! We got the Mediterranean skillet along with the Stuffed french toast! Best skillet ever, we enjoyed it very much. Service was great, very attentive and nice. Definitely will come back! Also patio seating is wonderful!

Watching the staff was its own show! They have customer service dialed in to a T. Service was great! Our waiter was funny and kind. I have never had my coffee cup filled more and still never found the bottom of my cup! Amazing place, tucked away on a beautiful street. DO NOT SKIP ON THE STUFFED FRENCH TOAST!!!!

A fantastic diner that's clearly a hit with the locals. We went for a late breakfast, enjoying incredibly filling omelettes, and we're surrounded by locals solving crossword puzzles. We weren't rushed and were topped up with drinks without needing to ask. 10/10 would go again!

The ambience was definitely cool, a modern take on a classic dinner. As for the food, it was definitely over priced for what you got. I ordered the veggie skillet and a coffee. Ended up being over 30 dollars just for that. Also fair warning the hash browns are more like mashed potatoes. The staff were very kind, definitely felt a little rushed to leave though. Overall not a bad spot, just a tad overpriced.

My girlfriend and I had breakfast here on Saturday, and the food was amazing from start to finish. We got their classic French toast with a side of berries. The French toast was eggy and delicious, and the berries were ripe in February! We also had the smokehouse frittata that came with toast and hashbrowns. We also got lattes, and they were yummy. We had so much food that we could only get through half of it. The staff was so sweet- they thought we didn’t enjoy it because didn’t want to take it to go box, but really we were just staying in a hotel and wouldn’t be able to eat it. The service was absolutely stellar, and the service was fantastic. Highly recommend!

formatted_address: 55 E Washington St Lobby, Chicago, IL 60602, USA
name: Pittsfield Cafe

reviews.text:
Hubby and I absolutely loved our breakfast at Pittsfield Cafe. It’s tucked inside a beautiful historic building just steps from Millennium Park, and the atmosphere is something special—high ceilings, marble, and a cozy diner feel right in the middle of downtown.
