The service was friendly and quick, and the food came out hot and delicious. We ordered eggs, pancakes, bacon and hash browns on the side, and everything was cooked perfectly. The pancakes were fluffy, the coffee was strong and constantly refilled, and the portions were generous for the price.

This spot is a great find if you want a classic, satisfying breakfast with no fuss. I’ll definitely be back next time

Wow, the building itself is art. Immediately enamored by the amazing ceiling. The food was terrific diner food. Tasty eggs and perfectly crispy bacon. 3 pancakes with the combo while most places have reduced to 2. Good service and unique atmosphere. Inside is more diner-like but there is a seating area outside of the doors which is beautiful with the amazing chandelier. Glad I tried this place.

Took out food to go but wish we could’ve stayed. Such a beautiful atmosphere, a rare type of experience that transported me back in time. The staff is so friendly and the food is delicious! I’d definitely go back

I can see why this is a Chicago staple! Hidden away in a fabulous building near the park decked in gold.
Got there on a Saturday about 10.30am and queue was small- we were a table of 3 and got one quickly - by then we were bubbling with excitement for coffee and food!

Food took a long time, almost felt like we were forgotten to be honest- but eventually when it came it was great! Coffee constantly topped up and water. Fresh OJ is expensive but the teen said worth it 🙂

I had the hash with corned beef - eggs easy over and WOW.
Teen had the pancakes - and refused to share or surrender to being full! 😂

Chicago's Winslow Building (1925) now houses Pitsfield Cafe. Architect Charles Palmer's limestone Classical Revival masterpiece originally served as First Merchant's Bank until 1938. The restored space features original bronze vault doors, mosaic floors, and ornate plaster details.

The incredible atmosphere—with all that architectural grandeur and historical significance—definitely steals the show here. While the food and service might not reach those same heights, you certainly won't leave disappointed. It's worth visiting just to soak in the space, with the meal and coffee being a pleasant bonus to the experience.

formatted_address: Logan Center for the Arts, E 60th St, Chicago, IL 60637, USA
name: Café Logan

reviews.text: Just a great spot for studying. Working. Meeting for coffee. Perfect set up of seats/tables. Plugs allllllll over the place so you can stay charged! The staff is amazing! So friendly. And the easy breezy light menu is pretty good. For breakfast or lunch. From sandwiches to salads, soups, wraps, chips, etc. A great vibe always!

My experience at Café Logan wasn’t the worst, but it was definitely unpleasant. I originally ordered a Do-Rite donut, which was fine, but when I went back for another, they gave me a completely different donut and insisted it was the same. Having already tasted the real Do-Rite earlier, I knew they were lying, but they remained persistent, refusing to acknowledge the mistake. After looking into it further, I realized that they label all their donuts as Do-Rite when they actually source them from another vendor. This feels misleading and dishonest to customers who expect to get what they’re paying for.

Beyond that, the food is overpriced for the quality. Nothing I tried stood out as particularly fresh or well-made, especially considering the premium prices. While the space itself is nice and has potential, the lack of transparency and the underwhelming food make it a place I wouldn’t go out of my way to visit again. There are plenty of better options in the area that offer higher-quality food and more honest service.

I ordered a latte and and a panini. They were both standard. This is a U of C campus cafe but it’s open to the public. Lots of students & faculty. Great Wi-Fi. Really good place to get some work done. Also great customer service! The ladies behind the counter were very nice.

My first visit to Cafe Logan was solid. It's spacious and bright (floor to ceiling windows along the east wall and part of the north wall) with Wi-Fi and plenty of seats, tables and outlets. I ordered a coffee - it was a nice cup of coffee at a decent price (maybe a little on the high end). The best part was Chicago artist Nikko Washington's exhibit on the cafe walls. I assume (hope!) that they rotate exhibits in the cafe. It's a really nice feature that makes this cafe unique (thus, the 4 star review). I'd probably come back, particularly if there are art exhibits in the cafe that interest me.

Pleasant atmosphere, classy decor, food that aims for "bougie" but ends up so-so.

My main problem with the place is how confusing the setup is. Sometimes they want me to order at the counter, sometimes at the register. Sometimes they custom-make sandwiches for you, sometimes they don't want to. Is that guy standing next to you waiting for his order, or waiting TO order? No way to tell! Is an employee going to take my order, or will the register just stand unattended for the whole lunch rush? Who knows! Even the text on the menu behind the counter is difficult--it's impossibly tiny and switches periodically to whatever menu you're not trying to order from. I often can't even figure out which door to the cafe that I'm supposed to use--it seems to change to various combinations of the three possible doorways. I pity the art students who must rely on this place.

formatted_address: 430 N Clark St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text:
What an amazing experience at clark&hubbard location! All the staff were so nice and greeted people immediately as they are walking in. Also very clean environment the guy kept wiping the floor from all the snow and salt.
You definitely do not come across a starbucks location that is clean with all staff being nice and friendly. I think her name is “cherry” sorry if i got it wrong! She is the star of the place. Attaching picture. All of you guys are amazing and keep up the good work.

Super nice Starbucks with perfect window seats for people-watching . The staff is very friendly. We were there on our way to the protests and they were clean, organized, efficient and super friendly even though they were busy.

Starbucks on Clark is super clean with an awesome contemporary vibe. The location is great, making it a convenient stop. The coffee is consistently excellent, making it a must-visit for any coffee lover. PROTIP: there is a 2nd door on Clark.

I asked literally just for a cup of water to be added because I couldn’t add it on the app I’d appreciate if people would be able to just make it instead of saying “you still have to order that at the register regardless” from Mari. All I needed was an iced water added nothing else I’d appreciate if people were more accommodating and didn’t try to make things more complicated .

Very fast service here! The staff were very friendly and knew that I’d be in a rush, so they got my coffee to me quickly. A lot of people here are putting in mobile orders, so there was a constant stream of people coming in and picking up coffee to go. Plenty of seating here and areas to sit with friends without feeling rushed.

formatted_address: 6701 W Forest Preserve Dr, Chicago, IL 60634, USA
name: Eli's Cheesecake Company

reviews.text: The best cheesecakes I've ever eaten. And the traditional one doesn't raise blood sugar levels like other cakes - tested on diabetics. The only problem is that it's not available during the week for most working people - the store closes at 5pm

Stopped in at 3:50pm as we raced to Eli’s on our way from Wisconsin to Indiana! They closed at 4PM but we just wanted to run in and grab a sampler! The cashier was lovely enough to unlock the doors for us and let us complete our purchase! The staff was friendly and the cheesecake was AMAZING as always. I was a bit sad that our sampler was made up of mostly all Raspberry, but we will try again next time! :)
Soooooooo good!!! The Carmel sea salt is amazing!! One of the top locations in the area!!! This is the BEST cheesecake in the area!!!
The café is a must visit while in Chicago! Eli’s always has a phenomenal selection of food, pastries, and unique cheesecakes. The café also has delicious drinks.
Received a delicious cheese cake from Eli’s as a Christmas gift! - received a few weeks before Christmas, we froze it and have been eating it since Christmas and it’s so delicious!

formatted_address: 1920 W Division St, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: Milk & Honey Cafe

reviews.text: Stopped in for lunch and we were glad we did.  Grilled Chicken sandwich with salad was very delicious.  Cauliflower soup was an excellent combination.  My wife had a veggie wrap.  My dislike was the pickle, too soggy, however that might just be me.  It’s probably ment to be.  The place is cool, like a cozy coffee shop with a warm fireplace.
Everything Was Fresh & Delicious! Packed Beautifully:-) I Appreciated That So I Was Able To Build My Avocado Toast Without It Being Soggy! Tasted Delicious! Waffle.Was Yummy As Well!

I came to this cafe at the recommendation of my cousin and it was great! I got a Matcha and their Turkey Reuben with chips and it was delicious! My friend ordered their Buffalo wrap and said it was great too. Their interior was also modern casual and super chill. The cashier wasn't too friendly though everything else made up for it. Would definitely come again!

They have a very interesting lineup of drinks. I got the cardamom latte. At first, it had a weird aftertaste, so I asked if I can taste the cardamom syrup by itself and decide if I wanted them to remake the drink or just order something else. They graciously accepted my request. I decided to reorder the same drink but with less espresso. I don't think cardamom and espresso is a good combination because the espresso is such a strong flavor.

For my meal I got the jerk chicken wrap. It had a lovely cucumber yogurt sauce. However, it needed salt. I also think the yogurt sauce would be better with properly spiced jerk chicken. Because cucumber is so refreshing, it needs something to refresh. I didn't think the wrap was spicy enough to balance the cooling agent of the sauce. So I think the sauce can end up diluting the overall flavor of the wrap. I liked the addition of pineapple and pickled onions. I left full! I will definitely come back to this place. I know I can have a $25 healthy meal with a specialty drink, sandwich, and chips. It's good for something traveling on a budget

I had their roast beef sandwich with a side salad. I also got some of their chips. It was very good. I loved the sandwich. The bread was super fresh. I also got a chocolate chip cookie it was also delicious. They have Coke products, and have cans of pop. They have a bunch of outdoor seating.

formatted_address: 1916 W Chicago Ave, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: West Town Bakery

reviews.text: I got the chicken melt and really enjoyed it. We also got a few of the cake balls but didn’t really enjoy them. The items we really wanted were gone by the time we got done eating… def get there early for the pastries. Very friendly waitress. Tight seating but would go back.

Superb biscuit sandwich (the Eckhart Park) with great cookery on the sausage patty, eggs, and buttermilk biscuit. I really enjoyed my Dirty Chai Latte. Service was upbeat and very attentive (in a helpful way). They seem to have seasonal espresso-based drinks with fun syrups if you're into that thing (which I am). This place came enthusiastically recommended by a vegan friend, so I'll be back to try their vegan options and seasonal coffee options.

Baked goods are rich and delicious at a good price. We got pointed in this direction by the dispensary next door. It was 25% off there if you bought a baked good. Solid way for businesses to collab and we got to try great new food. The workers were cool and we're going back for breakfast. (Will update after).
Update:
Breakfast was phenomenal. Lots of options (for vegetarians and vegans too). Large portions so you don't leave hungry. We sat on the patio, nice cool morning, great service. The lattes are wonderful.

Awesome bakery! Such a cool/hip environment! Great baked goods selection. I have not eaten regular food here because it’s usually too busy to get a table, but I can vouch for the bakery! Coffee is just okay- too acidic for me. But the baked goods are a WOW! They have outdoor seating on Chicago Avenue.
Feels like a small town breakfast place. We enjoy quality service and various breakfast choices.

formatted_address: 108 E Superior St, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Pierrot Gourmet at The Peninsula

reviews.text:
⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ 5/5

Pierrot Gourmet is a charming gem with a warm and welcoming atmosphere. The green-themed décor is elegant and fresh, and the space is impeccably clean. We ordered the pastry basket, and every single item was absolutely delicious—flaky, flavorful, and clearly made with care. The cappuccino was smooth and perfectly crafted. Highly recommend for anyone looking to enjoy a relaxing and high-quality coffee and pastry experience.

Had an absolutely fantastic breakfast here! The quiche was light and fluffy, with a perfectly buttery crust. It came with a fresh side salad that balanced the richness of the quiche beautifully. The orange juice was fresh-squeezed and full of flavor. To top it off, I indulged in an amarena cherry mousse cake that was delicate and flavorful, paired with a lavender cappuccino. Highly recommend!
The brunch was excellent. Drinks were great. We ordered the croque monsier, which was really good, as well as the shrimp salad. The dessert unfortunately was more style than substance.

The ambiance at Pierrot is a delightful mix of cozy elegance and modern charm.the food is the best especially avocado toast. But it’s the dessert menu that steals the show. The selection of sweets is nothing short of extraordinary. Each dessert is a work of art, meticulously crafted and bursting with flavor.

Cutest little cafe ever!  Located on the corner of the Peninsula Hotel, you’ll find a quaint bakery offering breakfast, lunch, coffee and desserts galore!
Everything was delicious and beautiful, I’m not even a coffee drinker and I ordered a lavender cappuccino and a matcha latte.
Don’t miss this place!

formatted_address: 1105 W Chicago Ave, Chicago, IL 60642, USA
name: Big Shoulders Coffee

reviews.text: Visiting for the weekend and found this gem while looking through other reviews. Iced espresso tonic was amazing, with the walnut coffee cake to match. Service was even better. Smiles, conversation, and a happy vibe. I'll be back when in town again.
Delicious coffee + breakfast burrito but a bit on the pricey end. Cozy atmosphere. We sat by the bar window because all the table seats were taken up, and it was nice to people watch while we ate.

One of the worst experiences I ever had in a coffee shop as a paying customer. I walked into this establishment and was the only person of color in the entire building.
I then went to the register waiting behind someone. Once it was my turn in line no one greeted or acknowledged me. I stood there waiting patiently as the staff helped others and never acknowledged me. I then walked out disappointed by the discrimination and blatant racism. I kept my dignity intact. I don’t recommend this spot for POC maybe another location is not like this but this was just my experience.

I really like the aesthetic of this coffee shop!
It’s really cute. I went right when it opened on a freezing day and the staff was so nice and welcoming.
I didn’t get the chance to try any food but I plan on coming back. I think I need to give the latte another chance :)

Expertly prepared pour over. With a surprising tea-like mouth feel and lots of nuances and complexity in the cup. Plum notes. I definitely recommend! I didn’t plan on buying beans, but I wasn’t leaving without them!

formatted_address: 1339 W Taylor St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: Sweet Maple Cafe

reviews.text:
A classic that never disappoints. Our favorite buttermilk pancake in the entire city. (Other than homemade)

We sat outside, in an open yet covered space in an enclosed screened in patio.

It was very comfortable and delicious.

You have to try it! Some places are just a gem!

Cheddar grits are yummy!
Bus yams butter warm, yum!
Cinnamon roll pancakes are 😋🫶🏼

Great service, small space, sometimes long waits but worth it. Very comfort vibes!

This breakfast joint is a solid 4.4⭐️s.  They have a very nice outdoor seating that is shaded, so even if its 95degrees, it was still fairly comfortable.

The food here is very good.  Started with a fairly large bowl of spicy sausage gravy and biscuit.  It was very filling and the gravy had a nice kick of heat.  Its tolerable even to those that are not into spicy foods.

Their flagship cinnamon roll pancakes was amazing.  I dont really eat pancakes, but this thinner version with crispy edges was worth the price.  The cinnamon swirl is sweet enough that syrup is unnecessary.

The staff here is friendly and accomodating.  Definitely a place to visit in the Little Italy neighborhood.

It looks a little run down( homie, big family kitchen vibe)
Definitely must be a southern cooking aficionado to enjoy food here.
Hardy country vittles indeed.
Pricing average. Decor needs updating.Service average.parking pay meters on street trying.
AWARDED 1 YUM ON A SCALE OF 3

Mom and my usual spot after Dr apt at Rush.130pm on Thursday is the perfect time to go. 1-3 tables filled. Waitress was attentive and friendly. The biscuits are the bomb! Especially with the sweet butter and only if they made their own jelly/jam!!!! Ooowweee!!!😉 I usually opt for lunch, so the grilled cheese on sourdough and tomato soup were the perfect combo for the weather and the temperature in the restaurant. It was SO cold. Otherwise,  5 stars for this popular breakfast joint!!

formatted_address: 275 Parkway Dr, Lincolnshire, IL 60069, USA
name: Liquid Fusion Lincolnshire

reviews.text:
I've always thought of this type of café being an innovative idea with the selection of drinks to kick back and just chill.

Illy coffee is a relatively high end brand up there with the likes of Starbucks which IMHO I do prefer Illy, the bubble tea is pretty good here and I've never had a fruit smoothie just yet.

One thing that's definitely a plus here is the fact that they're open very late, till midnight during the week and 1am on wknds.

Overall the prices are still reasonable, service is on par, interior is kept clean/sanitized and Liquid Fusion is an ideal place to relax and enjoy a drink.

We like this place. The staff seem friendly. Visited this place on Sunday morning. Not much crowded. Seems like quite a place where you can relax yourself or with your family. Ordered lychee and peach with pop-up and milk coffee with boba. Enjoyed them thoroughly.

The staff absolutely crushed it. They were lightning-fast, slinging drinks with ninja-level precision. No grumpy vibes, just pure hustle and charm that turned a quick stop into a highlight. The tea and pearls were killer, but the crew’s energy? Next-level.”

This is a nice little hangout spot to get some late-night bubble tea or coffee. They’re open late and they are busy late too!

That leads to the one issue I have with this place: lack of employees. Line literally takes forever. Only two or three people working at once - not enough people to supply the high demand!

Hot White Chocolate is very tasty. Will be back to have a fruit freeze.

Came in here for a quick boba drink fix. Loved all the flavors they offered. We had the Taro, Thai Tea, and Green Tea Latte and each one tasted so fresh. We add the jelly’s to each of the drinks and it was great.

The service is fast and they have a cute seating area. Do check out this place for crazy good boba drinks.  Drinks are delicious and not overly sweet.

formatted_address: 1120 E Diehl Rd, Naperville, IL 60563, USA
name: Arbor Vitae Java & Juice

reviews.text: Ashraf (the owner) is an amazing and profoundly kind person. His coffee and banana bread are delicious. Try the cold brew! It has a great kick and beats out Starbucks any day.

A delightful little place hidden away in the NIU Naperville Building. I had lentil soup yesterday. It was clearly made in house and honestly the best soup I have ever had. I will be making a trip back there to try some other things soon. They have a great menu full of salads, sandwiches, soups, hot dishes, baked goods, and coffee. Definitely a place to visit.

The owner was very hospitable and offered us hummus while we waited for our food. So accommodating, and the food and coffee were delicious.The food is DELICIOUS and very artistic. They have catering and all the coffee is 100% freshly ground when they make your cup of coffee. everything is made fresh and if it’s not to your liking they will remake it or give you something else, free of charge of course.

This little gem has the best home made soup, sandwiches, appetizers, and dessert in a cozy, friendly, and welcoming environment created by this establishment owner/chef and his wife.

The challenge I have every single time at Arbor Vitae is which soup to choose from the incredibly tasty variety that the chef makes daily. While the chef will offer you to sample all of them to choose, this unfortunately would not help because you would want to have them ALL !!

I actually end up having a bowl (never settle for a cup) of two soups added together in the chef's creative way to minimize the regret of missing out on some. Whether it is the hearty Lentil, the ever-tasty cream of chicken, or the melt-in-your-mouth beef with vegetable, or any of his other creations that he always pleasantly surprise his patrons, there is absolutely no room to go wrong on your selection.

As other reviewers wrote, the sandwiches like the chicken shawerma are incredibly delicious in fresh bread and creative sauces. Salads are garnished in an appetizing way with the healthy olive oil. Other appetizers include the tantalizing home-made smooth flavor-full hummus that you can dip into with warm bread and/or fresh-cut vegetables.

If you have room for dessert, the baklawa is incredible, the cookies are world class, and whatever the chef/owner bakes that day is always a hit.

Further more, if you have something in mind not in the menu that you would like to ask for to be catered especially for you to share with family and friends, do not hesitate to ask. I regularly order soup, sandwiches, hummus, desserts, and other one-off orders and my friends are so impressed that some who live 40 miles away would go to this Cafe asking for an encore experience !!

The two of us had to wait about 40 minutes to be seated. The restaurant was very loud for the duration of our visit. The wait staff was very attentive. We ordered the "Chicken and Avocado Grill" and "Joe's Healthy Chicken Sausage Scrambler" and a side of Canadian Bacon. The Scrambler's portion size was on the smaller side compared to.

formatted_address: 30 N La Salle St Lbby, Lbby 100E, Chicago, IL 60602, USA
name: Einstein Bros. Bagels

reviews.text: The bagel was overall good, but smaller than what I expected. The service was good, and they were quick to take and complete my order. The unfortunate part was they didn't have the tables set up for me to be able to eat the bagel there. Overall, decent experience.

Stopped by Einstein Bros. Bagels this morning, and let me tell you, it's a solid choice if you're craving a good breakfast in the Loop. I got the classic bagel with cream cheese and a bacon, egg, and cheese sandwich, and both hit the spot. The bagels were fresh, soft on the inside with that perfect crispy outside, and the sandwich? Super filling—definitely a winner. The vibe inside is super chill, and I was in and out in no time, even during the busy morning rush. I spent around $12 for both items, and I was full and satisfied. If you're looking for a quick, tasty breakfast, this place is a no-brainer.
Very presentable, very clean, but still the bagel is not the real taste of bagel I hoped to have

Card machines down and cash only. No biggie that happens. I tried ordering via the app since I didnt carry cash. It wouldnt allow me to modify adding butter to the bagel selected. I asked the cashier if I placed the order could they put butter on it. She said "no" because its an extra charge. She then asked another employee (maybe supervisor), who instructed me to order chips to offset the additional cost of butter since they couldnt figure out how to add it either. What the heck is that? All over something that shouldnt even really be extra but at most is .50 and at this point well worth the inconvenience I dealt with and time I had already spent there. I work right across the street and will pick up bulk bagel orders sometimes. I will NEVER be back. Gross incompetence and lack of customer service over .50 cents of butter where if they would have just done it, I would have felt appreciated and been more inclined for future trips back there.  Left my orange juice on the counter and walked out.

Great little place to get a quick breakfast. Ham & Swiss and Bacon sandwiches were very good. Outdoor eating area is nice and spacious. If you have any trouble finding it just look for the umbrellas, the sign isn't obvious unless you're looking right at it.

formatted_address: 1588 N Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: This Starbucks branch offers a spacious and impeccably clean environment, making it a comfortable place to enjoy coffee. The staff here go above and beyond with their exceptional service, creating a truly delightful experience for every visit.

It is very welcome. The building is at the corner of N Damon and N Milwaukee. It is easy to spot. And also open early in the morning which is really great for every early birds. Today Rick is a great helper, he is so nice. If you feel like to have a special cup of coffee you can make a stop here and just order your favorite drink ^^ I am sure you it will make your day. ☕️

This is one of the closest Starbucks Reserve places to me and its location is definitely superb! The ambience is perfect for reading, getting some work done, and catching up with friends. I like that they have classic & house affogato here along with other reserve drinks ☕️🍨!! (Didn’t know cinnamon goes well with affogato but it does, apparently🤭) Also, the building it’s located in is an absolute beauty, so I do suggest coming to this Starbucks if you are in the Wicker Park neighborhood.

First time I’ve been to a Starbucks reserve. They have an extensive menu other than the normal one. There are many fancy looking coffee machines as well in a bar type setting. I ordered my usual americano and cheese danish however I will order from the other menu when I return.

A few days ago, I thought Starbucks is a really great brand, but I need something different, ok in Chicago (Milwaukee - Damen) it is, Starbucks Reserve Bar, Coffe Master prepare four very carefully your coffee, high quality and amazing experience. 100 % recommend.

formatted_address: 1736 W Division St, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: Alliance Bakery — Division

reviews.text:
DO NOT order a cake from here. My order had a mix up with two different people communicating with me about my cake and giving me two different prices. I paid in full days before my pick up date since I was in the area. I Showed the man at the counter the order number and the price I was given on the email. I took my receipt and was reminded of my pick up date and time. On the day of pick up my brothers picked up the cake but the person helping them said that $400 was left to pay. Mind you I came days before showed the man my order number and the price that was given on the EMAIL and paid in FULL. I told my brothers just leave the cake we aren’t paying $400 more. my brothers ended up paying for the cake since they didn’t want my son to have a grocery store cake for his 1st birthday.
Now taste:
This was my first time trying the bakery and I was expecting it to be delicious! It was not and my guest also didn’t care for the cake.
I ordered fresh strawberries and the cake had a layer of strawberry jam. The cake was overly sweet as well.

A bakery with a renowned  artisan.The cakes are visually one of a kind.Fashioned by an expert
Now having said that I had a taste for a pecan roll which was tasty but small and less that average in appearance.
The croissant was ordinary and lacked the buttery appeal.
Parking difficult even with a loading zone.Service average.Decor classic elegance.
I will be back only if I spot an open parking spot.
AWARDED 1.5 YUMS ON A SCALE OF 3

Alliance Bakery is the best! We got our wedding, rehearsal dinner, and bridal shower cakes from them, and we received so many compliments on the taste! They also looked so great. The planning process was smooth as well, and I think their prices were pretty affordable compared to other bakeries in Chicago. We're looking forward to our next occasion to order dessert from them!

We started with Alliance Bakery's at-home tasting kit, which  made picking our flavors easy and fun to do. We wanted a small 6" cutting cake for our wedding and had a specific design in mind. They were responsive and easy to work with to design the cake we wanted for our wedding. The cake itself turned out exactly how we wanted, was delicious, and we were able to enjoy it for a few days after the wedding. We would recommend ordering your wedding cake or desserts for any occasion from Alliance Bakery!

My partner and I are from NC, visiting our friends in Chicago who have raved about this place for years! I can see why! We got a full raspberry ganache cake which is a chocolate cake with raspberry preserves and chocolate mousse filling , chocolate buttercream frosting covered in chocolate ganache 🤤 it was very rich in flavor and the cake was perfectly moist but it was not overly heavy. The flavors were perfect together. The people working there were very nice and both were actually from NC, one was even from the town we live in! Will definitely have to stop here everytime we visit

formatted_address: Depaul Center University, 333 S State St, Chicago, IL 60604, USA
name: Dunkin'

html_attributions: Elevator, Alarm, Coaster and Arcade Productions Inc

reviews.text: Mashair was very helpful with my first Dunkin’ experience, she helped me order a toasted french vanilla iced latte (small iced almond milk latte, two shots of French vanilla, and two shots of toasted almond). It was delicious!
Ordered the Maple Bacon sandwich (which is priced higher) and received regular bacon. Didn’t noticed until I was already to my destination. Check your items always.

I made a mobile order and the employees at the store lost my order. They refused to fulfill my order even after I showed the receipt and my bank statement saying it went through. I contacted Dunkin' Donuts support and they said it went through. Employees still refused to give me my order. This is theft.

Every time I come in, the staff are so welcoming and communicative. Honestly, Dunkin is Dunkin and it's there, but I really appreciate the people who work at this location. They deal with everything and they do it with grace and understanding. Especially when my sensory processing disorder kicks in and I can't decipher anything I'm hearing. Staff, if you're reading this, it's not your lovely accents, it's my disability. You're all so kind and I hope my etiquette properly expresses my gratitude. May your days be filled with laughter and peace.

TLDR; these employees are the reason I continue to patronize this location. They deserve recognition for all the hard work they do for such a busy location.

Forgot why I avoid this branch until I just came from there again. Don’t think I have gotten the right order for years. Just ordered bacon sandwich and latte. Open to start eating at my desk. Clearly just a coffee with cream (not even oatmilk I asked and paid for) and sausage instead of bacon.

formatted_address: 750 N Franklin St, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: i came around 12:30 pm and the service from the employees were amazing the cashier vanessa was very helpful and patient when i didn’t know what to order she recommended a drink i got it and it was delicious!! most definitely recommend this place !!

The employees at this store namely the rotund woman with long bleach blond hair need customer service retraining stat. I stood in line waiting for my pick up order, and I didn’t see mine ready until a few minutes later when I saw other customers waiting for pick up peeling off the cup holder sleeves to find their names… the idiots at this store hide the stickers with our names on them under the sleeve (see 2nd pic). Why should we be touching other people’s drinks to see if they belong to us? And when I asked for a to-go bag or a tray to carry my three sandwiches and two coffees out, I was met with extreme attitude.

Also Starbucks needs to get it together, their food is over priced trash compared to how it used to be just 2-3 years ago. I paid $5.95 for the “double smoked bacon” sandwich shown below. The bread wasn’t even toasted it was literally a cold hamburger bun from Kroger’s bakery section. The bacon was floppy. $30+ down the toilet.

I went into Starbucks to use the bathroom around 8:15 a.m today and was told that I had to make a purchase in order to use their bathroom. I am a CTA worker at this location on the Brown line and our bathroom is out of order. Is this what Starbucks employees are doing now. Will the same thing apply to CPD?

the staff working just after 2pm on 2/8 were incredibly hospitable and made my go to drink better than I’ve ever had it. I haven’t been to this location previously and now that I work in the area, I’ll definitely be back. kudos to those two ✨

The staff at this Starbucks made a great tea for my wife, coffee for me and sandwich for my bride with a muffin..they served it all quickly and effiently. 👏 bravo to the staff. Also the washroom was clean and it all made for a great stop before catching the Chicago L to Wrigley Field this Saturday morning. Thanks you, we will come again!

formatted_address: 5317 N Clark St #2113, Chicago, IL 60640, USA
name: Kopi Cafe

reviews.text: This is a seemingly cute cafe but on the whoa expensive side. I just want to warn everyone, you might think the pastries are reasonable but they are in my opinion, excessively priced. The cinnamon bun, first of all, was not a bun but a yellow cake. It did not taste like cinnamon at all and was $7.99! I have never in my life had a cinnamon bun that expensive and it was nothing special to boot. It was falsely advertised as a “bun” and not only that, the clerk didn’t use a glove to pick it up out of the case. Luckily his finger didn’t touch the cake itself. There was a lot of pressure to “dine in” as I looked at the menu and just was not up for the prices and I clarified that I was going to take it “to go” (not knowing it made a difference). I had already eaten and just wanted something quick. Then thinking I needed to try a bite of the “bun” before I left, I asked for a spoon. He gave me a plastic one. I asked if I could try a metal one since it was supposedly a bun which is thick and tough to cut with plastic, and he responded “the seating is dine in only.” He offered to let me do it but with the most disgusted, disgruntled, impatient attitude. I literally needed like 2 bites on my way out (after tipping $1 on an already ridiculous price) and didn’t want to take up a table for one item vs letting diners have a full lunch. I did not feel valued, or even wanted in the store at all. Talk about judgement and exclusion, wow this attitude sums that up to a T. Sorry to say but I will never be back. Disgusting.

I recently visited Kopi Café in Andersonville, seeking a cozy spot to work on my iPad and enjoy a cup of coffee. Upon entering, I was warmly greeted and seated, which was a pleasant surprise. The café boasts an extensive menu with numerous vegan options, making it appealing for those seeking diverse food choices.

I ordered the French toast from their breakfast selection. While it didn’t quite match my personal taste, others might appreciate its unique flavor. However, I soon discovered that Kopi Café does not offer Wi-Fi, and my cell service was virtually non-existent inside. This made it challenging to work or stay connected online. It seems the café encourages patrons to disconnect and perhaps read or engage in conversation, aligning with its cozy and eclectic ambiance.

In summary, Kopi Café is a charming establishment with a welcoming atmosphere and a menu catering to various dietary preferences. However, if you’re looking for a place to work online or require internet connectivity, this might not be the ideal spot. It’s better suited for those wishing to unplug and enjoy a meal or a good book.
Very helpful staff, a nice variety of seating, welcoming atmosphere radiating skill and creativity. Enjoyed the art and clothing gallery too.
Love their carrot cake and vegan steak tacos! Great Mexican latte as well! Highly recommend this cafe!

Such a cozy spot for a nice warm and refreshing meal! You can sit on the floor which is great for the neurodivergents or those who just want to stretch. The tuna sandwich was so good and packed with healthy flavor. The chai was a good compliment too! Staff were so kind and helped us get great food and drink on a chilly day!

formatted_address: 953 W Armitage Ave, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: Chicago Bagel Authority - Armitage

reviews.text: First time ever having a steamed bagel and I’m honestly not a fan. The bagel was warm but way too moist almost soggy. The sausage and egg were fine but not seasoned. Subbed the cheese for avocado which gave some creaminess and also added some jalapeños for a kick. Overall, a decent breakfast sandwich. Tons of options so always a reason to come back and try it unsteamed.

A quirky bagel place that’s always busy! They have sooooo many options to choose from, and fair prices. Takes a bit to get good cause there so busy but it’s fun to jam to the music and sit outside and wait. However, I would get coffee elsewhere.

Good place to have your breakfast/lunch
Taste really good, and delicious ingredients.
But I wish I had more Salmon in my breakfast sandwich.
And I wish they also had expresso machine.
I had to go to different store to get my Latte.
Definitely recommend this place.

I wanted to like this place more than I did. The food was very good for sure, the steamed bagel concept is an interesting departure from your regular style. I did think some of the food would be even better toasted, but that's just my preference - it was certainly tasty, flavorful, and an interesting combination of elements that I did quite enjoy. The reason for deducting a star is atmosphere - I did not enjoy the heavy metal style music, which made the place just seem a bit obscure and not very upbead or positive vibes inducing. Despite that - and I'm sure many people would be into that atmosphere, it just wasn't for me - the food was very good, so overall I was still glad to try it. If you're not into that type of music either, perhaps I'd suggest getting the bagel to go and just walk to a park nearby and eat it there. Still, would recommend trying their bagels!

Very clean establishment, the staff is extremely friendly with it's customers. I got lost in the menu with so many items but boy it didn't matter. The breakfast sandwich was delicious! I'm definitely coming back here!

formatted_address: 1618 W Chicago Ave, Chicago, IL 60622, USA
name: Hoosier Mama Pie Company

reviews.text: Was warmly welcomed by the team, and Leigh helped me pick out a slice of pie. The sour cream cherry was delicious! Great service and great pie. Thank you, Leigh! :)

Come for the breakfast items & Dollop Coffee and stay for their amazing pie!  There is always a line. Some days it moves faster than others.

Always fresh and locally sourced, I’venever had a bad bite here.

I particularly like their muffins, fruit turnovers, & a biscuit with jam. My favorite pie is the “Fat Elvis.”

There is ample seating both indoors and outdoors. The bustling cafe is a common meeting place for friend and families. Recommended.

Im slowly compiling a list of what I do and don’t like. Here are my opinions
Love:
-match pie (light match flavor and consistency is creme brûlée)
-biscuits and gravy (gravy is so good and biscuits are buttery and flaky)
-lemon curd cheesecake (tarty and just enough sweetness)
-broccoli and cheddar quiche (crispy broccoli on top and cheesy crust)

Okay flavors
-coconut cream (not much coconut?)
-chocolate cream (tastes like chocolate pudding in a pie crust with whipped cream on top)
-triple chocolate (barely tastes like chocolate)
-lemon chess (not lemony enough)

Came here for breakfast and left very happy.  My partner and I shared a pie and a quiche so we have something sweet and something savory. We tried the monthly special: lemon chess with sticky blueberry pie and it was SO good. The quiche was good too and I know we’re gonna be coming back or ordering pies to-go from here in the future.

this is my favorite spot in evanston! the warmest atmosphere and kindest staff, along with phenomenal food and drinks. it is always such a treat to go here and the kind staff really make all the difference!

i went with my friend today and an employee remembered her tea order from a few weeks ago, it was so special!

formatted_address: 251 E Huron St, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text:
Ordered a caramel macchiato and it was awful! I couldn’t return it due to my work assignment in the hospital. I could not go back.

It had a “burnt” taste which tells me they don’t change the coffee grounds daily and it might be reused several days. Which causes that burnt taste. Old grounds and no regular cleaning of the machine.  Yuck!!

Zero stars
The atmosphere is super relaxed, super clean, they treat you the best, the workers are super cool, I recommend this place one hundred percent

Maybe spent less time drawing hearts and smiley face and more time on service. If my food and drink are ready don’t hold it just so you can doodle on everything. Going back to Hyatt. This location is terrible.

Have been to this location twice. Both times I asked for a large, was charged for a large, and then given a small.
Not worth the hassle to have it remade. Just won't be going back.

This Starbucks runs really well. Great for picking up before work.

Squeeze the day.

formatted_address: 1938 W Fullerton Ave Suite C, Chicago, IL 60614, USA
name: Panera Bread

reviews.text:
Great Panera, big and well staffed.  The food portions are now too small and too pricey though.  I wish Panera would go back to how they used to be, quality food, decent portions and decent prices.

These photos were taken on Nov 4,2024 @ 10:30am depicting a filthy men's room.  There was urine all over the floor, garbage overflowing and filthy sinks.  I am very concerned about the situation and will notify the Chicago Health Department before someone gets sick here.
I did Doordash and ordered  The Croissant sandwich and they sent me a Burnt sandwich and Door dash only refunded me $5 dollars! I had to throw my lunch in the garbage

I used to come here everyday, but please give me another reason to come again. Constant missing items, food quality is not as good. Portion control is never there. Not sure if I’ll be back, but please do better.

I've frequented this Panera Bread location on numerous occasions, and each visit reaffirms my choice. The ambiance is pleasant, but what truly makes this branch stand out is its exemplary staff. Specifically, a gentleman named Q who, on each encounter, has exemplified what exceptional customer service truly means. He's attentive, friendly, and ensures every order is perfect.

Speaking of perfection, my specialty salad is never just thrown together; it’s meticulously prepared, showcasing the dedication to quality and freshness that Panera is known for. And while everything on their menu is noteworthy, the cinnamon rolls here deserve a special mention. They're always soft, fresh, and just the right amount of sweet.

In summary, whether you're a fan of Panera Bread or just passing by, this particular location is well worth the visit. Expect top-notch food complemented by unparalleled service.

I like the new place,  it's bigger and with no carpet.  Plenty of seats, outdoor seating and drive thru.  It also has curb side pickup for convenience but it is easier to walk in and get your food.  I like their pick 2 deals, I usually eat one half in one seating then the other at another time. I usually order from the application and pickup at the restaurant.  I like their salads as well as their cookies and their smoothies.  I will keep coming back.

formatted_address: 2385 N Milwaukee Ave, Chicago, IL 60647, USA
name: Gaslight Coffee Roasters

reviews.text: It’s  cute little coffee shop on a great spot on the corner. It has a small menu of the classic coffee options like latte and cortado, and they have 3 syrup options of lavender, vanilla, or mocha (nope, no caramel!). I forget how small the 8oz is it fits so cutely in my hand but it was a good amount of coffee for my walk home. A bit higher prices but it’s a small business supporting our community! Plenty of seating and space to study, work, or chill!

Small batch craft roaster with a lovely cafe. Matcha latte is well balanced and made there with almond milk so ask if you have a different preference. Good place to get work done or meet with a friend. Most seating is for two. Would definitely recommend!

Always a good sign when they're serving espresso and tonic. The barista was super helpful and engaged with my random questions about the shop. Thanks :)

Grabbed a cup of the tonic and even got a free drip cup with my bag of Songwe, Tanzania. Happy with it all 👌

Well known spot that services the area with their roasting.

The one downside for me is the location. It's a little rough and there's graffiti all over the windows.

Cozy coffee shop and roaster in a narrow corner building. Interior is sparse, but what's there is very nice. If they're roasting you'll be able to smell the beans in Milwaukee as you approach.

Pastry selection was small, but solid and the drip coffee was one of the best I've had in a while. Definitely going to make a return trip to pick up some beans when I start running low.

It’s cool, calm and amazing energy in there! I always saw it and it was on my list. One day on my way to work the bus stopped at the near f the station and why not I said myself The matcha muffin and cortado are so good! If you want to have a creative and productive day, you should definitely come here because of the beautiful energy of this place!

formatted_address: 915 E 60th St, Chicago, IL 60637, USA
name: Reva and David Logan Center for the Arts

reviews.text:
Our concert experience as co-host and audience members at Logan Center leaves wonderful lasting impressions. Helpful to have box office support, separate green room, and backstage attendants. The Logan Center staff are friendly and professional.

We would happily work with Logan Center again to host a performance event or workshop and hope to return again soon. Thanks and merci! 💜
A GREAT, SPECTACULAR  venue  to  showcase performing  arts,I had a great time .Everyone  was fantastic.

Came here for a recital and I'll gladly be back! The parking lot is open to the public weekdays after 4p and all day weekends, so I'll definitely use that for future visits. But street parking isn't too hard to come by either. There are no restrooms on the 9th floor, where the recital was held, and only single occupant bathrooms on 8th.

The performance hall is an excellent place for chamber music and other small to medium sized groups. Great for jazz concerts also, minus the beverages. The cafe also hosts jazz sessions, and beverages are available. The performance penthouse has breathtaking views. Nearby parking. Nothing not to like!
The performance was wonderfully informative musical depicting the African American journey from the African Kingdom through the many struggles and triumphs to present day.

formatted_address: 333 West Wacker Drive Lobby, W Lake St, Chicago, IL 60606, USA
name: Goodwin's Restaurants

reviews.text: I think I messed up… Goodwin’s has so many great options and I decided to order the sandwich with turkey and sour cream! The Nogales sandwich features an interesting combination that I have no idea why I ordered. It was good and showcase delicious meat, but there are so many better options like the Cuban Reuben or any traditional sandwich. The service was great and the owner is very welcoming. The atmosphere is free but a little contrasting, with the green apple logo contrasting the decorations that include surfboards. Overall, I enjoyed my experience at Goodwin’s and will be back to try another sandwich. For now, I give Goodwin’s 4 stars!

Goodwin’s is an absolute gem! The service is impeccable – the owner and his team here go above and beyond to make every visit a delight. Their menu is a testament to fresh, quality ingredients and creativity. From vibrant, crisp salads (and dressings that will leave you dreaming of more) to flavorful wraps, hearty homemade soups, and inventive sandwiches, every bite is phenomenal. Whether you’re grabbing a quick lunch or enjoying a leisurely meal, Goodwin’s is sure to exceed expectations. Highly recommend!

Goodwins is an amazing place. the food is always fresh and there is a ton of food on your plate. Tom the manager (i believe) is amazing he always helps me to get our corporate lunches organized and delivered on time. Wonderful place wonderful service

We are so lucky to have this spot in our building. The food is amazing whether breakfast or lunch and the owner Tom is top notch.
His customer service skills is off the chain and expects the same from his employees.
Let's talk about the food, it's fresh and seasoned well. My favorite breakfast sandwich is called the Venice it's toasted bread, peanut butter and thick bacon slices with a drizzle of honey. For lunch my spouse go to is the Corvallis: Sliced turkey breast, lettuce, avocado, tomato, cheddar cheese & monterey jack cheese with 1,000 island dressing on wheat, mine is the Ranier:
Roasted turkey breast, crisp bacon, cole slaw, cheddar cheese and russian dressing on sour dough

Me and my friends normally come here to eat but this particular day we ate a salad and found a long blonde gross hair inside our salad.
We normally come to see the Italian cashier girl who is so so sweet unfortunately they told us that she wasn't working there anymore and I can see why. We are so disappointed we will miss her. But we can see why she left,
The owner seems utterly out of touch with his employees and treats them horribly also the place seems a little bit racist to me because the white girl gets to keep her hair down while all the other employees who are Latin I see put their hair up.  Explains why there was hair in our food. This place is terrible especially now that that Italian girl isn't working anymore. Do not go back!  Trust me it smells like cigarettes and there WILL be hair in your food or worse. Just gross 🤢 🤮

formatted_address: 2959 N Lincoln Ave, Chicago, IL 60657, USA
name: Heritage Bikes & Coffee

reviews.text: Heritage is my favorite coffee on the north side and their food is also incredible! I love sitting on their patio especially since Chicago is finally defrosting for spring.
Very cute coffee shop, huge windows and a good amount of seating so this place would be great to study/work in! The coffee was also delicious!

Heritage Coffee and Bikes has a cool and diverse crowd and a wonderful place to grab coffee or lunch.  The coffee is second to none, but what really has me coming back is the customer service. Ben, the manager, knows returning clients by name and is genuinely happy to see them, greet them and provide excellent service.  I can't help but think of the last chorus line from Cheers song: "Our troubles are all the same, You wanna be where everybody knows your name"  Thank you to Ben and all of the wonderful baristas who take care of me.

This place is the tits!!! Everyone has good vibes and you can tell that they put that good good energy into their drinks/food 😎 fr, customer service is kind and everything tastes fire 🔥 also GET THE VEGAN CRUNCHWRAP even if you aren’t vegan

Heritage Bikes & Coffee is my go-to spot in Lakeview when I need a caffeine fix and some chill vibes. Last weekend, I swung by and grabbed their lavender latte with macadamia milk—super smooth and just the right hint of floral. Paired it with their breakfast burrito, which was loaded and totally hit the spot. Spent about $15 total, and it was worth every penny. The space has this cozy, vintage feel with big windows that let in tons of natural light—perfect for people-watching or getting some work done. Plus, it's cool to see folks getting their bikes tuned up while sipping on coffee. Definitely a unique blend of cafe and bike shop that captures the neighborhood's vibe.​

formatted_address: 1114 W Belmont Ave, Chicago, IL 60657, USA
name: Bittersweet Pastry Shop & Cafe

reviews.text: Lovely staff / great service. The place is quiet and clean with big windows for natural light. The food is high quality but maybe too inventive for my tastes? The ham and gruyere quiche was excellent! Very, very cheesy - I'd recommend getting something else carby to eat along with it. I know a light flaky crust is generally highly desirable (and it certainly was light and flaky) but in this case, I'd actually have liked a thicker crust to offset some of that cheese. Unfortunately, the almond croissant looked better than it tasted. I also had a chocolate brownie because I was looking for a chocolate boost but it fell flat as well - seemed to have some odd undertones? And I would have loved to enjoy the rich sipping chocolate with the croissant (I suspect it would have made the croissant much more of what I wanted) except the hot chocolate has citrus and spices which I wasn't looking for. If you like complex flavors and are looking for other flavors but not necessarily a chocolate fix, it's a great place.

What a cute little bakery and cafe. Decorated so cute inside and their plates were adorable. We had a chocolate croissant and iced coffees. I got their vanilla bean latte iced they make their vanilla bean in house!

We did wedding cake tastings with multiple bakeries, but Bittersweet’s quality blew the competition out of the water. All of the cakes, frostings, and fillings we tried were delicious, and the ones we chose for our cake came together perfectly! The cake was decorated beautifully and tasted amazing. If you want a custom cake that’s a step above the rest, look no further than Bittersweet.
Lovely atmosphere. Mango layer sheet pastry it’s delicious!!! Stunning texture very fresh crispy and the right amount of sweetness.

Stopped here on a Thursday evening for something sweet. I ordered a double chocolate fudge brownie that was amazing, and their signature hot chocolate. The serving size for the hot chocolate was very generous and it was really tasty.

I also ordered some bakery items to go - croissants with the esquites filling (delicious, plus they were BOGO that evening so I got one free), and some bread.

Service was great, I will definitely be back to try out more stuff!

formatted_address: 1430 W Taylor St, Chicago, IL 60607, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: More then half my drink was foam. There should be more coaching on what is expected for drinks to look like because i paid over $7 for this. I get matcha gets clumpy because of the new recipe, but im a partner myself and this could have been easily prevented. I did not have time to ask for a remake or call back so this makes it more frustrating.

I have been coming to this Starbucks for years . However I placed a mobile order and came in to pick it up . I went and grabbed both of my items . The young lady Vonnie saw I did . I asked for the sauce that came with my sandwich . She proceeded to ask me “ did I purchase a packet of sauce”. The sauce is approximately.26 ounces and she asked me did I purchase the sauce . I find this highly offensive. She then proceeded to say I need to know if you brought the sandwich and drink . Basically racially profiling me . I hope she receives a warning because I will not be back at this location for a while now

If I could leave 0 stars I absolutely would. It’s absurd how understaffed and overworked the people are here. I recently moved into the area so this has become my go - to Starbucks and the last 3 days their has been a woman with short hair ( who honestly is the only reason I come back) who is so kind but my heart breaks for her  because all  the other workers seem to be little to no help. Sitting around, on their phones (highly unprofessional). This place NEEDS better staffing and better management. It’s sad walking in and seeing what I’ve experienced coming here. Safe to say I won’t be coming here AGAIN!
The best Starbucks around with the nicest baristas. I go here a lot because they're really kind and they make the drinks well. Would recommend.

Overall I like visiting this Starbucks.
I frequently come to this store but;
-For winter: Inside is too cold, AC doesn’t work properly especially the one on the door. I guess they don’t want us to stay longer.
-Sometimes: Slow, long line. Using online order, you don’t want to wait in line, but mostly they don’t open their online system.
-Self-pay parking is available.

formatted_address: 6 E Chestnut St, Chicago, IL 60611, USA
name: Tempo Cafe

reviews.text: Sat outside nice location good views and cute setup. The vegetarian scrambler is a solid choice for the money it was easily enough for two people if your trying to be light on a lunch or brunch. The french toast is not worth it, too eggy and lacking any real sweetness def not worth the price would get something else.

It was the best breakfast we had in Chicago. They really do American breakfast very well, and I highly recommend it. We had scrambled eggs with vegetables and fruit pancakes. Even for two people, it was more than enough. It was extremely delicious as well. The inside was a bit dark and crowded, and the tables were very close to each other, but I didn’t see it as a problem. Definitely a place to visit!

Tasty brunch food in a friendly laid-back atmosphere! I came here for brunch with a friend and enjoyed their skillets! The eggs were fluffy, the toppings were fresh, and the potatoes were well cooked. I got the cheese on the potatoes, but honestly, I don’t think it’s too necessary - it’s good but the amount they put made the dish a bit too heavy for my liking

The food was I good, I got the Greek salad and a fresh juice and it was alright, but imma be honest, the prices were through the roof for me. The marmalade was really good tho, like really really good.

I was actually dissapointed here as the food quality wasn't quite what I expected.  The gravy came cool and slightly crusted as if under a heat lamp too long and the mashed potatoes were cool instead of hot. The turkey was real, fresh and good ...just too bad the meal wasn't hot.  I hope it was just one of those days...othwrwise rhe atmosphere is great as I love American style diners, the staff are friendly and the place is clean.
